<?xml version='1.0' encoding='utf-8'?>
<graphml xmlns="http://graphml.graphdrawing.org/xmlns" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:schemaLocation="http://graphml.graphdrawing.org/xmlns http://graphml.graphdrawing.org/xmlns/1.0/graphml.xsd">
  <key id="d6" for="edge" attr.name="source_id" attr.type="string" />
  <key id="d5" for="edge" attr.name="keywords" attr.type="string" />
  <key id="d4" for="edge" attr.name="description" attr.type="string" />
  <key id="d3" for="edge" attr.name="weight" attr.type="double" />
  <key id="d2" for="node" attr.name="source_id" attr.type="string" />
  <key id="d1" for="node" attr.name="description" attr.type="string" />
  <key id="d0" for="node" attr.name="entity_type" attr.type="string" />
  <graph edgedefault="undirected">
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 415&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 415 elaborates on the acquisition of benefits from received property and restitution conditions when the recipient switches from good to bad faith."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-fcc1f7edc6fff66f0cf31baecb707aad</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 416&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 416 mandates full reimbursement for necessary preservation, maintenance, or repair expenses of property to the person returning it."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-fcc1f7edc6fff66f0cf31baecb707aad</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 417&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 417 limits reimbursement for additional expenses to those made in good faith, contributing to property value at the restoration time."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-fcc1f7edc6fff66f0cf31baecb707aad</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 419&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 419 sets a time limit for actions regarding undue enrichment."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-fcc1f7edc6fff66f0cf31baecb707aad</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 420&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 420 defines and outlines liability for committing wrongful acts that harm others' rights."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-fcc1f7edc6fff66f0cf31baecb707aad</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;RESTITUTION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Restitution refers to the return of what has been unduly gained, often involving specific legal conditions to be fulfilled."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-fcc1f7edc6fff66f0cf31baecb707aad</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;MORAL DUTY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Moral duty refers to actions performed out of ethical obligation rather than legal requirement, which may affect entitlement to restitution."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-fcc1f7edc6fff66f0cf31baecb707aad</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SOCIAL PROPRIETY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Social propriety refers to actions in alignment with societal norms and expectations, affecting legal considerations like restitution."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-fcc1f7edc6fff66f0cf31baecb707aad</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;PROPERTY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Property discusses ownership and various rights associated with it, as outlined from Section 1298 to Section 1307 in the Civil and Commercial Code."&lt;SEP&gt;"Property in this context refers to the physical assets or real estate that are subject to the hire agreement between a letter and hirer."&lt;SEP&gt;"Property is the subject of the contract of hire, to be maintained by the hirer and delivered in good repair by the letter."&lt;SEP&gt;"Property refers to assets or possessions that can be retained or affected by obligations between debtors and creditors."&lt;SEP&gt;"Property refers to assets or possessions that may be subject to preferential rights or retained by creditors as security for a debt."&lt;SEP&gt;"Property refers to both movable and immovable assets that may be subject to various transactions, management, and legal proceedings as outlined in the document."&lt;SEP&gt;"Property refers to items of value, such as goods or money, that are involved in loan and deposit transactions within the document."&lt;SEP&gt;"Property refers to land or goods that can be owned, transferred, or acquired under legal regulations."&lt;SEP&gt;"Property refers to owned assets, which in legal contexts are subject to restitution rules involving rightful ownership and enhancements."&lt;SEP&gt;"Property refers to the assets or resources specially appropriated for the foundation's objectives, not for private profit."&lt;SEP&gt;"Property refers to the objects or items brought by the depositor or traveler to be safeguarded, such as luggage, specie, currency notes, bills, bonds, jewels, or other valuables."&lt;SEP&gt;"Property refers to assets owned by individuals or entities, protected under law from illegal acts such as theft or damage, as listed in Sections 334 to 365."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-5429b702233c5b142e4f7e7899dffac1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fcc1f7edc6fff66f0cf31baecb707aad&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-47c412635e02e67c8c5e723ae7e9d0ea&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ac44eff8208c6427b97025d89925979e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cc95f23cfbd6112c8327703d8101a010&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-629bbfda7f476a27cd4f982000bd902b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-46940167ee3908fb358c9a82647ea322&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bd6efc93031ebfde67a4ae4a12bbe3ce&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a3d4a61fa1cf40d9a40ee60bcdbb217e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9926eb44610bf5182e4fad6451742c28&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bac2de5ec87beec114bb4549e917cb4e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-880c1ecd6c4ca0a05ce8398767d6a999</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;BAD FAITH&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Bad faith describes dishonesty or deception in legal conduct, increasing liability and reducing entitlements, e.g., in restitution."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-fcc1f7edc6fff66f0cf31baecb707aad</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;FORCE MAJEUR&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Force majeur refers to extraordinary events beyond control that may affect legal liabilities or responsibilities, such as in restitution."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-fcc1f7edc6fff66f0cf31baecb707aad</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;FRUIT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"In legal terms, fruit refers to benefits derived from property, subject to restitution rules based on timing and the recipient's faith."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-fcc1f7edc6fff66f0cf31baecb707aad</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;AGENCY AGREEMENT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The formal arrangement between a principal and an agent, detailing the tasks and responsibilities the agent is to perform on behalf of the principal."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-86f6e708f5c93636e3a2e9b024058eac</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THAI CONTRACTS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Thai Contracts is a category section on the Samuiforsale website that provides information related to legal contracts in Thailand."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-f2d6a052f92eea2a650b78a251a1b5bb</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;PRINCIPAL&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A principal is a person who employs an agent to perform tasks or acts on their behalf under a contract."&lt;SEP&gt;"A principal is an individual or entity who provides authority to an agent to act on their behalf, typically retaining the ultimate responsibility and benefits of the agent's actions."&lt;SEP&gt;"The individual or entity who authorizes an agent to act on their behalf in transactions or business dealings."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-86f6e708f5c93636e3a2e9b024058eac&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b3971476de4ec8b22a6311d4e55caca0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e5738a6d02b9e258a742c992fef4b611</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;AGENT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"An agent is a person authorized to act for another, known as the principal, under a contract of agency."&lt;SEP&gt;"An agent is an individual or entity acting on behalf of a principal to perform certain tasks or duties, often with the authority to make decisions within a specified scope."&lt;SEP&gt;"The individual or entity authorized to act on behalf of the principal, responsible for executing duties as specified in the agency agreement."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-86f6e708f5c93636e3a2e9b024058eac&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b3971476de4ec8b22a6311d4e55caca0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e5738a6d02b9e258a742c992fef4b611</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SUBAGENT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A person designated by the agent, potentially with the principal's approval, to carry out specific tasks or duties within the scope of the agency."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-86f6e708f5c93636e3a2e9b024058eac</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;AUTHORITY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Authority refers to the power or right granted to the agent to act on behalf of the principal in various transactions."&lt;SEP&gt;"The legal power or right given to the agent or subagent to make decisions and act on behalf of the principal."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-86f6e708f5c93636e3a2e9b024058eac&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b3971476de4ec8b22a6311d4e55caca0</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;REMUNERATION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Compensation or payment that the agent is entitled to receive for performing tasks on behalf of the principal as specified in the agency agreement."&lt;SEP&gt;"Remuneration is compensation that may be implied or agreed upon for services rendered during the deposit of property."&lt;SEP&gt;"Remuneration is the compensation determined by the court to be paid to the manager for handling the property of an absent person."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-86f6e708f5c93636e3a2e9b024058eac&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-629bbfda7f476a27cd4f982000bd902b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-055e2a0c9f60207819211360d38e04f8</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;LIABILITY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Legal responsibility that both the principal and agent have towards each other, as well as to third parties, in relation to actions performed under the agency agreement."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-86f6e708f5c93636e3a2e9b024058eac</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;BANKRUPTCY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A legal proceeding involving a partnership or company that cannot repay outstanding debts and seeks relief from some or all of its liabilities."&lt;SEP&gt;"A legal status involving a person or entity that cannot repay debts owed, potentially affecting the continuation of an agency."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bankruptcy is a legal state wherein an individual or organization cannot meet its debt obligations, impacting the rights of debtors and creditors."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bankruptcy is a legal status of a person or organization that cannot repay the debts it owes to creditors, affecting the division of Sin Somros."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bankruptcy is a legal status of an association that can lead to its dissolution if declared by a court judgment."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-34e7b7cbd3efe1f3b5bdd00742010ed6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-182a2b244fdc4ad235c762ab46288dca&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-aac23a1f6cf12366451f6be3ff0a3ed2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2f3971fdef62800a7dabb59d8dfbd427&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-86f6e708f5c93636e3a2e9b024058eac</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THIRD PERSON&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A Third Person is an external party who may challenge the buyer's rights to the property, potentially leading to legal action affecting both buyer and seller."&lt;SEP&gt;"A Third Person refers to an individual or entity, not originally part of the obligation, who may perform the obligation on behalf of the debtor."&lt;SEP&gt;"A third person is an entity that gains benefit from a contract made between other parties, with the right to claim performance directly."&lt;SEP&gt;"A third person is an outside party who is not a partner but may be affected by partnership transactions or agreements."&lt;SEP&gt;"Any individual or entity external to the principal-agent relationship who might be involved or affected by the agent's actions under the agency."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-81d63dbc17e3f3707788a6e2552b764c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-23efb3388014eb72630dbca0d161e5c7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-86f6e708f5c93636e3a2e9b024058eac&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6cd9b0e3cf4adfb36e41fca038140314&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-33f27ab34f7ee4094ebd4f5171db4171</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;MEETING NOTICE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"An official announcement informing shareholders about the details of an upcoming general meeting."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-740fcd675101e2f9ab2be7e083f3215d</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;REIMBURSEMENT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Reimbursement is the act of repaying someone for expenses they have incurred on behalf of another."&lt;SEP&gt;"The act of compensating the agent for expenses reasonably incurred while executing tasks on behalf of the principal."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-86f6e708f5c93636e3a2e9b024058eac&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fb415930f5508ba24d6b39a4a2237451</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;MARRIAGE REGISTRAR&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"ROLE"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Marriage Registrar is an official responsible for maintaining the Marriage Register and recording void marriages notified by the Court."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Marriage Registrar is responsible for updating the Marriage Register with changes notified by the Court."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9eea79da373e97e5b9f92916632488ba&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2f3971fdef62800a7dabb59d8dfbd427</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;ANTE-NUPTIAL AGREEMENT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"An Ante-nuptial Agreement is a legal document established before marriage, affecting property management and Sin Somros provisions."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9eea79da373e97e5b9f92916632488ba</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;LAW ONLINE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Law Online is a referenced website that offers legal information related to Thailand."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-f2d6a052f92eea2a650b78a251a1b5bb</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;ADOPTION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Adoption is a legal process by which a person becomes the legal parent of a child, involving rights and responsibilities traditionally held by natural parents."&lt;SEP&gt;"Adoption refers to the legal process by which a person becomes the lawful child of a parent or parents other than his or her birth parents, with rights and duties outlined in legal sections."&lt;SEP&gt;"Adoption, described in Section 1598 of the Civil and Commercial Code, outlines the legal procedure for adopting a child."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-5429b702233c5b142e4f7e7899dffac1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e6503e3e2e955a071268b1be787bc7d1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5de833b12d9eff458c614eff446c0d4b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;ADOPTOR&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Adoptor is the person who legally adopts another person, usually a child, and gains certain rights and responsibilities as detailed in adoption laws."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-5de833b12d9eff458c614eff446c0d4b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;ADOPTED CHILD&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"An adopted child is a child legally taken and regarded as one's own, entitled to the same inheritance rights as a biological child."&lt;SEP&gt;"An adopted child is a minor who has been legally taken and treated as the offspring of someone who is not their biological parent."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Adopted Child is the individual who becomes the legal child of the Adoptor, acquiring certain rights while potentially losing natural parental connections as per adoption regulations."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-4c5aad3770b3111c6e3b4171b1b6cb5c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c2ac78f2ab241f4845c5c94a44c0ffb6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5de833b12d9eff458c614eff446c0d4b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;DIVIDEND&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A distribution of a company's earnings to its shareholders, as prescribed by law."&lt;SEP&gt;"A portion of a company's profit paid to shareholders, as defined by various sections within the company regulations."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-b23ff2ff58dfd16196c0503c1c3ca1b2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-740fcd675101e2f9ab2be7e083f3215d</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;NATURAL PARENT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Natural Parent is the biological parent of the Adopted Child, who may lose parental power upon the child's adoption."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-5de833b12d9eff458c614eff446c0d4b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1598/21&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1598/21 is part of the legal code that outlines specific regulations and requirements related to adoption procedures."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-5de833b12d9eff458c614eff446c0d4b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1598/27&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1598/27 refers to the legal provision stating the conditions under which adoption is considered valid, specifically involving registration."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-5de833b12d9eff458c614eff446c0d4b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1598/28&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1598/28 describes the status and rights acquired by the Adopted Child as a legitimate child of the Adoptor, and the impact on natural parental rights."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-5de833b12d9eff458c614eff446c0d4b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SHAREHOLDER&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A Shareholder is an individual or entity that holds shares in the company and has rights and responsibilities detailed in the company’s regulations."&lt;SEP&gt;"A Shareholder is an individual or entity that legally owns one or more shares of a company's stock and has certain rights such as voting on corporate matters."&lt;SEP&gt;"A Shareholder is an individual or entity that owns shares in a company and may have liabilities continuing even after the company is struck off."&lt;SEP&gt;"An individual or entity that owns shares in a company and is entitled to vote at general meetings."&lt;SEP&gt;"Shareholder refers to an individual who holds shares in a company and possesses certain voting rights depending on shareholding conditions."&lt;SEP&gt;"Shareholders are individuals or entities that own shares in a company and receive notices regarding company decisions and changes."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-28aaa22d510e3f49e80675454af7f8a3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4b333b466a8e220c02cd14e77e8fb935&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7b4f64350387b4e64a273fdcc8130b07&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-740fcd675101e2f9ab2be7e083f3215d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-691e23128e3c79c43c11b76dcdb0c630&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6cd60bb5f8e5d886648c66def090b185</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1598/29&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1598/29 is a legal provision detailing that adoption does not grant the Adoptor the right to inherit from the Adopted Child."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-5de833b12d9eff458c614eff446c0d4b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1598/30&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1598/30 covers the rights of the Adoptor to reclaim properties given to the Adopted Child if the latter dies without heirs."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-5de833b12d9eff458c614eff446c0d4b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1598/31&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1598/31 outlines the procedures for dissolving an adoption, either through mutual consent or court order, depending on the Adopted Child's status."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-5de833b12d9eff458c614eff446c0d4b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;REQUISITION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A formal request by shareholders to summon an extraordinary general meeting to address specific issues."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-740fcd675101e2f9ab2be7e083f3215d</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1598/32&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1598/32 states that adoption is dissolved by the law if a marriage contravenes Section 1451."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-5de833b12d9eff458c614eff446c0d4b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;RESOLUTION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Decisions or official statements passed at a general meeting, often requiring specific voting processes."&lt;SEP&gt;"Resolution is a formal decision made during a general meeting, subject to voting by shareholders and sometimes requiring a special majority."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-740fcd675101e2f9ab2be7e083f3215d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7b4f64350387b4e64a273fdcc8130b07</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1598/33&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1598/33 details the grounds on which an action for the dissolution of adoption may be claimed, including misconduct or non-compliance with duties."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-5de833b12d9eff458c614eff446c0d4b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1598/34&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1598/34 specifies the time limits within which an action for the dissolution of adoption must be initiated."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-5de833b12d9eff458c614eff446c0d4b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1598/35&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1598/35 describes the procedures for bringing an action for dissolution of adoption on behalf of an Adopted Child under a certain age."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-5de833b12d9eff458c614eff446c0d4b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;COMPANY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A business entity with shareholders, directors, and regulations governing its operations and meetings."&lt;SEP&gt;"A company is a legal entity formed by a group of individuals to engage in and operate a business enterprise."&lt;SEP&gt;"A legal entity formed by a group of individuals to engage in and operate a business enterprise."&lt;SEP&gt;"Company refers to a legal entity that holds general meetings, creates financial reports, and follows specific voting and resolution regulations."&lt;SEP&gt;"Company signifies an organization that may need to recognize the creation of a pledge in its books, especially concerning shares or debentures."&lt;SEP&gt;"The term 'company' refers to limited companies that are subject to laws regarding dissolution, amalgamation, and conversion into a limited company."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-f92e53c4b928412441b1d00eeb6aab74&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-34e7b7cbd3efe1f3b5bdd00742010ed6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-28aaa22d510e3f49e80675454af7f8a3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7b4f64350387b4e64a273fdcc8130b07&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ddd247e62a952c755b8e64cbea59a2d3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-740fcd675101e2f9ab2be7e083f3215d</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1598/36&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1598/36 explains the effect of a court judgment on the dissolution of adoption, specifying when it becomes effective."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-5de833b12d9eff458c614eff446c0d4b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SAMUIFORSALE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
      <data key="d1">"An organization mentioned in the context of offering feedback forms, possibly involved in real estate or legal services."&lt;SEP&gt;"SAMUIFORSALE is a webpage offering real estate information and legal resources about property law in Thailand."&lt;SEP&gt;"SamuiForSale is an organization or entity mentioned in the text, possibly related to real estate or legal services, as indicated by its contact form link."&lt;SEP&gt;"SamuiForSale seems to be a component or form mentioned in the feedback sections."&lt;SEP&gt;"Samuiforsale appears to be a feedback link possibly related to a web form or service, but not directly involved in divorce proceedings."&lt;SEP&gt;"Samuiforsale is a platform providing general Thai legal information and resources in English, aimed at expats in Thailand."&lt;SEP&gt;"Samuiforsale is a platform providing general legal information and resources in English regarding Thai law, specifically aimed at expatriates in Thailand."&lt;SEP&gt;"Samuiforsale is an online platform offering English translations and general information about Thai legal matters, useful for expats living in Thailand."&lt;SEP&gt;"Samuiforsale is an organization providing general Thai legal information, though it does not replace specific legal advice."&lt;SEP&gt;"Samuiforsale provides Thai legal information and law resources in English, targeted at expats in Thailand."&lt;SEP&gt;"Samuiforsale provides general Thai legal information and law resources in English online, targeted at expats."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-8ddccbf45ec50ee6c41104c7f6c4c61b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0e69519b80d6cad28fe98f2e9235bd60&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8db429ff50410ec3964e2dd051739fba&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3eb681d2c9c192f73e0418def1ff82e7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8ce6f1498128f5fc6034c5e3b827db4f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cced3c5fac31674d85b89a0610b1ee09&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-af5697d7b87ddc73215d01d7439bac2b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-63871d590b9819463b4e112a2305a28f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f2d6a052f92eea2a650b78a251a1b5bb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e0099557ffbf92309faf8ac19f118ba2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2b194bfa1a18d3dffd302b027ba18352</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;PLEDGEE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Pledgee is an individual or entity that holds and enforces the pledge, responsible for notifying the debtor and selling the pledged property."&lt;SEP&gt;"Pledgee is the person who receives movable property from the pledgor as security in a pledge contract."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-b3971476de4ec8b22a6311d4e55caca0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f92e53c4b928412441b1d00eeb6aab74</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;CAPITAL&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Capital refers to a city that serves as the seat of government for a country or region."&lt;SEP&gt;"The financial assets or resources that a company utilizes for its operations, significant in assessing company losses."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-cbeb601f9cbed905a0411d31327a5a60&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-740fcd675101e2f9ab2be7e083f3215d</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;PLEDGOR&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Pledgor is the individual or entity who provides property as security in a pledge and is entitled to any surplus from its sale."&lt;SEP&gt;"Pledgor is the person who, in a pledge contract, delivers movable property to another, the pledgee, as security for performing an obligation."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-b3971476de4ec8b22a6311d4e55caca0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f92e53c4b928412441b1d00eeb6aab74</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;DIRECTOR&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A Director is an appointed or elected member of a company's board of directors, holding responsibility for the strategic direction and potential liabilities of the company."&lt;SEP&gt;"A member of the board responsible for overseeing company operations and making decisions, subject to shareholder approval."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Director is a person responsible for managing the company, overseeing operations, and ensuring compliance with established regulations and shareholder meetings."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-6cd60bb5f8e5d886648c66def090b185&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-740fcd675101e2f9ab2be7e083f3215d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-691e23128e3c79c43c11b76dcdb0c630</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;WAREHOUSEMAN&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A warehouseman is a person who stores and maintains goods for remuneration in the usual course of business."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-b3971476de4ec8b22a6311d4e55caca0</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;PLEDGED PROPERTY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Pledged Property refers to the goods or assets provided as security under a pledge agreement, held by the pledgee until obligations are fulfilled."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-b3971476de4ec8b22a6311d4e55caca0</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;INTEREST&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Interest is the cost of borrowing money, usually calculated as a percentage of the outstanding balance. It may cease to accrue during the creditor's default."&lt;SEP&gt;"Interest refers to the cost paid for borrowing money, which is subject to legal restrictions on rates in the document."&lt;SEP&gt;"Interest refers to the periodic payment made by the debtor to the creditor as part of the financial obligation."&lt;SEP&gt;"Payments made to shareholders from the company's profit, usually prescribed by law."&lt;SEP&gt;"The additional amount payable to the agent on advances or expenses made while executing tasks, calculated from the day the payment was made."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-c35036965b446b68b1f64bc55f989965&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-629bbfda7f476a27cd4f982000bd902b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-740fcd675101e2f9ab2be7e083f3215d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-86f6e708f5c93636e3a2e9b024058eac&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e7fb2f4e3c8f089ed58aad2cf781f6f9</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;NOTIFICATION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Notification is the formal communication that must be sent by the pledgee to notify the debtor or pledgor about the enforcement actions or details of an auction."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-b3971476de4ec8b22a6311d4e55caca0</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;GENERAL MEETING&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A General Meeting is an assembly of an association's members where resolutions, such as dissolution or asset transfer, are decided."&lt;SEP&gt;"A General Meeting is an event where decisions regarding the company's directors, such as their appointment and remuneration, are made. It plays a crucial role in the governance of the company."&lt;SEP&gt;"A General Meeting is an event where shareholders and company officials gather to discuss and consent on matters such as bearing inspection expenses from company assets."&lt;SEP&gt;"A formal assembly of shareholders, required to be held within specified intervals to discuss company matters, classified as ordinary or extraordinary."&lt;SEP&gt;"A formal assembly of the partners or shareholders in a partnership or company to confirm directors, appoint liquidators, adopt balance-sheets, and make decisions about the settlement of the organization's affairs."&lt;SEP&gt;"A gathering of the company's shareholders where critical decisions, such as declaring dividends, are made."&lt;SEP&gt;"General Meeting is an event where shareholders gather to discuss and vote on resolutions concerning the company's operations."&lt;SEP&gt;"The General Meeting involves partners or members of a company making decisions about liquidation, appointing liquidators, and confirming balance-sheets."&lt;SEP&gt;"The general meeting, referred to as the statutory meeting, is held by promoters for subscribers to discuss company business once shares are paid."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-34e7b7cbd3efe1f3b5bdd00742010ed6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-182a2b244fdc4ad235c762ab46288dca&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7b4f64350387b4e64a273fdcc8130b07&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-740fcd675101e2f9ab2be7e083f3215d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fd4f265f6be599f877d85099036f52dc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-237bd5a5c70b356f874e427eb5f0128b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-07706a49d3b190ef1fa2b1178a2e275f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b23ff2ff58dfd16196c0503c1c3ca1b2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-83644292281589f5325e70fbbf9a5034</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;PUBLIC AUCTION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A Public Auction is an event in which goods or properties, like forfeited shares, are sold to the highest bidder, often used by companies to liquidate assets or recover debts."&lt;SEP&gt;"A process by which perishable or risky property connected with an offence may be sold by the government before expiration of legal periods."&lt;SEP&gt;"Public Auction is a process where the seller, after notifying the defaulting buyer, can sell the property to the highest bidder if payment is not made."&lt;SEP&gt;"Public Auction is a sale event through which unclaimed or perishable luggage is sold by the carrier if not collected within specified timeframes."&lt;SEP&gt;"Public Auction is a specific type of auction where the pledged property is sold to the highest bidder in an open forum."&lt;SEP&gt;"Public Auction is an event where property is sold to the highest bidder, often under legal circumstances such as those ordered by a court or bankruptcy proceedings."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9ca3fcb51a635c23cbd4974dd21e277f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4b333b466a8e220c02cd14e77e8fb935&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7289405ac6638bb4a476489ae0c1b33d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2c753f490ffe4fe92240bb63a93c4481&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b3971476de4ec8b22a6311d4e55caca0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-880c1ecd6c4ca0a05ce8398767d6a999</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;EXPENSES&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Expenses refer to the costs incurred for preserving or maintaining the pledged property, which may be reimbursed."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-b3971476de4ec8b22a6311d4e55caca0</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1664&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1664 is a legal provision that declares the invalidity of a will made under certain emergency conditions if the testator can later make a will in prescribed forms."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 1664 states the validity period for wills made under exceptional circumstances, lasting one month after normal conditions resume."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-950a514fa4e2ba58663fe41bd3a39da9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-96ca137e685d301646809ca5adf41812</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;PUBLIC PROSECUTOR&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">The Public Prosecutor is a legal official with diverse responsibilities and authorities in the judicial system. They represent the state's interests and are empowered to initiate legal actions on behalf of the state, especially in cases involving familial legal matters. The Public Prosecutor is authorized to conduct criminal prosecutions and present cases in court, ensuring adherence to judicial proceedings.

Additionally, the Public Prosecutor plays a crucial role in matters concerning individuals who cannot represent themselves. They may apply to the court for the appointment of a representative ad litem for a child without a legal representative or initiate legal actions on behalf of an adopted child, especially when the child is under certain age conditions. In cases where parental consent for adoption is unreasonably refused, the Public Prosecutor can apply to the court for adoption applications.

The Public Prosecutor can be involved in guardianship issues, including applying for the adjudication of a person as incompetent, appointing guardians, custodians, or curators, and seeking the discharge of a guardian when necessary. They have the authority to manage issues related to the property of missing persons, including provisional measures and court decisions related to adjudications of disappearance.

In terms of marriage and familial relationships, the Public Prosecutor can apply to void a marriage if no involved party can do so and represent the state's interests concerning will-created foundations. They also have the authority to apply for the appropriation of assets from dissolved foundations and address violations of an association's regulations.

The Public Prosecutor ensures compliance with court-determined conditions, submits changes regarding court orders for children's care, and addresses misconduct related to guardianship. Furthermore, they have the exclusive power to prosecute for relegation and manage cases involving detained persons' violations. Through all these roles, the Public Prosecutor maintains the legal and state interests within the judicial framework.</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-a0818329731c6e20f0c0c43a0133253c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cb6f943ed567718e3b0963e9f80b3c0b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-140da0bea780fb9ec8b35168f6556b93&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-268065f480c7c2e17bd0004a31f0f454&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6e4efb3313af866dc7bcaba7c4daff62&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-edf03699076f42c474bd2d773c684e42&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ce00bf86a210ec770e6555803254e48b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9fb8ecc1d3b7f08bd11bfbe372805373&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a2aa959400bcd6663682a867aebf2801&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e417732f0f4e36ea8784fa2cc5dd8a85&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-42fad725aa98ee40547f7a36e0de09d6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2f3971fdef62800a7dabb59d8dfbd427&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e8a12bcf29dd0e194c7a3e4a71523199&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4e5197de768063837bf5a455698da0aa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1f4064eab77e56a7c7daab785bacf7e8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-99e04c388a7385a4978847a999d423f1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-86deb2357b8656ccf8680e27cbac71ec&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e0099557ffbf92309faf8ac19f118ba2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e1e198b1f8b66564b0fae2fbe893a4c6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6158dfc7a7c5c354484d988186bd2709&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6fd5b0ac67c6f4aafc6e1ef0e7ce2a77&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d9947bc7fb3e59afe960708bcf533e3c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-52f915665c66fcbe0e7563608cbf7287&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d10f80809fc56f611edbadcb4809bc4e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-055e2a0c9f60207819211360d38e04f8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5de833b12d9eff458c614eff446c0d4b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1507&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1507 pertains to voidable marriages stemming from duress influencing consent."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-fc29664ee0997602190bcc550d1eddec</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 831&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 831 explains that the extinction of an agency cannot be used against a third party acting in good faith unless they are knowingly negligent of the change."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-e5738a6d02b9e258a742c992fef4b611</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1013&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1013 categorizes partnerships into ordinary, limited partnerships, and limited companies."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-b004bfce3d731fd6bae3b797ccb93662</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 688&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 688 allows a surety to request that a creditor first attempt to collect from the debtor unless certain conditions apply."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-5806a4ac5edf0880beed390e35f10ef7</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;COMMITTEE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Committee refers to the group of at least three persons responsible for managing the foundation's activities according to its regulations and the law."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-46940167ee3908fb358c9a82647ea322</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;PARENTAL POWER&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Parental Power refers to the authority granted to parents or guardians to make decisions and exercise control over various aspects of a child's life."&lt;SEP&gt;"Parental Power refers to the legal authority given to parents or guardians over their minor children, including the management of the child’s property and decision-making in the child's best interests."&lt;SEP&gt;"Parental Power refers to the legal rights and responsibilities of a parent over their child, which can be challenged or modified through court judgments."&lt;SEP&gt;"Parental Power refers to the legal rights and responsibilities parents have over their minor children, including making decisions for their well-being."&lt;SEP&gt;"Parental Power refers to the legal rights and responsibilities that parents have towards their child, including decisions about the child's well-being and education."&lt;SEP&gt;"Parental Power refers to the rights and duties exercised over a ward, similar to those of a parent, detailed in relevant legal sections."&lt;SEP&gt;"Parental power refers to the legal rights and responsibilities held by parents over their minor children, including decision-making regarding their welfare and property."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-a0818329731c6e20f0c0c43a0133253c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-140da0bea780fb9ec8b35168f6556b93&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c8c3be6aeb4b1e7e1a17d53346a1d923&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e6503e3e2e955a071268b1be787bc7d1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d10f80809fc56f611edbadcb4809bc4e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9926eb44610bf5182e4fad6451742c28&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4c5aad3770b3111c6e3b4171b1b6cb5c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1458 PARAGRAPH ONE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1458 paragraph one addresses the rights acquired through marriage prior to its nullification."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-fc29664ee0997602190bcc550d1eddec</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 832&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 832 provides that a principal can demand the return of any written authority once an agency ceases to exist."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-e5738a6d02b9e258a742c992fef4b611</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1014&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1014 mandates the establishment of offices for registering partnerships and companies per the Minister's regulations."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-b004bfce3d731fd6bae3b797ccb93662</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;REAL SECURITY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Real Security is the collateral owned by the debtor that must be used to satisfy the obligation before the surety is called upon."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-5806a4ac5edf0880beed390e35f10ef7</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;PRINCIPAL OFFICE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Principal Office is the main location where the foundation or association's administration and official activities are concentrated."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-46940167ee3908fb358c9a82647ea322</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;BONDS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Bonds are financial instruments in which a guardian may invest the ward's funds, including those issued or guaranteed by the Thai Government."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-d10f80809fc56f611edbadcb4809bc4e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1499/1&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1499/1 mandates that an agreement regarding parental power and maintenance for children from void marriages must be in written form or decided by the court."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-fc29664ee0997602190bcc550d1eddec</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;COMMISSION AGENCY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A commission agency involves a commission agent engaging in business transactions like buying or selling on behalf of a principal, covering rules for remuneration and performance responsibilities."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-e5738a6d02b9e258a742c992fef4b611</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1015&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1015 ensures that registered partnerships or companies are recognized as juristic persons distinct from their members."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-b004bfce3d731fd6bae3b797ccb93662</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 693&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 693 grants the surety a right of recourse for losses suffered after fulfilling the debtor's obligation."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-5806a4ac5edf0880beed390e35f10ef7</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;BRANCH OFFICES&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Branch Offices are additional locations apart from the principal office where the foundation or association may conduct its activities."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-46940167ee3908fb358c9a82647ea322</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;BANK&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A Bank can be an institution where a guardian is allowed to make fixed deposits of the ward's funds."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-d10f80809fc56f611edbadcb4809bc4e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1503&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1503 provides conditions under which an application can be made to the court for marriage cancellation, particularly in cases of voidability."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-fc29664ee0997602190bcc550d1eddec</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 833&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 833 describes the role of a commission agent and the nature of transactions undertaken on behalf of a principal."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-e5738a6d02b9e258a742c992fef4b611</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1016&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1016 requires registration at the principal Registration Office and any amendments to be filed at the same location."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-b004bfce3d731fd6bae3b797ccb93662</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 689&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 689 specifies conditions under which a creditor must first seek execution from the debtor's property before demanding performance from the surety."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-5806a4ac5edf0880beed390e35f10ef7</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;COMMITTEE OF THE FOUNDATION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Committee of the Foundation is responsible for overseeing the management and operations according to the foundation's regulations."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-46940167ee3908fb358c9a82647ea322</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;DEATH OF THE WARD&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Death of the Ward is an event that terminates the guardianship relationship."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-d10f80809fc56f611edbadcb4809bc4e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1504&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1504 outlines the rights of interested persons to apply for marriage cancellation based on voidability, excluding parents or guardians who gave consent."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-fc29664ee0997602190bcc550d1eddec</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 834&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 834 covers the entitlement of a commission agent to receive usual remuneration for transactions concluded on behalf of a principal."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-e5738a6d02b9e258a742c992fef4b611</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1017&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1017 dictates registration timelines for events occurring internationally, from notification reception at the registration or publication site."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-b004bfce3d731fd6bae3b797ccb93662</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 696&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 696 states that if the surety fulfills the obligation without notifying the debtor, the surety loses recourse against the debtor unless compensated for undue enrichment."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-5806a4ac5edf0880beed390e35f10ef7</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;APPLICANT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Applicant is the individual or group who submits a formal request for registering a foundation, responsible for providing necessary documents."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-46940167ee3908fb358c9a82647ea322</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1018&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1018 imposes fees for registration services as determined by the competent Minister's regulations."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-b004bfce3d731fd6bae3b797ccb93662</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SURETY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A Surety is a person who guarantees the performance of an obligation by the debtor and may be affected by prescription."&lt;SEP&gt;"Surety refers to a guarantee or assurance, often involving a surety or guarantor who ensures the fulfillment of an obligation by a debtor."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Surety is the person or entity in a suretyship contract that promises to satisfy the debtor's obligation if the debtor defaults."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-d45ed62b6b0bfc44f2c1ae4fe430c9c0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5806a4ac5edf0880beed390e35f10ef7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5f23a6639e72b69e61fefaaa9a0d77c3</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;JURISTIC PERSON&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A Juristic Person is a legal entity with rights and obligations, created when a foundation is authorized based on a will."&lt;SEP&gt;"A Juristic Person is a legal entity, such as a corporation, that may be appointed as a Controller of Property if they have full capacity."&lt;SEP&gt;"A juristic person is a legal entity recognized by law as having rights and responsibilities, which can receive an association's remaining assets under certain conditions."&lt;SEP&gt;"A juristic person is a legal entity recognized by law, such as an association, which has specific rights and responsibilities."&lt;SEP&gt;"A juristic person is a legal entity that, according to this text, has rights and responsibilities defined by law, and must have representatives for acting on its behalf."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-182a2b244fdc4ad235c762ab46288dca&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-91e6c9c6ece02f3027772a9577efdcd4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a2aa959400bcd6663682a867aebf2801&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-553b3730ac4ba8b3212a7d230dbc31ad&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e0099557ffbf92309faf8ac19f118ba2</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 835&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 835 applies the general provisions of agency law to commission agency unless explicitly contradicted by this chapter's rules."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-e5738a6d02b9e258a742c992fef4b611</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SUPERFICIARY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Superficiary is the person granted the right of superficies, allowing them to own buildings, structures, or plantations upon or under the land."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-d6852cd5ceee34402f3999c849ff9c9f</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE STATE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The State is a governmental institution in Thailand, referred to in the context of being affected by wrongful acts of officials according to the Criminal Code."&lt;SEP&gt;"The State is the governing body with authority over unclaimed and ownerless property as per specified sections of the legal text."&lt;SEP&gt;"The State refers to the governmental or political organization at a national level that can be affected by wrongful actions performed by officials."&lt;SEP&gt;"The State represents the governmental entity that receives forfeited properties as per court judgments."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-ee7dd29b88d53ea4523197532d9851fe&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-37adf4ae405c50d2a9e02b9fbd91341e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-de71dcf326342843893937651bd927f6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2c753f490ffe4fe92240bb63a93c4481</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;MORTGAGE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A mortgage is a legal agreement in which a property is used as security against a loan or obligation, with specific provisions for enforcement and rights."&lt;SEP&gt;"Mortgage involves legal agreements securing loans against property."&lt;SEP&gt;"Mortgage is a legal agreement by which a bank or creditor lends money at interest in exchange for taking title of the debtor's property, with the condition that the conveyance of title becomes void upon the payment of the debt."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-8db429ff50410ec3964e2dd051739fba&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9926eb44610bf5182e4fad6451742c28&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5f23a6639e72b69e61fefaaa9a0d77c3</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;PARAGRAPH ONE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Paragraph One refers to the section detailing the period of time to be reduced for specific circumstances related to disappearance."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-e0099557ffbf92309faf8ac19f118ba2</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 836&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 836 states that an incapacitated person cannot be a commission agent without proper authorization."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-e5738a6d02b9e258a742c992fef4b611</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1019&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1019 highlights the consequences of incomplete or incorrect registration applications or documents."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-b004bfce3d731fd6bae3b797ccb93662</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;RIGHT OF USUFRUCT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Right of Usufruct is a legal entitlement allowing an individual, the usufructuary, to use and enjoy the benefits of someone else's property for a certain period."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-d6852cd5ceee34402f3999c849ff9c9f</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;TESTATOR&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A Testator is a person who has written and executed a will that is in effect at the time of their death."&lt;SEP&gt;"A Testator is an individual who creates a will to distribute their estate after death."&lt;SEP&gt;"A testator is an individual who has made a will, determining the disposition of their estate upon death."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Testator is an individual who writes and declares their testamentary intentions, often in the presence of witnesses and specific officials."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Testator is the person who creates a will to dispose of their property, potentially including the appointment of a Controller of Property."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-89b8c822a665cc12b23359be3cc927d4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cced3c5fac31674d85b89a0610b1ee09&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6f29560483a94cdf780f52af44990dd1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-96ca137e685d301646809ca5adf41812&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-553b3730ac4ba8b3212a7d230dbc31ad</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;OWNERLESS MOVABLES&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Ownerless movables refer to items not owned by anyone, including abandoned movable objects and wild animals under specific conditions."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-2c753f490ffe4fe92240bb63a93c4481</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;MORTGAGOR&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A mortgagor is a person or entity that assigns property as security to a mortgagee in a mortgage agreement."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-5f23a6639e72b69e61fefaaa9a0d77c3</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;PERIL OF LIFE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Peril of Life refers to risky situations, other than war or vehicle loss, which are considered in determining the period of disappearance."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-e0099557ffbf92309faf8ac19f118ba2</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 837&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 837 clarifies that a commission agent acquires direct rights and duties against other transaction parties but is not liable for their non-performance to the principal unless otherwise agreed."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-e5738a6d02b9e258a742c992fef4b611</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;LAND&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Land is the geographical area owned by a person and can be subject to rights like superficies or usufruct granted to another person."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-d6852cd5ceee34402f3999c849ff9c9f</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;LEGATEE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A Legatee is a person who receives a legacy or inheritance under a will."&lt;SEP&gt;"A Legatee is a person who receives a legacy or property from a Testator through the provisions of a will."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-6f29560483a94cdf780f52af44990dd1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-553b3730ac4ba8b3212a7d230dbc31ad</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;WILD ANIMALS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Wild animals are considered ownerless when free but are not ownerless when in captivity in zoological gardens or enclosed private waters."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-2c753f490ffe4fe92240bb63a93c4481</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;MORTGAGEE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A Mortgagee is a person or entity that holds a mortgage, with rights to enforce claims on mortgaged property."&lt;SEP&gt;"A Mortgagee is a person or financial institution that lends money with property as security, holding a preferential right in the event of default."&lt;SEP&gt;"A mortgagee is a person or entity that receives interest in a property as security for a loan or obligation in a mortgage contract."&lt;SEP&gt;"A mortgagee is an entity or person who lends money to a borrower in exchange for taking a security interest in the borrower's property."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-d45ed62b6b0bfc44f2c1ae4fe430c9c0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e3fe26f521adf40f2978335cdbc054b9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2c01a4f68c167448d4624c0e8d938db0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5f23a6639e72b69e61fefaaa9a0d77c3</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;REVOCATION OF ADJUDICATION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Revocation of Adjudication refers to the process of overturning a previous ruling of disappearance if proven otherwise by the person or interested party."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-e0099557ffbf92309faf8ac19f118ba2</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 838&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 838 indicates scenarios where a commission agent assumes liability for non-performance due to an implied contract or local customs, termed a del credere agent."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-e5738a6d02b9e258a742c992fef4b611</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;BUILDINGS, STRUCTURES OR PLANTATIONS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Buildings, structures, or plantations are physical entities that the superficiary may have rights over through superficies."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-d6852cd5ceee34402f3999c849ff9c9f</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1646-1658&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"These sections outline general provisions and forms related to wills in the Thailand Civil Code."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-6f29560483a94cdf780f52af44990dd1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;OBLIGATION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"An Obligation is a legal duty bound by a contract or law, requiring parties to perform certain acts or make payments."&lt;SEP&gt;"An Obligation is a legal duty that requires a party to perform an action or settle a debt, often shared in joint debtor situations."&lt;SEP&gt;"An obligation is a legal or contractual duty imposed on the debtor to perform an act or provide a service or payment to a creditor."&lt;SEP&gt;"An obligation refers to a legal or financial duty that a debtor must perform for a creditor, often secured by agreements like suretyship or mortgage."&lt;SEP&gt;"An obligation refers to the binding commitment arising from a juristic act, which might be performed, demanded, or secured in various ways."&lt;SEP&gt;"Obligation is a legal duty owed by the debtor to the creditor, which can be secured by retaining property."&lt;SEP&gt;"Obligation is the duty or debt that the debtor is required to fulfill under the terms of a pledge or agency agreement."&lt;SEP&gt;"Obligation is the responsibility or duty that the debtor has towards the creditor, requiring certain acts or payments."&lt;SEP&gt;"Obligation refers to a legal duty that binds a partnership or partner to adhere to specific terms, such as debt repayment or the performance of certain acts."&lt;SEP&gt;"Obligation refers to a legal or binding duty or responsibility that an individual or organization must fulfill."&lt;SEP&gt;"Obligation refers to the duty owed by the debtor, which can be secured by a surety and involves legal commitments."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-c35036965b446b68b1f64bc55f989965&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-30e7eef2c9f266924b324154eca432d3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ac44eff8208c6427b97025d89925979e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5f23a6639e72b69e61fefaaa9a0d77c3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5806a4ac5edf0880beed390e35f10ef7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-aac23a1f6cf12366451f6be3ff0a3ed2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d82b5d0a885fc8b96ea11f873f6f0c0a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b3971476de4ec8b22a6311d4e55caca0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8ced30eeca0d6aa10b4e6af82a8bb160&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6cd9b0e3cf4adfb36e41fca038140314&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e7fb2f4e3c8f089ed58aad2cf781f6f9</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;CODE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Code refers to the legal framework or set of laws under which juristic persons and their rights and duties are defined."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-e0099557ffbf92309faf8ac19f118ba2</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 839&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 839 discusses consequences when a commission agent conducts a transaction at different prices than instructed by the principal."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-e5738a6d02b9e258a742c992fef4b611</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;FINDER OF LOST PROPERTY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A finder of lost property is a person who discovers an ownerless item and is subject to legal obligations to return it and may receive a reward."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-2c753f490ffe4fe92240bb63a93c4481</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;DESCENDANT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A Descendant is a person who is a legitimate heir, eligible for inheritance under certain conditions outlined in the civil code."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-6f29560483a94cdf780f52af44990dd1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 700&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 700 refers to a legal statute outlining the liabilities of a surety when an extension of time is granted to a debtor."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-5f23a6639e72b69e61fefaaa9a0d77c3</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;CONSTITUTIVE ACT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Constitutive Act refers to the official document or regulation that establishes the formation and powers of a juristic person."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-e0099557ffbf92309faf8ac19f118ba2</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 840&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 840 requires commission agents to pass any unanticipated financial gains on to the principal."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-e5738a6d02b9e258a742c992fef4b611</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;ACQUISITION OF OWNERSHIP&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The process described in which a person acquires ownership of a previously ownerless movable by means of occupation, under lawful conditions."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-2c753f490ffe4fe92240bb63a93c4481</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;ESTATE ADMINISTRATOR&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"An Estate Administrator is an individual appointed by the deceased, or by the benefactors, to manage the distribution of the estate and arrange the funeral."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-6f29560483a94cdf780f52af44990dd1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 701&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 701 is a legal provision allowing the surety to perform the obligation towards the creditor when the obligation is due."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-5f23a6639e72b69e61fefaaa9a0d77c3</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;ASSOCIATION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"An Association is a type of juristic person created for collective activity without profit-sharing, requiring registration under this Code."&lt;SEP&gt;"An association is a collective entity created for conducting activities continuously and collectively by persons, not sharing profits or incomes. It must have regulations and be registered according to legal provisions."&lt;SEP&gt;"An association is an organization that operates within specific regulations, focusing on the collective conduct of its members."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-91e6c9c6ece02f3027772a9577efdcd4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e0099557ffbf92309faf8ac19f118ba2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-46940167ee3908fb358c9a82647ea322</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 841&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 841 mandates that a commission agent must promptly report transaction details to the principal after execution."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-e5738a6d02b9e258a742c992fef4b611</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1318&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A section in the legal text that discusses the conditions under which a person can acquire ownership of an ownerless movable."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-2c753f490ffe4fe92240bb63a93c4481</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;INHERITANCE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Inheritance refers to the assets passed down to heirs according to the stipulations in a will or by statutory laws in the absence of a will."&lt;SEP&gt;"Inheritance refers to the legal right to receive property or titles as a result of the legal recognition of lineage."&lt;SEP&gt;"Inheritance refers to the process of transferring property or titles after the death of an individual, often involving legal stipulations particularly regarding minors."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9926eb44610bf5182e4fad6451742c28&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6f29560483a94cdf780f52af44990dd1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d9947bc7fb3e59afe960708bcf533e3c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 702&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 702 defines the concept and legal framework of a mortgage as a contract for securing an obligation without transferring possession."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-5f23a6639e72b69e61fefaaa9a0d77c3</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot; OBLIGATIONS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Obligations are legal commitments where individuals or entities are required to perform certain actions or fulfill certain duties, often in the context of contracts or debts."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-0ffc320382a3c1523b402789d6bfce44</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 842&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 842 discusses applying deposit law provisions to commission agents holding entrusted property with exceptional disposal provisions in critical situations."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-e5738a6d02b9e258a742c992fef4b611</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1320&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A section that specifies the conditions under which wild animals are regarded as ownerless or owned."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-2c753f490ffe4fe92240bb63a93c4481</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;RENOUNCER&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A Renouncer is a person who gives up their right to inherit, but may still represent the deceased in specific inheritance matters involving another party."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-6f29560483a94cdf780f52af44990dd1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;FLOATING HOUSES&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Floating houses refer to movable properties that can be registered and mortgaged as security for obligations, classified under mortgagable movables."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-5f23a6639e72b69e61fefaaa9a0d77c3</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;GENERAL PREFERENTIAL RIGHT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"General preferential rights denote a non-specific rank of precedence in receiving benefits from a debtor's property, applicable under specific legal conditions and regulations."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-0ffc320382a3c1523b402789d6bfce44</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 843&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 843 permits a commission agent to be the buyer or seller of entrusted property under certain exchange conditions, subject to principal approval."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-e5738a6d02b9e258a742c992fef4b611</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1323&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A section outlining the obligations of a person who finds lost property, including delivery to the owner or police."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-2c753f490ffe4fe92240bb63a93c4481</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;EXPENSES FOR THE COMMON BENEFIT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"These are expenses incurred for preserving, liquidating, or distributing the debtor's property that benefit all creditors, giving rise to a preferential right."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-bac2de5ec87beec114bb4549e917cb4e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SHIPS OF FIVE TONS AND OVER&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"This refers to a type of movable property that can be registered and mortgaged according to legal provisions for securing obligations."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-5f23a6639e72b69e61fefaaa9a0d77c3</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;FIRST RANK&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The first rank refers to the highest level of priority given to certain preferential rights, allowing those rights to be exercised before others."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-0ffc320382a3c1523b402789d6bfce44</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 844&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 844 affirms that transactions by a commission agent have the same validity between principal and agent as directly conducted ones."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-e5738a6d02b9e258a742c992fef4b611</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;ANTIQUE OBJECTS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Antique objects are items of significant age and value that, if unclaimed, have ownership vested in the State, with a reward for the finder."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-2c753f490ffe4fe92240bb63a93c4481</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;FUNERAL EXPENSES&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Funeral expenses are costs associated with the burial of the debtor that are eligible for preferential rights according to the debtor's station in life."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-bac2de5ec87beec114bb4549e917cb4e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;BEAST OF BURDEN&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Beast of burden is considered a type of movable property that can be registered and mortgaged for securing obligations."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-5f23a6639e72b69e61fefaaa9a0d77c3</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECOND RANK&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The second rank indicates a level of priority that follows the first rank in the order of preferential rights, affecting the exercise of those rights."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-0ffc320382a3c1523b402789d6bfce44</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;TITLE XVI&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Title XVI is a legal section dealing with brokerage, outlining the responsibilities and remuneration conditions for brokers."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-e5738a6d02b9e258a742c992fef4b611</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;POLICE OR COMPETENT OFFICIAL&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Authorities to whom a finder of lost property must report or deliver items, ensuring lawful handling and rewards."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-2c753f490ffe4fe92240bb63a93c4481</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;OWNERSHIP BY OCCUPATION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A legal principle allowing a person to claim ownership of a movable object through occupation, if not prohibited by law."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-2c753f490ffe4fe92240bb63a93c4481</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;TAXES AND DUTIES&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Taxes and duties refer to public charges like property taxes which have preferential rights in debt recovery."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-bac2de5ec87beec114bb4549e917cb4e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;IMMOVABLES&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Immovables refer to properties that are fixed and can be mortgaged, such as land or buildings, as security for an obligation."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-5f23a6639e72b69e61fefaaa9a0d77c3</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THIRD RANK&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The third rank represents the third level of priority in the hierarchy of preferential rights, affecting how rights are exercised against others."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-0ffc320382a3c1523b402789d6bfce44</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 845&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 845 sets the conditions under which a broker is owed remuneration for facilitating contract opportunities, dependent on contract completion."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-e5738a6d02b9e258a742c992fef4b611</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;DOCUMENT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Document refers to the legal record that embodies the obligation between the debtor and creditor."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-c35036965b446b68b1f64bc55f989965</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;EMPLOYEE ENTITLEMENTS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Compensation owed to an employee, such as wages for services rendered to the debtor, which are prioritized under preferential rights."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-bac2de5ec87beec114bb4549e917cb4e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 703&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 703 explains which kinds of properties, both immovable and certain movable, are eligible for mortgage."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-5f23a6639e72b69e61fefaaa9a0d77c3</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;PRESERVATION OF AN IMMOVABLE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Preservation of an immovable refers to actions taken to maintain or protect real estate property, which can establish preferential rights if registered promptly."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-0ffc320382a3c1523b402789d6bfce44</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 846&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 846 addresses the implied agreement of broker remuneration based on business circumstances and outlines reimbursement conditions."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 846 details the conditions under which a broker's remuneration is impliedly agreed upon, based on the nature of the business entrusted."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-e5738a6d02b9e258a742c992fef4b611&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b004bfce3d731fd6bae3b797ccb93662</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;BANKRUPTCY PROCEEDINGS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Bankruptcy Proceedings are legal processes initiated when a debtor cannot meet financial obligations, affecting their rights and obligations."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-c35036965b446b68b1f64bc55f989965</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SUPPLIES OF DAILY NECESSARIES&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Essential goods like food, drink, and fuel necessary for the debtor’s living, subject to preferential rights up to six months."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-bac2de5ec87beec114bb4549e917cb4e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 704&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 704 mandates that a mortgage contract must specify the property designated as security for an obligation."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-5f23a6639e72b69e61fefaaa9a0d77c3</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;AGRICULTURAL SERVICES&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Agricultural services involve various tasks or services provided to support farming activities, which may hold preferential rights when related to property."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-0ffc320382a3c1523b402789d6bfce44</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;MINISTER OF INTERIOR&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Minister of Interior is an official responsible for deciding appeals related to the refusal of foundation registration."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Minister of Interior is the official who decides appeals against orders of refusal for registration made by the Registrar, and whose decision is final."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-91e6c9c6ece02f3027772a9577efdcd4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-46940167ee3908fb358c9a82647ea322</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;BUDDHIST MONK&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A Buddhist monk is a person who practices Buddhism in a monastic context and is subject to specific inheritance rules."&lt;SEP&gt;"A religious figure associated with Buddhism, recognized by specific symbols and attire, whose impersonation is penalized under Thai law."&lt;SEP&gt;"Buddhist Monk denotes a religious figure within Buddhism, whose attire and symbols are protected from misrepresentation under specific legal sections."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-1429bffff14b8577c8748fc8f14a6678&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6fd5b0ac67c6f4aafc6e1ef0e7ce2a77&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c2ac78f2ab241f4845c5c94a44c0ffb6</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;MOVABLES&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Movables are personal property items that can be subject to special preferential rights based on obligations like hiring or lodging."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-bac2de5ec87beec114bb4549e917cb4e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 705&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 705 restricts the act of mortgaging a property to its current owner at the time of the agreement."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-5f23a6639e72b69e61fefaaa9a0d77c3</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SUPPLIER OF SEEDS OR MANURE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A supplier of seeds or manure provides agricultural inputs essential for planting and farming, and may have specific preferential rights related to such supplies."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-0ffc320382a3c1523b402789d6bfce44</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 78&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 78 outlines the conditions under which the punishment for an offender may be reduced due to extenuating circumstances."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 78 outlines the requirements for creating an association for continuous and collective activities without profit-sharing, necessitating proper regulations and registration."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-7770756870427eb344039070455f889c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-91e6c9c6ece02f3027772a9577efdcd4</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;MONASTERY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A monastery is a building or complex where monks live and practice their religious duties, which can inherit property from monks under certain conditions."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-c2ac78f2ab241f4845c5c94a44c0ffb6</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 709&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 709 allows a person to mortgage their property as security for another's obligation."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-5f23a6639e72b69e61fefaaa9a0d77c3</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SALES OF IMMOVABLE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Sales of immovable refer to transactions involving real estate properties, where preferential rights may depend on the registration and completion of the sale contract."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-0ffc320382a3c1523b402789d6bfce44</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 79&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 79 specifies the necessary particulars required in the regulations of an association, including name, objective, and management rules."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 79 states that if a person alleged to have committed an offence pays the maximum fine before evidence is submitted in court, the case will be dismissed."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-7770756870427eb344039070455f889c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-91e6c9c6ece02f3027772a9577efdcd4</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 247&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 247 of the legal code covers circumstances under which the holder of a right of retention may incur necessary expenses regarding retained property and the obligation of the owner to reimburse such expenses."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-bac2de5ec87beec114bb4549e917cb4e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;ILLEGITIMATE CHILD&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"An illegitimate child is a child born to parents who are not legally married to each other but can be legitimized and have rights to inheritance."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-c2ac78f2ab241f4845c5c94a44c0ffb6</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 714&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 714 requires that a mortgage contract must be written and registered with an official authority."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-5f23a6639e72b69e61fefaaa9a0d77c3</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;JOINT DEBTORS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Joint Debtors are parties who are collectively responsible for the fulfillment of an obligation or debt."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-aac23a1f6cf12366451f6be3ff0a3ed2</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 81&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 81 describes the procedure for filing an application for the registration of an association, including required documents and member details."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-91e6c9c6ece02f3027772a9577efdcd4</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 248&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 248 outlines the conditions under which the exercise of a right of retention does not prevent the running of prescription against the obligation involved."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-bac2de5ec87beec114bb4549e917cb4e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;LEGITIMIZED CHILD&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A legitimized child is an illegitimate child who has been formally recognized by the father, gaining rights similar to legitimate children including inheritance."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-c2ac78f2ab241f4845c5c94a44c0ffb6</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE GUARDIAN&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Guardian is an individual tasked with the responsibility of managing and making important decisions for a ward who is not yet sui juris."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-cb6f943ed567718e3b0963e9f80b3c0b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;JOINT CREDITORS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Joint Creditors are parties entitled to demand a performance, each has the right to the entire performance, but the debtor is bound to fulfill it only once."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-aac23a1f6cf12366451f6be3ff0a3ed2</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 82&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 82 details the conditions under which the Registrar issues a certificate of registration to an association, and the process of corrections if necessary."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-91e6c9c6ece02f3027772a9577efdcd4</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 249&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 249 allows a debtor to claim the extinction of the right of retention by providing appropriate security."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-bac2de5ec87beec114bb4549e917cb4e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;DECEASED&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The deceased is the person who has died, with their estate being subject to division among heirs according to law."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-c2ac78f2ab241f4845c5c94a44c0ffb6</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE WARD&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Ward is an individual under the legal protection and management of a guardian until reaching legal maturity or discretion."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-cb6f943ed567718e3b0963e9f80b3c0b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;TRANSFER OF CLAIMS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Transfer of Claims refers to the legal act of transferring a claim or right from one party to another, ensuring the transferee gains all associated rights."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-aac23a1f6cf12366451f6be3ff0a3ed2</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 83&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 83 declares that an association, once registered, becomes a juristic person."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-91e6c9c6ece02f3027772a9577efdcd4</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 250&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 250 describes how a right of retention is extinguished upon the loss of possession of the property, with exceptions."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-bac2de5ec87beec114bb4549e917cb4e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;PARENTS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Parents are individuals who may be financially responsible for harm caused by their child under certain legal stipulations."&lt;SEP&gt;"Parents are the mother and father of a person, who are statutory heirs and have rights to inheritance under certain conditions."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-7770756870427eb344039070455f889c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c2ac78f2ab241f4845c5c94a44c0ffb6</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1598/5&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1598/5 outlines the responsibilities and consultation requirements of the guardian during important transactions with the ward."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-cb6f943ed567718e3b0963e9f80b3c0b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 292 TO 299&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"These sections refer to legal provisions regarding the rights and obligations of joint debtors and creditors, as well as procedures related to claims."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-aac23a1f6cf12366451f6be3ff0a3ed2</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 84&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 84 covers the process for making alterations to the regulations of an association and the requirement for registration of such changes."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-91e6c9c6ece02f3027772a9577efdcd4</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 251&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 251 provides a holder of a preferential right the ability to receive performance of an obligation in preference to other creditors, as per legal provisions."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-bac2de5ec87beec114bb4549e917cb4e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 253&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 253 defines the general preferential rights granted to a person in whose favor an obligation exists based on common benefit, funeral expenses, taxes, and employee entitlements."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-bac2de5ec87beec114bb4549e917cb4e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;BROTHERS AND SISTERS OF FULL BLOOD&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Brothers and sisters of full blood share both parents with a person and can be statutory heirs."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-c2ac78f2ab241f4845c5c94a44c0ffb6</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1598/6&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1598/6 specifies the conditions under which guardianship is terminated, such as the ward's death or becoming sui juris."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-cb6f943ed567718e3b0963e9f80b3c0b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;NOTICE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A Notice is a formal written communication conveying important information or requests, such as calls on shares or warnings of forfeiture, to stakeholders in a company."&lt;SEP&gt;"Notice refers to a formal notification given to inform a party about a transfer of obligation or a related legal action."&lt;SEP&gt;"Notice refers to the formal communication required to inform parties about legal matters such as transfers of claims or changes in obligations."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-6cd9b0e3cf4adfb36e41fca038140314&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-aac23a1f6cf12366451f6be3ff0a3ed2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4b333b466a8e220c02cd14e77e8fb935</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 85&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 85 outlines the process for appointing new directors to an association and the need for registering these changes at the Registrar."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-91e6c9c6ece02f3027772a9577efdcd4</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 254&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 254 explains the preferential rights on account of expenses incurred for the common benefit of all creditors, concerning the preservation, liquidation, or distribution of a debtor's property."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-bac2de5ec87beec114bb4549e917cb4e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;BROTHERS AND SISTERS OF HALF BLOOD&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Brothers and sisters of half blood share one parent with a person, and can be statutory heirs under specified conditions."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-c2ac78f2ab241f4845c5c94a44c0ffb6</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1598/7&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1598/7 details the conditions under which the guardian's functions are terminated, including death, resignation, incompetency, and court revocation."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-cb6f943ed567718e3b0963e9f80b3c0b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;MERGER OF THE CLAIM IN DEBT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"This event occurs when a debt or obligation is combined with a claim, affecting the legal rights and obligations of the involved parties."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-aac23a1f6cf12366451f6be3ff0a3ed2</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1603&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1603 refers to legal provisions under the Civil and Commercial Code that discuss how an estate devolves on heirs by statutory right or by will."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-a7a64e6f6e939634750f7cc32da6d781</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 255&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 255 details the preferential rights associated with funeral expenses in alignment with the social status of the debtor."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-bac2de5ec87beec114bb4549e917cb4e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;GRANDPARENTS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Grandparents are the parents of a person's parents, included as potential statutory heirs."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-c2ac78f2ab241f4845c5c94a44c0ffb6</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1598/8&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1598/8 provides grounds for the court to discharge a guardian, including failure to perform duties, gross negligence, and misconduct."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-cb6f943ed567718e3b0963e9f80b3c0b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;JUDICIAL ATTACHMENT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Judicial Attachment is a legal process that seizes a debtor's property to secure a claim, relevant in determining if a claim is transferable."&lt;SEP&gt;"Judicial Attachment is a legal seizure of assets or claims subject to a court order, barring them from being set off against other obligations."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-aac23a1f6cf12366451f6be3ff0a3ed2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8ced30eeca0d6aa10b4e6af82a8bb160</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1604&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1604 outlines the eligibility for a natural person to be an heir, such as having personality at the time of death of the de cuius or capability of rights."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-a7a64e6f6e939634750f7cc32da6d781</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 256&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 256 outlines preferential rights related to taxes and local rates due by the debtor for the current and preceding years."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-bac2de5ec87beec114bb4549e917cb4e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;UNCLES AND AUNTS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Uncles and aunts are the siblings of a person's parents, who may be considered as statutory heirs."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-c2ac78f2ab241f4845c5c94a44c0ffb6</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1598/9&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1598/9 allows for an application for the discharge of a guardian by the ward, a relative, or the Public Prosecutor."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-cb6f943ed567718e3b0963e9f80b3c0b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;COMPULSORY EXECUTION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Compulsory Execution is a legal proceeding to enforce a court judgment, affecting the rights related to transferred claims."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-aac23a1f6cf12366451f6be3ff0a3ed2</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1605&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1605 details the conditions under which an heir is excluded from succession if they fraudulently or knowingly prejudice other heirs."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-a7a64e6f6e939634750f7cc32da6d781</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 257&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 257 defines preferential rights concerning money owed to employees for services rendered, ensuring their entitlements are prioritized."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-bac2de5ec87beec114bb4549e917cb4e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;DIVISION PER STIRPES&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Division per stirpes is an inheritance method where descendants inherit a deceased ancestor's share if the intermediary heir is deceased."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-c2ac78f2ab241f4845c5c94a44c0ffb6</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1598/10&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1598/10 permits the appointment of a temporary manager of the ward's property while a discharge application is pending."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-cb6f943ed567718e3b0963e9f80b3c0b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SURETYSHIP&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Suretyship is a contractual agreement where a third party, known as the surety, assures a creditor that they will fulfill an obligation if the primary debtor fails to perform."&lt;SEP&gt;"Suretyship is a contractual arrangement where a third party guarantees the performance or obligations of a debtor to a creditor."&lt;SEP&gt;"Suretyship is a legal contract where a third party, known as the surety, agrees to fulfill a debtor's obligation if the debtor fails to do so."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-cc95f23cfbd6112c8327703d8101a010&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5806a4ac5edf0880beed390e35f10ef7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-aac23a1f6cf12366451f6be3ff0a3ed2</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1606&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1606 lists those who are excluded from succession due to unworthy actions, such as causing death or falsifying information affecting succession."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-a7a64e6f6e939634750f7cc32da6d781</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 258&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 258 outlines legal penalties related to the misuse of marked items, specifically tickets disposed to public people."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 258 pertains to preferential rights for supplies of daily necessaries, including essential living provisions, within six months."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-0821966abff87f794597de47538cc67e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bac2de5ec87beec114bb4549e917cb4e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1621&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1621 details the rights of statutory heirs to inherit portions of an estate not disposed of by a will."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-c2ac78f2ab241f4845c5c94a44c0ffb6</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1598/11&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1598/11 mandates the transfer and accounting of the ward's property by the guardian or their heir upon termination of guardianship."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-cb6f943ed567718e3b0963e9f80b3c0b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;DOMAINE PUBLIC&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Domaine Public is a category of property that forms part of the State's national estate, protected from alienation or prescription."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-e69f756c60167e54cbfb8769b0011720</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1607&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1607 describes the personal effects of exclusion from succession, where descendants succeed as if the excluded heir were dead."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-a7a64e6f6e939634750f7cc32da6d781</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 259&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 259 covers special preferential rights in movables related to obligations like hiring, lodging, carriage, preservation, sales, and supplies."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 259 specifies penalties for offences relating to misused tickets offered to the public."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-0821966abff87f794597de47538cc67e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bac2de5ec87beec114bb4549e917cb4e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1622&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1622 specifies that a Buddhist monk cannot claim inheritance as a statutory heir unless they leave the monkhood and enforce their claim in a specified period."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-c2ac78f2ab241f4845c5c94a44c0ffb6</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1580 AND SECTION 1581&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Sections 1580 and 1581 are mentioned as applicable with modifications to the guardianship process."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-cb6f943ed567718e3b0963e9f80b3c0b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SPECIAL LAW OR ROYAL DECREE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Special Law or Royal Decree refers to the legal mechanisms through which properties in the public domain may be transferred or altered."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-e69f756c60167e54cbfb8769b0011720</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1608&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1608 pertains to the disinheritance of heirs by an express declaration of intention through a will or deposited writing."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-a7a64e6f6e939634750f7cc32da6d781</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 260&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 260 details preferential rights concerning the hiring of immovable property and the obligations that arise from such relations."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 260 discusses the punishment for dealing with tickets obtained through forgery or other illegal means."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-0821966abff87f794597de47538cc67e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bac2de5ec87beec114bb4549e917cb4e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1598/12&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1598/12 discusses the payment of interest on money mismanaged by either the guardian or the ward."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-cb6f943ed567718e3b0963e9f80b3c0b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;RIPARIAN OWNER&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Riparian Owner is the individual who owns land adjacent to waterways and acquires land formed by alluvion."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-e69f756c60167e54cbfb8769b0011720</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1609&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1609 allows for the revocation of a declaration of disinheritance and specifies how such revocation can be made."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-a7a64e6f6e939634750f7cc32da6d781</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1623&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1623 addresses the property of Buddhist monks acquired during monkhood, which becomes the property of the monastery upon their death unless disposed of by will."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-c2ac78f2ab241f4845c5c94a44c0ffb6</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 261&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 261 addresses penalties for creating or possessing devices for forging or altering documents or tickets."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 261 explains the rights of a letter in respect of movables brought onto hired land or property by the hirer."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-0821966abff87f794597de47538cc67e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bac2de5ec87beec114bb4549e917cb4e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1598/13&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1598/13 outlines the ward's preferential right over the guardian's property for obligations owed."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-cb6f943ed567718e3b0963e9f80b3c0b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;CONSTRUCTOR&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Constructor is an individual who builds on another's land, subject to certain legal conditions, depending on whether the construction was made in good or bad faith."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-e69f756c60167e54cbfb8769b0011720</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1610&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1610 addresses the appointment of a guardian, custodian, or curator for minors or individuals of unsound mind who inherit an estate."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-a7a64e6f6e939634750f7cc32da6d781</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1624&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1624 explains that property belonging to a person before entering the monkhood shall devolve to statutory heirs and not transfer to the monastery."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-c2ac78f2ab241f4845c5c94a44c0ffb6</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 262&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 262 provides information about reduced penalties for offences involving foreign government stamps."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 262 states that preferential rights extend to movables brought by a transferee or sub-hirer into hired property."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-0821966abff87f794597de47538cc67e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bac2de5ec87beec114bb4549e917cb4e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1598/14&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1598/14 details conditions under which a guardian may receive remuneration, including stipulations in a will or court determination."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-cb6f943ed567718e3b0963e9f80b3c0b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;LANDOWNER&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Landowner is the rightful owner of a piece of land and may engage in legal proceedings concerning constructions made on their land."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-e69f756c60167e54cbfb8769b0011720</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;NATURAL PERSON&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A natural person refers to a human being with the ability to have legal rights and obligations, potentially serving as an heir."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-a7a64e6f6e939634750f7cc32da6d781</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1625&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1625 outlines the property liquidation and distribution process between a deceased person and their surviving spouse."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-c2ac78f2ab241f4845c5c94a44c0ffb6</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1626&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1626 describes the division of an estate among statutory heirs after compliance with Section 1625, focusing on the class and degree of heirs."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-c2ac78f2ab241f4845c5c94a44c0ffb6</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 263&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 263 concerns preferential rights of the letter in cases of general liquidation of hirer's property, specifying rent and damages obligations."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 263 deals with the compounding of offences and penalties for multiple offences under related sections."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-0821966abff87f794597de47538cc67e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bac2de5ec87beec114bb4549e917cb4e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1598/15&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1598/15 discusses rights and duties when a spouse is appointed guardian of an incompetent spouse, applied with modifications."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-cb6f943ed567718e3b0963e9f80b3c0b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;GOOD FAITH CONSTRUCTION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Good Faith Construction refers to buildings erected by a constructor who mistakenly believes they have the right to build on another's land, subject to provisions for compensation."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-e69f756c60167e54cbfb8769b0011720</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;PERSONALITY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Personality in this context refers to the legal recognition of a person's capacity to have rights and duties, relevant at the time of inheritance proceedings."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-a7a64e6f6e939634750f7cc32da6d781</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1627&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1627 establishes that illegitimate children legitimated by their father and adopted children are recognized as descendants for inheritance purposes."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-c2ac78f2ab241f4845c5c94a44c0ffb6</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 264&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 264 covers the crime of forging documents and the associated penalties."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 264 limits the letter's preferential rights to claims not covered by security money."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-0821966abff87f794597de47538cc67e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bac2de5ec87beec114bb4549e917cb4e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1598/16&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1598/16 lays out the management powers over personal and common marital property by a spouse appointed as guardian."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-cb6f943ed567718e3b0963e9f80b3c0b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;BAD FAITH CONSTRUCTION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Bad Faith Construction refers to buildings constructed with knowledge that the land does not belong to the constructor, requiring restitution or removal at the constructor's expense."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-e69f756c60167e54cbfb8769b0011720</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;UNSOUND MIND&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A condition where a person is incapable of managing their affairs due to mental incapacity, affecting their eligibility in inheritance matters."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-a7a64e6f6e939634750f7cc32da6d781</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1628&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1628 states that spouses living apart under desertion or separation still retain their inheritance rights unless legally divorced."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-c2ac78f2ab241f4845c5c94a44c0ffb6</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 265&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 265 discusses preferential rights for dues to lodging proprietors for services rendered."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 265 specifies penalties for forging official or right-indicating documents."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-0821966abff87f794597de47538cc67e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bac2de5ec87beec114bb4549e917cb4e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SIN SUAN TUA&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Sin Suan Tua is the individual property of each spouse, which is prioritized for fulfilling personal obligations."&lt;SEP&gt;"Sin Suan Tua refers to personal property as defined in the context of marital and family law."&lt;SEP&gt;"Sin Suan Tua refers to personal property managed by a spouse when appointed as guardian."&lt;SEP&gt;"Sin Suan Tua refers to personal property that is not subject to equal distribution upon divorce, differing from Sin Somros."&lt;SEP&gt;"Sin Suan Tua refers to the personal property of each spouse, including possessions acquired before marriage or through personal gifts, wills, or tools necessary for professional work."&lt;SEP&gt;"Sin Suan Tua refers to the personal property of each spouse, used for individual debts."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-cb6f943ed567718e3b0963e9f80b3c0b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3eb681d2c9c192f73e0418def1ff82e7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9eea79da373e97e5b9f92916632488ba&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6158dfc7a7c5c354484d988186bd2709&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2f3971fdef62800a7dabb59d8dfbd427&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9acfb88a2614f5c4b2f078b95a067e71</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;CONDITIONAL OWNER&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Conditional Owner is an individual with provisional rights to land, which may be altered based on specific conditions related to ownership."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-e69f756c60167e54cbfb8769b0011720</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;FRAUD&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Fraud involves deception intended to result in financial or personal gain, affecting the legitimacy of a will if proven to have influenced its creation."&lt;SEP&gt;"Fraud involves deception to manipulate a declaration of intention, affecting the validity of a juristic act."&lt;SEP&gt;"Fraud involves deception to secure unfair or unlawful gain, affecting the integrity of a juristic act."&lt;SEP&gt;"Fraud refers to deceitful actions that can influence the inheritance process, causing heirs to be excluded if they engage in such actions."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-8ddccbf45ec50ee6c41104c7f6c4c61b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-933d505d06605d728d8a7325e6245238&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a7a64e6f6e939634750f7cc32da6d781&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-42327e0a2270d0b8c03bcfa35b359606</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1630&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1630 clarifies that lower class heirs have no rights if higher class heirs survive, except in specific parental scenarios."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-c2ac78f2ab241f4845c5c94a44c0ffb6</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;RENT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Rent refers to a periodic payment made by the hirer to the letter for the use of property under a hire agreement."&lt;SEP&gt;"Rent refers to payment made for the temporary use of another's property, relevant in agreements like superficies when it's stipulated in the contract."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-bd6efc93031ebfde67a4ae4a12bbe3ce&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d6852cd5ceee34402f3999c849ff9c9f</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SIN SOMROS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Sin Somros denotes common marital property, subject to joint management regulations."&lt;SEP&gt;"Sin Somros encompasses property acquired during marriage, shared assets, or any fruits derived from Sin Suan Tua."&lt;SEP&gt;"Sin Somros refers to common marital property managed by a spouse when appointed as guardian."&lt;SEP&gt;"Sin Somros refers to property jointly owned by spouses, requiring mutual management and consent for certain actions."&lt;SEP&gt;"Sin Somros refers to the common property of both spouses acquired during the marriage, considered in legal calculations for compensation in inheritance."&lt;SEP&gt;"Sin Somros refers to the marital property accumulated during the marriage, which is subject to division upon divorce."&lt;SEP&gt;"Sin Somros refers to the property jointly owned by spouses during marriage, which can be used for shared debts."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-cb6f943ed567718e3b0963e9f80b3c0b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3eb681d2c9c192f73e0418def1ff82e7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9eea79da373e97e5b9f92916632488ba&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6158dfc7a7c5c354484d988186bd2709&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-82d56e3add17387eb012a80a933cb63c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2f3971fdef62800a7dabb59d8dfbd427&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9acfb88a2614f5c4b2f078b95a067e71</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;COMPOSITE THING&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Composite Thing refers to an object made from the joining of multiple movables, resulting in shared ownership or a principal owner."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-e69f756c60167e54cbfb8769b0011720</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;WILL&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A Will is a legal declaration by which a person names one or more persons to manage their estate and provides for the transfer of their property at death according to the will's stipulations."&lt;SEP&gt;"A Will is a legal document created by a Testator to dispose of their property and potentially appoint a Controller of Property."&lt;SEP&gt;"A legal document expressing a person's wishes regarding the distribution of their estate after death."&lt;SEP&gt;"A will is a legal document in which a person specifies how their property should be distributed after their death."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-c2ac78f2ab241f4845c5c94a44c0ffb6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6f29560483a94cdf780f52af44990dd1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a7a64e6f6e939634750f7cc32da6d781&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-553b3730ac4ba8b3212a7d230dbc31ad</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1631&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1631 addresses inheritance rights among descendants of different degrees, allowing only closest descending children to inherit directly."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-c2ac78f2ab241f4845c5c94a44c0ffb6</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;LETTER&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Letter is the individual or party who owns the property being hired out, responsible for delivering it in good repair and handling defects according to the contract."&lt;SEP&gt;"The letter is the person or entity that leases out the property to a hirer in exchange for rent."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-47c412635e02e67c8c5e723ae7e9d0ea&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bd6efc93031ebfde67a4ae4a12bbe3ce</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;RECEIVER&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"ROLE"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A Receiver is a person appointed by a court to manage property, often in cases where the owner is unable to do so."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-d42bf94e7a02b8cef96bd3ed9bc3ceaf</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;OCCUPATION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Occupation is the act of acquiring ownership of an ownerless movable, subject to legal regulations and rights."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-e69f756c60167e54cbfb8769b0011720</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;EXCLUSION FROM SUCCESSION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The event where an heir is prevented from inheriting due to unworthy actions or legal disqualifications as outlined in the Code."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-a7a64e6f6e939634750f7cc32da6d781</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1632&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1632 outlines the distribution of inheritance among statutory heirs of different classes in accordance with the provisions of the law."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-c2ac78f2ab241f4845c5c94a44c0ffb6</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;HIRER&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Hirer is the individual or party who rents and takes possession of a property under specific contract terms, responsible for maintaining the property and complying with the contract stipulations."&lt;SEP&gt;"The hirer is the person or entity that rents the property from a letter and is responsible for paying rent and maintaining the property."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-47c412635e02e67c8c5e723ae7e9d0ea&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bd6efc93031ebfde67a4ae4a12bbe3ce</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;USUFRUCTUARY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"ROLE"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A Usufructuary is a person or entity that has the right to use and enjoy the property of another, being responsible for maintenance and certain expenses."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Usufructuary is the person granted the usufruct, entitling them to the possession, use, and enjoyment of a property, including rights of management."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-d42bf94e7a02b8cef96bd3ed9bc3ceaf&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d6852cd5ceee34402f3999c849ff9c9f</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;COMMISSION AGENT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A commission agent is a person who conducts commercial transactions, such as buying or selling property, in their own name on behalf of a principal and is entitled to remuneration for such activities."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-e5738a6d02b9e258a742c992fef4b611</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;DISINHERITANCE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A process where an individual is intentionally deprived of their legal right to inherit."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-a7a64e6f6e939634750f7cc32da6d781</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 560-579&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Sections 560-579 detail various legal stipulations and guidelines related to contracts of hire and hire-purchase including rights and duties of involved parties."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-bd6efc93031ebfde67a4ae4a12bbe3ce</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1633&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1633 guarantees equal shares of inheritance among statutory heirs within the same class, with a single heir entitled to the full portion."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-c2ac78f2ab241f4845c5c94a44c0ffb6</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;OWNER&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"ROLE"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Owner is an individual or entity that holds legal title to a property and has responsibilities including bearing extraordinary expenses."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Owner is the individual who holds the title to a piece of land or property and has the right to create superficies or usufruct."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-d42bf94e7a02b8cef96bd3ed9bc3ceaf&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d6852cd5ceee34402f3999c849ff9c9f</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;DEL CREDERE AGENT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A del credere agent is a type of commission agent who guarantees the performance of a contract and receives special remuneration for undertaking such a guarantee."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-e5738a6d02b9e258a742c992fef4b611</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;MANAGING PARTNERS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Managing partners are responsible for managing the business of the partnership and can be removed only with the consent of all other partners unless otherwise agreed."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-81d63dbc17e3f3707788a6e2552b764c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1634&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1634 details the division of an inheritance per stirpes among descendants, favoring direct descendants but allowing lower degree claims through representation."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-c2ac78f2ab241f4845c5c94a44c0ffb6</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;CONTRACT OF HIRE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A Contract of Hire is an agreement where one party rents a property from another, involving rights, responsibilities, and terms specified in sections 560-569."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Contract of Hire is a legal agreement that defines the terms and conditions under which a property is rented from the Letter to the Hirer."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-47c412635e02e67c8c5e723ae7e9d0ea&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bd6efc93031ebfde67a4ae4a12bbe3ce</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;BETROTHAL&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Betrothal is a formal engagement where property like Khongman or Sinsod is exchanged as part of the marriage arrangement."&lt;SEP&gt;"Betrothal is the formal engagement between individuals, following certain legal conditions, and involves exchanging property such as Khongman and Sinsod."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-32f0865d6629c46fe99f13ae20d441f7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d42bf94e7a02b8cef96bd3ed9bc3ceaf</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;BROKER&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A broker is a person who facilitates transactions between parties by indicating opportunities or procuring contracts, typically paid upon successful completion of these transactions."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-e5738a6d02b9e258a742c992fef4b611</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;NON-MANAGING PARTNERS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Non-managing partners have the right to inquire into the business's management and inspect partnership books and documents."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-81d63dbc17e3f3707788a6e2552b764c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1056&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The legal provision governing the termination of a partnership at the end of a financial year with at least six months' notice."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-e319f375a4d832025273d5a023fbe5e9</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;HIRE-PURCHASE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Hire-Purchase involves contracts where the owner lets out property under a hire agreement and may transfer ownership upon completion of payments, detailed in sections 572-574."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-bd6efc93031ebfde67a4ae4a12bbe3ce</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;KHONGMAN&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Khongman is a specific property category involved in Sin Suan Tua, whose classification affects how assets are managed and divided."&lt;SEP&gt;"Khongman is property transferred to a woman after betrothal."&lt;SEP&gt;"Khongman refers to the property given by the man to the woman as evidence of a betrothal."&lt;SEP&gt;"Khongman refers to the return of certain items following the breach or denunciation of a betrothal agreement, as per sections 1439 and 1442."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-32f0865d6629c46fe99f13ae20d441f7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d42bf94e7a02b8cef96bd3ed9bc3ceaf&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f3a1cd577a93157d9b1c759e9c604a8c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9eea79da373e97e5b9f92916632488ba</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 828&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 828 refers to a legal provision discussing the obligations of an agent to protect the principal's interests upon the principal's death, incapacitation, or bankruptcy."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-e5738a6d02b9e258a742c992fef4b611</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;PARTNERSHIP AGREEMENT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The partnership agreement is the governing document that outlines partner responsibilities, management authority, and conditions for adding or removing partners."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-81d63dbc17e3f3707788a6e2552b764c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;HIRE OF SERVICES&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A Hire of Services is a contract where an employee renders services to an employer who pays for these services, as specified in sections 575-579."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-bd6efc93031ebfde67a4ae4a12bbe3ce</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1057&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The legal provision allowing dissolution of a partnership by the court under specified conditions such as violations or impracticality."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-e319f375a4d832025273d5a023fbe5e9</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SINSOD&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Sinsod is property given by a man to the woman's guardians in return for her agreement to marry."&lt;SEP&gt;"Sinsod is property transferred from the man to the woman's parents, adopter, or guardian as acknowledgment of agreement to marriage."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-32f0865d6629c46fe99f13ae20d441f7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d42bf94e7a02b8cef96bd3ed9bc3ceaf</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 829&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 829 outlines the responsibilities of an heir or representative to inform the principal and safeguard their interests if the agent dies, becomes incapacitated, or goes bankrupt."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-e5738a6d02b9e258a742c992fef4b611</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;PARTNER&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A Partner is an individual who holds a role within a partnership, with responsibilities and potential liabilities under partnership agreements."&lt;SEP&gt;"A partner is an individual who is involved in a registered partnership, sharing the responsibilities, profits, and liabilities of the business based on the partnership agreement."&lt;SEP&gt;"A partner is an individual who shares in the management, profits, and liabilities of a partnership."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-30e7eef2c9f266924b324154eca432d3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-691e23128e3c79c43c11b76dcdb0c630&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-81d63dbc17e3f3707788a6e2552b764c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;AGRICULTURAL YEAR&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Agricultural Year refers to the specific period assumed for the hire of paddy land and relates to farming cycles."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-bd6efc93031ebfde67a4ae4a12bbe3ce</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1058&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The provision allowing for the expulsion of a partner by court order instead of partnership dissolution in certain circumstances."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-e319f375a4d832025273d5a023fbe5e9</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;IMMERSED PROPERTY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Immersed Property refers to real estate that is subject to certain legal charges or obligations, allowing periodic performance or specific use."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-d42bf94e7a02b8cef96bd3ed9bc3ceaf</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 830&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 830 states that the causes for the extinction of an agency must be notified to the other party, where they cannot be used as a defense otherwise."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-e5738a6d02b9e258a742c992fef4b611</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;PARTNERSHIP BOOKS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Partnership books refer to the records and documents that detail the financial and managerial activities of a partnership."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-81d63dbc17e3f3707788a6e2552b764c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1445&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1445 allows a betrothed man to claim compensation from another man who knowingly has intercourse with his betrothed woman."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 1445 defines the prescription period for claims related to misconduct impacting a betrothal agreement."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-32f0865d6629c46fe99f13ae20d441f7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f3a1cd577a93157d9b1c759e9c604a8c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1059&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The section that outlines circumstances under which a partnership may continue for an indefinite time if there is no settlement or liquidation."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-e319f375a4d832025273d5a023fbe5e9</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;TRUST&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A Trust is an arrangement involving the management of the testator's property by another for the benefit of a third party, although its effect is void according to the given sections."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-a2aa959400bcd6663682a867aebf2801</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1446&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1446 also addresses the prescription for claims concerning misconduct in a betrothal, similar to Section 1445."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 1446 permits a betrothed man to claim compensation without renouncing the agreement if the woman is violated."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-32f0865d6629c46fe99f13ae20d441f7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f3a1cd577a93157d9b1c759e9c604a8c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1060&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The legal provision stating that a subsisting partnership can continue after buying out a partner whose membership has ceased."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-e319f375a4d832025273d5a023fbe5e9</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;OFFICIAL RECEIVER IN BANKRUPTCY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Official Receiver in Bankruptcy is a legal figure responsible for managing the affairs of bankrupt individuals or entities, particularly in public auctions."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-880c1ecd6c4ca0a05ce8398767d6a999</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1447&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1447 deals with the determination of compensation claims according to circumstances."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-32f0865d6629c46fe99f13ae20d441f7</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1061&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The section detailing the requirements for the liquidation process after the dissolution of a partnership unless other methods are agreed upon."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-e319f375a4d832025273d5a023fbe5e9</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;TITLE III&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Title III is a section of a legal book that outlines the rules governing how ownership can be acquired through prescription."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-880c1ecd6c4ca0a05ce8398767d6a999</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1447/1&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1447/1 establishes time limits for claiming compensation related to betrothal agreement breaches."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 1447/1 outlines time limits for making compensation claims."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-32f0865d6629c46fe99f13ae20d441f7</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1062&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"This section lists the order in which the liquidation must address obligations, reimbursements, contributions, and distribution of any remaining balance."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-e319f375a4d832025273d5a023fbe5e9</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;PRESCRIPTIVE ACQUISITION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Prescriptive Acquisition refers to the legal process of obtaining ownership of property through continuous and open use over a period specified by law."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-880c1ecd6c4ca0a05ce8398767d6a999</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1441&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1441 outlines that no compensation claims can be made if one party of the betrothal dies before marriage."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-32f0865d6629c46fe99f13ae20d441f7</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1063&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"This section discusses how losses should be divided if assets are insufficient to return the total amount of contributions to the partners after fulfilling obligations."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-e319f375a4d832025273d5a023fbe5e9</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;WASTE LAND&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Waste Land refers to uninhabited and often unused land that may revert to State ownership when abandoned."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-880c1ecd6c4ca0a05ce8398767d6a999</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;REPUTATION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Reputation refers to the social standing that may be damaged, leading to compensation claims in a breach of betrothal."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-32f0865d6629c46fe99f13ae20d441f7</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1064&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The section covering the registration of ordinary partnerships, detailing the necessary particulars for registering a partnership."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-e319f375a4d832025273d5a023fbe5e9</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;ARTIFICIAL DRAINAGE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Artificial Drainage involves human-made channels or alterations that direct water flow from one piece of land to another."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-880c1ecd6c4ca0a05ce8398767d6a999</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 418&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 418 details restoration responsibilities for property alterations by a recipient in bad faith, stating potential costs the owner might bear."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 418 is related to undue enrichment laws applicable to the return of Khongman or Sinsod."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-fcc1f7edc6fff66f0cf31baecb707aad&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-32f0865d6629c46fe99f13ae20d441f7</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1064/1&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A specific clause providing guidelines for the resignation of a managing partner in a registered partnership."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-e319f375a4d832025273d5a023fbe5e9</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;BOUNDARY LINE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Boundary Line refers to the dividing line between two properties, which has legal significance for construction and ownership."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-880c1ecd6c4ca0a05ce8398767d6a999</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SPOUSES&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Spouses in this text are surviving partners of a deceased individual, entitled to inherit based on specific legal conditions outlined in the sections."&lt;SEP&gt;"Spouses refer to individuals who are married to each other and may have claims affected by prescription upon dissolution of marriage."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-d45ed62b6b0bfc44f2c1ae4fe430c9c0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-82d56e3add17387eb012a80a933cb63c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE EMPLOYER&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Employer is the party that hires employees or contractors, and has the right to terminate contracts under certain conditions."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-2ce8b9dc980462f61e8da5767b5fa7eb</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;LAND LAW&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Land Law comprises the regulations governing the ownership, use, and transfer of land."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-880c1ecd6c4ca0a05ce8398767d6a999</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;ACTION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Action refers to a legal proceeding initiated to enforce or establish a right or obligation, often related to prescription interruption."&lt;SEP&gt;"Action refers to the legal proceedings that arise in the context of property sales, particularly when disputes about property rights or eviction claims are involved."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-d45ed62b6b0bfc44f2c1ae4fe430c9c0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-33f27ab34f7ee4094ebd4f5171db4171</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE EMPLOYEE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Employee is the individual who provides services to the employer and has specific rights and obligations under the contract."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-2ce8b9dc980462f61e8da5767b5fa7eb</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1533&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1533 specifies that upon divorce, the Sin Somros (marital property) is to be equally divided between the spouses."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-3eb681d2c9c192f73e0418def1ff82e7</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 193/14, SECTION 193/15, SECTION 193/16, SECTION 193/17, SECTION 193/18, SECTION 193/19, SECTION 193/20, SECTION 193/21, SECTION 193/22, SECTION 193/23, SECTION 193/24, SECTION 193/25, SECTION 193/26, SECTION 193/27, SECTION 193/28, SECTION 193/29&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"These sections are legal provisions outlining various rules and exceptions related to the interruption and completion of prescription periods."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-d45ed62b6b0bfc44f2c1ae4fe430c9c0</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE CONTRACTOR&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Contractor is an individual or entity hired to complete a specific work for the employer, with responsibilities for providing tools and materials."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-2ce8b9dc980462f61e8da5767b5fa7eb</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1527&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1527 provides conditions under which a divorce can be effected on grounds such as insanity or communicable diseases."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-3eb681d2c9c192f73e0418def1ff82e7</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;TRANSFEREE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Transferee is a person who receives shares from the transferor and becomes the registered owner in the company's register of shareholders."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Transferee is an entity that receives a transfer of obligation rights from another party known as the transferor."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Transferee is the person or entity receiving the ownership of hired property, acquiring the associated rights and duties from the transferor."&lt;SEP&gt;"The transferee is an individual or entity that receives a transfer of property which is subject to a mortgage."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-6cd9b0e3cf4adfb36e41fca038140314&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6cd60bb5f8e5d886648c66def090b185&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e3fe26f521adf40f2978335cdbc054b9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bd6efc93031ebfde67a4ae4a12bbe3ce</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;CONTRACT TERMINATION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Contract Termination refers to the cessation of a contract due to specific conditions such as absence of skill, misconduct, or non-compliance."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-2ce8b9dc980462f61e8da5767b5fa7eb</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1529&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1529 specifies the time limit within which a divorce claim can be made based on certain grounds provided in Section 1516 and others."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-3eb681d2c9c192f73e0418def1ff82e7</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;PRINCIPAL DEBTOR&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The principal debtor is the person who owes money to the mortgagee and is personally liable for the debt."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-e3fe26f521adf40f2978335cdbc054b9</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 578&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 578 outlines the conditions under which an employer can terminate a contract due to the employee's lack of special skill if such skill was warranted."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-2ce8b9dc980462f61e8da5767b5fa7eb</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1531&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1531 outlines that divorce by mutual consent is effective upon registration, while divorce by court judgment is effective when the judgment is final."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-3eb681d2c9c192f73e0418def1ff82e7</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;CREDITORS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Creditors are entities to whom the company owes money and must be informed of any proposed capital reductions to raise objections if necessary."&lt;SEP&gt;"Creditors are individuals or entities to whom the company owes money and must be notified of proposed amalgamations or transformations."&lt;SEP&gt;"Creditors in this context are individuals or entities that hold a financial claim against the mortgaged property."&lt;SEP&gt;"Entities or individuals to whom a partnership or company owes money."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-34e7b7cbd3efe1f3b5bdd00742010ed6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-07706a49d3b190ef1fa2b1178a2e275f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-28aaa22d510e3f49e80675454af7f8a3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e3fe26f521adf40f2978335cdbc054b9</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 579&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 579 specifies that an employee's absence for a reasonable cause and duration does not justify contract termination."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-2ce8b9dc980462f61e8da5767b5fa7eb</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1532&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1532 addresses the liquidation of property following a divorce, distinguishing between divorces by mutual consent and by court judgment."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-3eb681d2c9c192f73e0418def1ff82e7</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;AUCTION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"An Auction is a public sale in which goods or properties are sold to the highest bidder."&lt;SEP&gt;"An auction is a public sale event where the mortgaged property is sold to the highest bidder."&lt;SEP&gt;"Auction is the public sale event where pledged property can be sold by the pledgee to satisfy the pledgor's obligation."&lt;SEP&gt;"Auction is the public sale of the subject of performance when it is not suitable for deposit or at risk of deterioration."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Auction is a public sale event where goods are sold to the highest bidder, and it requires public advertisement regarding its time and place."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-c35036965b446b68b1f64bc55f989965&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e3fe26f521adf40f2978335cdbc054b9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b3971476de4ec8b22a6311d4e55caca0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8ced30eeca0d6aa10b4e6af82a8bb160&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ad85db58921b57d9188908867cdfdeba</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 580&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 580 details when remuneration is payable, either at the end of the service period or after services have been rendered."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-2ce8b9dc980462f61e8da5767b5fa7eb</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1534&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1534 discusses the implications of one spouse disposing of the Sin Somros in a manner that harms the other before divorce."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-3eb681d2c9c192f73e0418def1ff82e7</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 735 TO SECTION 746&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"These sections outline the legal procedures and rights related to the enforcement and removal of a mortgage, rights of transferees, and the extinction of a mortgage."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-e3fe26f521adf40f2978335cdbc054b9</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 581&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 581 explains the presumption of a new contract if service continues after the end period without employer objection."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-2ce8b9dc980462f61e8da5767b5fa7eb</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1535&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1535 states that upon termination of the marriage, both spouses are liable for common debts equally."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-3eb681d2c9c192f73e0418def1ff82e7</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;MORTGAGED PROPERTY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The property that is used as security for the mortgage loan and is subject to the rights and enforcement actions described in the sections."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-e3fe26f521adf40f2978335cdbc054b9</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 582&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 582 allows either party to terminate a contract by giving notice when no contract duration is fixed."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-2ce8b9dc980462f61e8da5767b5fa7eb</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;TITLE II: PARENT AND CHILD&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Title II covers regulations related to parent and child relationships, including issues of parentage and legitimate parent-child relationships."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-3eb681d2c9c192f73e0418def1ff82e7</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;DOMICILE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Domicile is defined as the principal place of residence for a natural person, which can change according to several factors."&lt;SEP&gt;"Domicile refers to the home or residence of the creditor, which could influence the performance obligations."&lt;SEP&gt;"Domicile refers to the legal residence or location of the transferee, as needed for legal notifications and transactions."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-c35036965b446b68b1f64bc55f989965&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e3fe26f521adf40f2978335cdbc054b9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-42fad725aa98ee40547f7a36e0de09d6</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 583&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 583 allows for dismissal without notice if an employee disobeys commands, neglects duties, or is guilty of misconduct."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-2ce8b9dc980462f61e8da5767b5fa7eb</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;CHAPTER I: PARENTAGE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Chapter I within Title II discusses the legal presumption of a child's legitimacy based on the circumstances of the marriage and birth."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-3eb681d2c9c192f73e0418def1ff82e7</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;FORECLOSURE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Foreclosure is the legal process by which a mortgagee can claim ownership of the mortgaged property due to the debtor's failure to fulfill obligations."&lt;SEP&gt;"The legal process by which a mortgagee can terminate the mortgagor's equitable right of redemption, usually by court order and subsequent sale of the mortgaged property."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-e3fe26f521adf40f2978335cdbc054b9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-03ac67cce0a415062b1435a1e40830bb</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 584&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 584 explains that a contract requiring the employer's personality is extinguished upon the employer's death."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-2ce8b9dc980462f61e8da5767b5fa7eb</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1536&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1536 presumes a child born during certain periods of marriage to be legitimate, affecting custodial rights and responsibilities."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 1536 relates to legal presumptions about the legitimacy of a child within specific contexts."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-3eb681d2c9c192f73e0418def1ff82e7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d9947bc7fb3e59afe960708bcf533e3c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;OFFICIAL REGISTER&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The official register is an authoritative registry where entries related to property ownership, transfers, and liens are recorded."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-e3fe26f521adf40f2978335cdbc054b9</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 585&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 585 entitles an employee to a certificate detailing service length and nature once services end."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-2ce8b9dc980462f61e8da5767b5fa7eb</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1537&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1537 involves legal considerations and judgments related to the legitimacy of a child."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 1537 relates to the legitimacy of a child when a woman remarries within a specific period after a prior marriage ends."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-3eb681d2c9c192f73e0418def1ff82e7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d9947bc7fb3e59afe960708bcf533e3c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;RELEASE OF MORTGAGE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A legal declaration that a mortgage has been satisfied, released, and is no longer enforceable against the property."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-e3fe26f521adf40f2978335cdbc054b9</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 586&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 586 mandates the employer to cover return travel costs for employees brought from elsewhere, barring termination by employee's fault."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-2ce8b9dc980462f61e8da5767b5fa7eb</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1538&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1538 deals with the legitimacy of a child born from a marriage that violated legal restrictions outlined in Section 1452."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 1538 provides legal context for determining a child's legitimacy in connection to previous marriages."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-3eb681d2c9c192f73e0418def1ff82e7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d9947bc7fb3e59afe960708bcf533e3c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1539&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1539 allows for legal actions to repudiate a child's legitimacy by the husband or man who used to be the husband."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-d9947bc7fb3e59afe960708bcf533e3c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;MERGER&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"In legal terms, merger refers to the termination of certain rights over the mortgaged property when they coincide with becoming the same legal person."&lt;SEP&gt;"Merger occurs when rights and liabilities under an obligation become vested in the same person, typically extinguishing the obligation."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-e3fe26f521adf40f2978335cdbc054b9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8ced30eeca0d6aa10b4e6af82a8bb160</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 587&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 587 defines the hire of work contract as an agreement for the contractor to accomplish specific work for the employer."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-2ce8b9dc980462f61e8da5767b5fa7eb</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1541&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1541 outlines conditions under which a husband cannot repudiate a child once recognized."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-d9947bc7fb3e59afe960708bcf533e3c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE COMPANY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Company is an organization that manages the transfer of shares, maintains a register of shareholders, and operates under specific regulations defined by law."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Company is an organization with regulations regarding the appointment, removal, and duties of its directors. It must register any change in directors and has specific protocols for meetings and decision-making processes."&lt;SEP&gt;"The company referred to in the document, responsible for handling dividends, reserve funds, and auditing as per regulations."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-83644292281589f5325e70fbbf9a5034&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b23ff2ff58dfd16196c0503c1c3ca1b2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6cd60bb5f8e5d886648c66def090b185</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 588&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 588 states that contractors must provide necessary tools or instruments for work execution."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-2ce8b9dc980462f61e8da5767b5fa7eb</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE DIRECTORS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Directors of the company who are responsible for managing dividends, keeping the books, supervising audits, and ensuring compliance with company regulations."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-b23ff2ff58dfd16196c0503c1c3ca1b2</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 589&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 589 obligates contractors to supply materials of good quality if they are responsible for them."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-2ce8b9dc980462f61e8da5767b5fa7eb</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1542&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1542 discusses time constraints for entering repudiation actions after the child's birth."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-d9947bc7fb3e59afe960708bcf533e3c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SHAREHOLDERS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Individuals or entities holding shares in the company, entitled to dividends and capable of inspecting company documents."&lt;SEP&gt;"Individuals or entities that own shares in a company and have rights to vote on certain company matters and receive profits."&lt;SEP&gt;"Shareholders are individuals or entities that hold shares in a limited company, having rights to receive offers of new shares proportionate to their holdings."&lt;SEP&gt;"Shareholders are individuals or entities that own shares in a company and have rights and responsibilities within that company."&lt;SEP&gt;"Shareholders are individuals or entities that own shares in a company, holding certain rights and responsibilities."&lt;SEP&gt;"Shareholders are individuals or entities that own shares in the company, giving them certain rights and responsibilities, including voting at meetings."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-34e7b7cbd3efe1f3b5bdd00742010ed6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d67f818d289a7a42a391ffd601a49336&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ddd247e62a952c755b8e64cbea59a2d3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fd4f265f6be599f877d85099036f52dc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-07706a49d3b190ef1fa2b1178a2e275f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b23ff2ff58dfd16196c0503c1c3ca1b2</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 590&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 590 requires contractors to use employer-supplied materials carefully and return any surplus."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-2ce8b9dc980462f61e8da5767b5fa7eb</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1543&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1543 allows substitution in legal actions for repudiation if the original petitioner dies before case finalization."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-d9947bc7fb3e59afe960708bcf533e3c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE REGISTRAR&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Registrar is a governmental or official figure responsible for overseeing the registration and regulation of foundations, including assessing suitability and inspecting their activities."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Registrar is an authority to whom the directors must submit certain documents, such as the balance sheet, by stipulated deadlines."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Registrar is an official responsible for maintaining the register of associations and has the authority to strike off associations from the register under certain conditions."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Registrar is responsible for notifying involved parties of legitimation applications and carrying out the registration following a court judgment."&lt;SEP&gt;"The registrar handles notifications and publications regarding the dissolution of foundations and oversees the liquidation process."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-182a2b244fdc4ad235c762ab46288dca&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a8f2d8db15aae9334e2b0c36d4ea99c8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-86deb2357b8656ccf8680e27cbac71ec&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b23ff2ff58dfd16196c0503c1c3ca1b2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c8c3be6aeb4b1e7e1a17d53346a1d923</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 591&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 591 outlines contractor liability related to defects or delays caused by employer-provided materials or instructions."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-2ce8b9dc980462f61e8da5767b5fa7eb</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1544&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1544 permits others to initiate repudiation actions if the husband dies, under specific conditions."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-d9947bc7fb3e59afe960708bcf533e3c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE AUDITORS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Elected individuals responsible for auditing the company's accounts and ensuring their accuracy, who must report their findings in ordinary meetings."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-b23ff2ff58dfd16196c0503c1c3ca1b2</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 592&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 592 grants the employer the right to inspect work during execution."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-2ce8b9dc980462f61e8da5767b5fa7eb</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1545&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1545 enables a child to request repudiation actions if not recognized as the legitimate child of the mother's husband."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-d9947bc7fb3e59afe960708bcf533e3c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE COMPETENT MINISTER&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A government official with the authority to appoint inspectors upon shareholder request to examine the company's affairs."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-b23ff2ff58dfd16196c0503c1c3ca1b2</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 593&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 593 allows contract cancellation by the employer if work commencement is delayed or if timely completion is unlikely."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-2ce8b9dc980462f61e8da5767b5fa7eb</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;BIRTH REGISTER&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Birth Register is an official document where births are registered, affecting a child's legitimacy status."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-d9947bc7fb3e59afe960708bcf533e3c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;BALANCE SHEET&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A financial statement that summarizes the company's assets, liabilities, and shareholders' equity at a specific point in time."&lt;SEP&gt;"Balance sheet entails financial documentation such as dividend distribution, books, and dissolution, as covered in Sections 1196 to 1297."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-5429b702233c5b142e4f7e7899dffac1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b23ff2ff58dfd16196c0503c1c3ca1b2</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 594&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 594 provides conditions for employers to demand defects be addressed by setting reasonable deadlines."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-2ce8b9dc980462f61e8da5767b5fa7eb</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE COMMITTEE OF THE FOUNDATION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Committee of the Foundation is a group responsible for managing and amending the regulations of the foundation and ensures its objectives are pursued successfully."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-a8f2d8db15aae9334e2b0c36d4ea99c8</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;INTERIM DIVIDENDS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Dividends distributed by the company board of directors before the annual earnings have been calculated."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-b23ff2ff58dfd16196c0503c1c3ca1b2</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 595&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 595 pertains to contractor liability for material defects under sales law provisions."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-2ce8b9dc980462f61e8da5767b5fa7eb</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;DIRECTORS OF THE FOUNDATION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Directors are individuals responsible for executing the foundation’s activities and maintaining its compliance with legal and internal regulations."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-a8f2d8db15aae9334e2b0c36d4ea99c8</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;RESERVE FUND&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A portion of the company's profits set aside as a safeguard or for future investments, as stipulated by company regulations."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-b23ff2ff58dfd16196c0503c1c3ca1b2</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 596&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 596 allows for remuneration reduction or contract rescission if work is delayed."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-2ce8b9dc980462f61e8da5767b5fa7eb</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 115&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 115 refers to a legal provision applied mutatis mutandis in various regulations concerning the foundation's activities or amendments."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 115 refers to legal penalties for instigating military or police forces to desert duties."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-5206f82195413280707c7f3a4938d1ba&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a8f2d8db15aae9334e2b0c36d4ea99c8</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;AUDITORS' REPORT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A report created by auditors that gives an opinion on whether the company's financial statements are accurate and fairly presented."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-b23ff2ff58dfd16196c0503c1c3ca1b2</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 597&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 597 limits contractor liability for work delay if accepted by the employer without reservation."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-2ce8b9dc980462f61e8da5767b5fa7eb</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 112 (2)&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 112 (2) details specific legal requirements or exceptions under which changes to the foundation's regulations can be made."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-a8f2d8db15aae9334e2b0c36d4ea99c8</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;INSPECTION BY MINISTERS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"An investigation conducted by appointed officials into the company's affairs, initiated at the request of shareholders."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-b23ff2ff58dfd16196c0503c1c3ca1b2</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1064/2&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1064/2 of the legal text mandates that any change in the managing partner of a registered partnership must be registered within fourteen days."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-30e7eef2c9f266924b324154eca432d3</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 127&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 127 outlines the committee's authority to amend the regulations of the foundation for achieving its objectives or due to changing circumstances."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-a8f2d8db15aae9334e2b0c36d4ea99c8</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;ORDINARY MEETING&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Regularly scheduled meeting of shareholders in which auditors are elected and other standard business is conducted."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-b23ff2ff58dfd16196c0503c1c3ca1b2</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1069&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1069 specifies that a registered partnership is dissolved if it becomes bankrupt, in addition to other circumstances outlined in section 1055."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-30e7eef2c9f266924b324154eca432d3</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 131&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 131 details the conditions under which a court may order the dissolution of a foundation, such as legal violations or cessation of activities."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-a8f2d8db15aae9334e2b0c36d4ea99c8</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;EXTRAORDINARY MEETING&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A special meeting convened to address specific issues, such as the appointment of an auditor during a vacancy."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-b23ff2ff58dfd16196c0503c1c3ca1b2</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1073&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1073 allows for the amalgamation of registered partnerships, provided all partners consent or as per existing partnership agreements."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-30e7eef2c9f266924b324154eca432d3</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;CIVIL AND COMMERCIAL CODE B.E. 2535&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Civil and Commercial Code B.E. 2535 is a set of legal provisions that have been amended to guide the establishment of wills and related procedures."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-950a514fa4e2ba58663fe41bd3a39da9</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE MORTGAGEE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Mortgagee is the individual or institution that lends money secured by real property through a mortgage and holds certain rights and responsibilities."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-03ac67cce0a415062b1435a1e40830bb</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;ASSETS OF THE PARTNERSHIP&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Assets of the partnership refer to the resources and properties owned by the partnership, used to meet its obligations or shared among partners."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-30e7eef2c9f266924b324154eca432d3</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;MILITARY OFFICER OR OFFICIAL OF COMMISSIONED RANK&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"ROLE"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A military officer or official of commissioned rank has authority similar to the Kromakarn Amphoe in validating wills made during arms conflict or war conditions."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-950a514fa4e2ba58663fe41bd3a39da9</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE MORTGAGOR&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Mortgagor is the person or entity that borrows money by offering real property as security for the obligation to repay the loan."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-03ac67cce0a415062b1435a1e40830bb</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1078&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1078 outlines the requirements for registering a limited partnership, including necessary registration details such as firm name, partner names, and addresses."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 1078 requires the registration of limited partnerships and lists the necessary information to be included, such as the firm name and partnership's object."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-30e7eef2c9f266924b324154eca432d3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-855466dea5984defb1f279860dbf5504</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;MINISTER OF INTERIOR, DEFENSE AND FOREIGN AFFAIRS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Minister of Interior, Defense, and Foreign Affairs have the authority to issue regulations for implementing provisions and setting rates and fees related to wills under the Book."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-950a514fa4e2ba58663fe41bd3a39da9</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE DEBTOR&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Debtor is an individual or entity with obligations that may grant preferential rights in specific immovable or movable property."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Debtor is the individual or entity responsible for fulfilling the performance obligations secured by the mortgage."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Debtor is the party obligated to compensate for damages or distinctions in value during default periods, and their role involves negotiating with creditors."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-23624fb7fffe655b4b7087bd796a908a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-03ac67cce0a415062b1435a1e40830bb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2c01a4f68c167448d4624c0e8d938db0</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;CONTROLLER OF PROPERTY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A Controller of Property is a designated individual or organization responsible for managing and controlling property on behalf of a minor or an incompetent person, as appointed by a will."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-553b3730ac4ba8b3212a7d230dbc31ad</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1665&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1665 outlines that the signature of a testator can be substituted by a fingerprint certified by two witnesses if required by specific sections."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-950a514fa4e2ba58663fe41bd3a39da9</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SERVITUDE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Servitude involves a legal obligation on an immovable property for the benefit of another property, restricting certain rights or imposing certain duties on the owner."&lt;SEP&gt;"Servitude is a legal obligation entailing a burden on the Servient Property for the benefit of the Dominant Property, subject to conditions and possible extinction."&lt;SEP&gt;"Servitude is a legal obligation that may be attached to a property, limiting the rights of the owner, often affecting the property's use or transferability."&lt;SEP&gt;"Servitude is a legal right granted for the use of land, often involving registration of rights in cases of encroachment."&lt;SEP&gt;"Servitude refers to a right by which something is owed or due to another party, often concerning the use of land."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-0e69519b80d6cad28fe98f2e9235bd60&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e69f756c60167e54cbfb8769b0011720&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-03ac67cce0a415062b1435a1e40830bb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9f9bc4a4809d7c6d989c8e5d2ab6f09f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-33f27ab34f7ee4094ebd4f5171db4171</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;INALIENABILITY CLAUSE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"An Inalienability Clause is a stipulation in a disposition of property that prevents the beneficiary from transferring the property to others."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-553b3730ac4ba8b3212a7d230dbc31ad</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1666&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1666 specifies that certain provisions do not apply to witnesses whose signatures are mandated under other sections."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-950a514fa4e2ba58663fe41bd3a39da9</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 722&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 722 details the precedence of mortgages over servitudes or real rights registered without the mortgagee's consent."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-03ac67cce0a415062b1435a1e40830bb</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;LEGITIMATION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Legitimation is a legal process that declares a child as legitimate, affecting the child's rights, including inheritance and use of the father's family name."&lt;SEP&gt;"Legitimation is the legal process where a child's status is legitimized, which involves the parent's marriage, court judgment, or registration by the father."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-a0818329731c6e20f0c0c43a0133253c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c8c3be6aeb4b1e7e1a17d53346a1d923</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1667&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1667 explains how a Thai subject can make a will in a foreign territory, using either the local form or Thai law."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-950a514fa4e2ba58663fe41bd3a39da9</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1668&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1668 states that the testator does not need to disclose the contents of the will to witnesses unless specified by law."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-950a514fa4e2ba58663fe41bd3a39da9</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 723&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 723 outlines the conditions under which a mortgagee can enforce the mortgage due to property damage or loss."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-03ac67cce0a415062b1435a1e40830bb</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE CHILD&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Child is an individual whose legitimacy and parental power is being determined through legal proceedings. The child's consent or objection plays a role in the legitimation process."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-c8c3be6aeb4b1e7e1a17d53346a1d923</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1669&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1669 allows persons serving in armed forces to make wills in certain forms during war times, with military officers having key roles."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-950a514fa4e2ba58663fe41bd3a39da9</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 724&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 724 explains the rights of a mortgagor who performs an obligation on behalf of a debtor to recover costs."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-03ac67cce0a415062b1435a1e40830bb</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE MOTHER&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Mother is the biological parent of a child whose legitimation and parental power is addressed in legal processes. Her consent is required for registration unless objected."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-c8c3be6aeb4b1e7e1a17d53346a1d923</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 725&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 725 addresses the rights and lack of recourse between multiple mortgagors securing the same obligation."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-03ac67cce0a415062b1435a1e40830bb</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE FATHER&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Father is the biological parent who applies for the legitimation of the child, impacting the child's legitimacy status and parental power through legal actions."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-c8c3be6aeb4b1e7e1a17d53346a1d923</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1670&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1670 lists categories of people who cannot serve as witnesses in the creation of a will."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-950a514fa4e2ba58663fe41bd3a39da9</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 726&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 726 concerns the effects of releasing one mortgagor on others when an order is specified for multiple mortgages."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-03ac67cce0a415062b1435a1e40830bb</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SUBHIRER&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Subhirer is a third party who rents the property from the original hirer, becoming liable to the Letter in certain circumstances."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-47c412635e02e67c8c5e723ae7e9d0ea</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1671&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1671 sets out requirements for individuals who write wills on behalf of others, including signing and stating their role."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-950a514fa4e2ba58663fe41bd3a39da9</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 727&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 727 indicates the applicability of suretyship provisions to mortgages securing obligations for others."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-03ac67cce0a415062b1435a1e40830bb</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 544&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 544 outlines that a hirer cannot transfer rights or sublet the property without permission unless specified in the contract."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-47c412635e02e67c8c5e723ae7e9d0ea</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1672&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1672 grants powers to specific ministers to establish regulations related to wills and their associated fees."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-950a514fa4e2ba58663fe41bd3a39da9</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 545&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 545 specifies that a subhirer becomes directly liable to the letter and that payments made in advance cannot be used against the letter."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-47c412635e02e67c8c5e723ae7e9d0ea</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1673&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1673 addresses the rights and duties under a will, which take effect upon the death of the testator with possible conditions on timing."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-950a514fa4e2ba58663fe41bd3a39da9</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 728&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 728 describes the process for mortgage enforcement through notifying the debtor and legal action."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-03ac67cce0a415062b1435a1e40830bb</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1674&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1674 explains how testamentary dispositions under conditions take effect, relating to the fulfillment of those conditions."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-950a514fa4e2ba58663fe41bd3a39da9</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 729&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 729 specifies the conditions under which a mortgagee can claim foreclosure when a debtor defaults."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-03ac67cce0a415062b1435a1e40830bb</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 546&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 546 requires the letter to deliver the property in good repair."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-47c412635e02e67c8c5e723ae7e9d0ea</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 547&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 547 obligates the letter to reimburse the hirer for necessary expenses incurred for the property's preservation, except for ordinary maintenance."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-47c412635e02e67c8c5e723ae7e9d0ea</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THAILANDLAWONLINE.COM&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Thailandlawonline.com is a website providing online legal information and resources specific to Thailand."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-f2d6a052f92eea2a650b78a251a1b5bb</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;FRAUDULENT ACTS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Fraudulent Acts refer to dishonest actions by the debtor intended to deceive creditors, which can be cancelled by the Court."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-ac44eff8208c6427b97025d89925979e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 548&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 548 allows the hirer to terminate the contract if the property is delivered in a condition unsuitable for its intended purpose."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-47c412635e02e67c8c5e723ae7e9d0ea</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SITEMAP&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Sitemap is a section on the Samuiforsale website that helps users navigate through articles and laws."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-f2d6a052f92eea2a650b78a251a1b5bb</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;INSOLVENCY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Insolvency is the financial state where the debtor is unable to meet their debts, affecting rights like retention."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-ac44eff8208c6427b97025d89925979e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 549&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 549 relates to the delivery and liability of the letter in case of defects, governed akin to provisions in sales."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-47c412635e02e67c8c5e723ae7e9d0ea</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1449&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1449 deals with legal aspects of declaring a marriage void under specific conditions."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 1449 is a legal provision related to the conditions under which a marriage can be considered void."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 1449 prohibits marriage if either party is insane or adjudged incompetent."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-f3a1cd577a93157d9b1c759e9c604a8c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fc29664ee0997602190bcc550d1eddec&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2f3971fdef62800a7dabb59d8dfbd427</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 550&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 550 holds the letter liable for defects arising during the contract and requires them to make necessary repairs."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-47c412635e02e67c8c5e723ae7e9d0ea</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;PERIOD OF TIME&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Period of Time refers to the duration for which rights, such as superficies or usufruct, are granted or can be exercised."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Period of Time refers to the durations for which certain legal or contractual agreements or obligations are valid or calculated."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-a51405b734dd6683f138a8765370d40b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d6852cd5ceee34402f3999c849ff9c9f</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1451&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1451 prohibits marriage between an adopter and the adopted."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-f3a1cd577a93157d9b1c759e9c604a8c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 551&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 551 describes the hirer's right to terminate the contract if defects are not addressed timely by the letter."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-47c412635e02e67c8c5e723ae7e9d0ea</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 193&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 193 allows for exemption from punishment if the offense was committed to assist immediate family members."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 193 outlines specific legal circumstances under which a debtor cannot take advantage of certain periods of time."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-a51405b734dd6683f138a8765370d40b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-268065f480c7c2e17bd0004a31f0f454</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1452&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1452 is a legal provision mentioned in the context of marriage legitimacy."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 1452 is a legal provision under which a marriage may be considered void, affecting property rights and inheritance."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 1452 is a legal regulation outlining the circumstances under which a marriage may be declared void."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 1452 prohibits marriage for anyone who is already married."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-f3a1cd577a93157d9b1c759e9c604a8c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fc29664ee0997602190bcc550d1eddec&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2f3971fdef62800a7dabb59d8dfbd427&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d9947bc7fb3e59afe960708bcf533e3c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 552&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 552 restricts the hirer's use of the property to ordinary purposes or those specified in the contract."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-47c412635e02e67c8c5e723ae7e9d0ea</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;PRESCRIPTION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Prescription is a legal concept related to the acquisition of ownership over a property, after a period of uninterrupted and peaceful possession."&lt;SEP&gt;"Prescription is the legal process by which claims may be extinguished due to the passage of time, as defined in various sections of the legal document."&lt;SEP&gt;"Prescription refers to the lapse of a legal right to enforce an obligation due to the passage of time, affecting the entitlement to restitution."&lt;SEP&gt;"Prescription refers to the lapse of time that can extinguish a legal claim or obligation, impacting the rights of creditors or debtors."&lt;SEP&gt;"Prescription refers to the legal concept of time limitations on rights or obligations, which affects suretyship as outlined in Section 692."&lt;SEP&gt;"Prescription refers to the legal limitation period for bringing actions to enforce rights and obligations."&lt;SEP&gt;"Prescription refers to the method of barring claims when they have not been enforced within a legally defined period."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-fcc1f7edc6fff66f0cf31baecb707aad&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d45ed62b6b0bfc44f2c1ae4fe430c9c0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5806a4ac5edf0880beed390e35f10ef7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-aac23a1f6cf12366451f6be3ff0a3ed2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3d46b5b738f6e0830f256b8e2ed69058&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9f9bc4a4809d7c6d989c8e5d2ab6f09f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a51405b734dd6683f138a8765370d40b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1453&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1453 outlines waiting periods and exceptions for remarriage following the end of a previous marriage."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-f3a1cd577a93157d9b1c759e9c604a8c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 553&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 553 mandates the hirer to maintain the property with ordinary care."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-47c412635e02e67c8c5e723ae7e9d0ea</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;TITLE V&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Title V refers to the legal provisions governing the computation and determination of periods of time."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-a51405b734dd6683f138a8765370d40b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1454&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A reference to a legal provision specifying which persons must give consent for a marriage, without which it is voidable."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 1454 relates to marriage of minors and includes additional provisions from Section 1436."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-f3a1cd577a93157d9b1c759e9c604a8c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cb8c8544779f197bfe5eef0d6b3bba3c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 554&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 554 allows the letter to terminate the contract if the hirer does not comply with the use and maintenance provisions."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-47c412635e02e67c8c5e723ae7e9d0ea</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;TITLE VI&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Title VI refers to the legal provisions governing the barring of claims through prescription."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-a51405b734dd6683f138a8765370d40b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1455&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1455 describes the methods for giving consent to a marriage."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-f3a1cd577a93157d9b1c759e9c604a8c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 555&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 555 gives the letter or their agents the right to inspect the property at reasonable times."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-47c412635e02e67c8c5e723ae7e9d0ea</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1456&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1456 provides recourse for minors seeking court consent to marry under certain conditions."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-f3a1cd577a93157d9b1c759e9c604a8c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 556&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 556 outlines the hirer's obligation to permit necessary repairs even if inconvenient unless the repairs disrupt the property's intended use."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-47c412635e02e67c8c5e723ae7e9d0ea</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1457&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1457 requires marriage to be registered officially."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-f3a1cd577a93157d9b1c759e9c604a8c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 557&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 557 requires the hirer to inform the letter of needed repairs or encroachments, and holds the hirer liable for delays from non-notification."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-47c412635e02e67c8c5e723ae7e9d0ea</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;PROXY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Proxy is an individual appointed by a shareholder or group of shareholders to represent them and vote on their behalf at a general meeting."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-7b4f64350387b4e64a273fdcc8130b07</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1458&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1458 is a legal statute discussing the rights acquired through a marriage declared void and specifies provisions about judgments affecting marriage nullification."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 1458 outlines legal conditions that may render a marriage void, affecting subsequent property relations."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 1458 states that marriage is based on mutual agreement to marry, declared publicly."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-f3a1cd577a93157d9b1c759e9c604a8c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fc29664ee0997602190bcc550d1eddec&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2f3971fdef62800a7dabb59d8dfbd427</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;CHAIRMAN&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Chairman is an individual responsible for presiding over company meetings and making declarations on resolutions based on voting outcomes."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Chairman is a director elected to lead meetings. In the absence of an elected chairman, the directors at the meeting may appoint one."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-83644292281589f5325e70fbbf9a5034&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7b4f64350387b4e64a273fdcc8130b07</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1459&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1459 deals with marriage involving Thai citizens in foreign countries."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-f3a1cd577a93157d9b1c759e9c604a8c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 558&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 558 prohibits the hirer from making alterations without permission and holds them liable for any resulting damage."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-47c412635e02e67c8c5e723ae7e9d0ea</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;BALANCE-SHEET&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A financial statement that provides a snapshot of a partnership or company's financial condition by detailing assets, liabilities, and equity."&lt;SEP&gt;"Balance-Sheet refers to a financial statement summarizing assets, liabilities, profit, and loss, and is subject to annual audit and shareholder review."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-34e7b7cbd3efe1f3b5bdd00742010ed6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7b4f64350387b4e64a273fdcc8130b07</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1460&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1460 accommodates marriage registration in special cases such as danger or war, assessing the date of intention to marry as official registration."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-f3a1cd577a93157d9b1c759e9c604a8c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 559&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 559 specifies the schedule for rent payments based on customary or contractual stipulations."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-47c412635e02e67c8c5e723ae7e9d0ea</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SPECIAL RESOLUTION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A Special Resolution is a formal decision made by a limited company to increase or reduce capital, dissolve the company, or undertake other significant actions."&lt;SEP&gt;"A Special Resolution is a formal decision required to make changes or additions to the company’s regulations and must be passed by a specified majority of shareholders."&lt;SEP&gt;"A special resolution is a specific type of shareholder decision required for actions like amalgamation and must be registered with relevant authorities."&lt;SEP&gt;"Special Resolution is a vote requiring a higher majority than ordinary resolutions, often involving significant corporate decisions or regulatory requirements."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-07706a49d3b190ef1fa2b1178a2e275f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-28aaa22d510e3f49e80675454af7f8a3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6cd60bb5f8e5d886648c66def090b185&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7b4f64350387b4e64a273fdcc8130b07</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THAI DIPLOMATIC OR CONSULAR OFFICER&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A Thai Diplomatic or Consular Officer acts within their authority to oversee and certify a will's authenticity made in a foreign territory according to Thai law."&lt;SEP&gt;"These officers are responsible for registering marriages according to Thai law when conducted abroad."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-950a514fa4e2ba58663fe41bd3a39da9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f3a1cd577a93157d9b1c759e9c604a8c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 560&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 560 allows the letter to terminate the contract for non-payment of rent."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-47c412635e02e67c8c5e723ae7e9d0ea</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1520&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1520 refers to the law governing divorce by mutual consent and the exercise of parental power over children."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-359c29184e76341f84467fcf371024a6</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;POLL&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Poll is a voting process used during a general meeting when a numerical vote count is deemed necessary, typically following a show of hands."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-7b4f64350387b4e64a273fdcc8130b07</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;MAN&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Man refers to one of the parties involved in the marriage or betrothal process."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-f3a1cd577a93157d9b1c759e9c604a8c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;AUDITORS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Auditors are appointed professionals responsible for examining and verifying a company’s financial statements and practices for accuracy and compliance."&lt;SEP&gt;"Auditors are professionals responsible for examining the company's financial statements, such as the balance-sheet, ensuring accuracy and compliance."&lt;SEP&gt;"Auditors are professionals who examine financial records and processes to ensure accuracy, compliance, and to identify areas for efficiency improvement."&lt;SEP&gt;"Professionals responsible for examining and verifying the financial affairs of a partnership or company during liquidation."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-34e7b7cbd3efe1f3b5bdd00742010ed6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d67f818d289a7a42a391ffd601a49336&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2b194bfa1a18d3dffd302b027ba18352&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7b4f64350387b4e64a273fdcc8130b07</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;WOMAN&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Woman refers to one of the parties involved in the marriage or betrothal process."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-f3a1cd577a93157d9b1c759e9c604a8c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1516&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1516 outlines various grounds on which a divorce can be filed, including insanity, communicable diseases, and other specified conditions."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 1516 provides specific grounds upon which an action for divorce can be based."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-359c29184e76341f84467fcf371024a6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3eb681d2c9c192f73e0418def1ff82e7</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;REGISTRAR&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"An official responsible for maintaining the registration of limited partnerships and changes related to management."&lt;SEP&gt;"Registrar is an official responsible for maintaining the register of documents and ensuring compliance with registration requirements."&lt;SEP&gt;"Registrar is the official responsible for receiving and processing applications for the registration of foundations, ensuring conformity with laws and regulations."&lt;SEP&gt;"Registrar refers to an official responsible for maintaining company records, including the filing of balance sheets and shareholder information."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Registrar is a government official or agency responsible for maintaining the official record of registered companies and their compliance with regulatory requirements."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Registrar is an official responsible for maintaining records of registered partnerships and other legal entities, ensuring compliance with regulatory requirements."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Registrar is responsible for overseeing the registration status of partnerships and companies, particularly in verifying if they are operating or in liquidation."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Registrar is responsible for recording marriage agreements publicly and overseeing marriage registrations."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Registrar is the authority responsible for accepting, reviewing, and approving applications for registration of associations, ensuring that their objects and regulations comply with the law."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Registrar is the official responsible for recording declarations of intention to marry and maintaining the Marriage Register."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Registrar is the official responsible for registering the conversion of partnerships into limited companies and recording the loss of partnership status."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-91e6c9c6ece02f3027772a9577efdcd4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-30e7eef2c9f266924b324154eca432d3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9fb8ecc1d3b7f08bd11bfbe372805373&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7b4f64350387b4e64a273fdcc8130b07&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ddd247e62a952c755b8e64cbea59a2d3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-46940167ee3908fb358c9a82647ea322&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-237bd5a5c70b356f874e427eb5f0128b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f3a1cd577a93157d9b1c759e9c604a8c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-691e23128e3c79c43c11b76dcdb0c630&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6cd60bb5f8e5d886648c66def090b185&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-855466dea5984defb1f279860dbf5504</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1450&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1450 is a legal provision detailing specific grounds on which a marriage may be adjudged void."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 1450 outlines legal conditions associated with declaring a marriage void."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-fc29664ee0997602190bcc550d1eddec&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2f3971fdef62800a7dabb59d8dfbd427</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1523&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1523 details entitlements to compensation in cases of adultery or misconduct causing emotional harm in a marriage."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-359c29184e76341f84467fcf371024a6</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;VOTING RIGHTS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Voting Rights denote the entitlements of shareholders to vote on matters presented at the company's general meeting, influenced by share ownership and company regulations."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-7b4f64350387b4e64a273fdcc8130b07</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1474 (2)&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1474 (2) relates to the acquisition of property by the spouse through a will or gift, affecting the classification of such property as Sin Suan Tua."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-2f3971fdef62800a7dabb59d8dfbd427</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1530&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1530 details the Court's power to make provisional orders regarding maintenance, custody, and lodging during a divorce proceeding."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 1530 relates to legal procedures in cases where a spouse may be adjudged as an incapacitated person and the implications for divorce proceedings."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-359c29184e76341f84467fcf371024a6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3eb681d2c9c192f73e0418def1ff82e7</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1463&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1463 refers to legal regulations concerning the appointment of guardians for incapacitated persons."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-359c29184e76341f84467fcf371024a6</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;EMPLOYER&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"An Employer is an individual or organization who hires employees and may be jointly liable for wrongful acts committed by employees during employment."&lt;SEP&gt;"The employer is the party to whom the work is delivered and who can accept, reject, or seek remuneration reduction based on the contract conditions."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-6674ed785a247829af22e22520fa7260&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7c177d209afa32287351a7f88d669f7a</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE SELLER&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Seller is responsible for delivering property to the buyer and ensuring the property's compliance with the contract terms, including potential liabilities for defects and eviction."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9ca3fcb51a635c23cbd4974dd21e277f</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1516 (1)&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1516 (1) is a specific clause detailing a ground for divorce which involves misconduct leading to the claim for compensation."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-359c29184e76341f84467fcf371024a6</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;EMPLOYEE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"An Employee is a person hired by an employer to work and may commit wrongful acts for which the employer is jointly liable."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-6674ed785a247829af22e22520fa7260</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE BUYER&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Buyer is the individual or entity purchasing the property, with specific rights to reject or accept property under certain conditions and liability considerations."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9ca3fcb51a635c23cbd4974dd21e277f</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1516 (3)&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1516 (3) outlines another ground for divorce, particularly focusing on actions making the other party intolerable."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-359c29184e76341f84467fcf371024a6</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;PRINCIPAL AND AGENT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Principal and Agent relationship refers to a legal arrangement where the agent acts on behalf of the principal, and both can be liable for wrongful acts."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-6674ed785a247829af22e22520fa7260</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;DELIVERY OF PROPERTY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Delivery of Property refers to the seller's obligation to make the property available to the buyer in accordance with the contract terms."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9ca3fcb51a635c23cbd4974dd21e277f</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1516 (4)&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1516 (4) specifies the criteria for divorce based on particular actions by the spouse under scrutiny."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-359c29184e76341f84467fcf371024a6</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;PARENTS OR GUARDIAN&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Parents or Guardian are individuals responsible for minors or incapacitated persons and may be jointly liable for wrongful acts by these individuals."&lt;SEP&gt;"Parents or guardians are individuals responsible for the care and supervision of children, whom the Court may engage with to ensure the child's proper behavior under Sections 74 and 77."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-6674ed785a247829af22e22520fa7260&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-52f915665c66fcbe0e7563608cbf7287</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SALE OF MOVABLE PROPERTY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Sale of Movable Property involves transactions where the property can be transported, with specific conditions regarding quantity discrepancies and buyer's acceptance."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9ca3fcb51a635c23cbd4974dd21e277f</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1516 (6)&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1516 (6) includes situations that qualify for divorce when specific conditions are met by the guilty party."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-359c29184e76341f84467fcf371024a6</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;WRONGFUL ACT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A Wrongful Act refers to unlawful conduct that injures another person’s life, body, health, liberty, property, or rights, requiring compensation."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-6674ed785a247829af22e22520fa7260</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SALE OF IMMOVABLE PROPERTY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Sale of Immovable Property involves transactions of real estate where total area specifications impact buyer's options in cases of discrepancies."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9ca3fcb51a635c23cbd4974dd21e277f</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;FEEDBACK COMPONENT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Feedback Component mentions an unrelated fragment possibly indicating a feedback form interaction or administrative action."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-359c29184e76341f84467fcf371024a6</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;STATUTORY PROVISION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A Statutory Provision is a law made to protect individuals, where infringement leading to damage presumes fault in the wrongdoer."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-6674ed785a247829af22e22520fa7260</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;LIABILITY FOR DEFECT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Liability for Defect relates to the seller's responsibility for any impairments in the property which diminish its value or suitability, with certain conditions exempting the seller."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9ca3fcb51a635c23cbd4974dd21e277f</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;ADULTERER&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Adulterer refers to a third party involved in a marital relationship, potentially responsible for causing harm or possessing entitlement implications."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-359c29184e76341f84467fcf371024a6</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;COMPENSATION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Compensation involves making amends for injury or damage caused, discussed in legal terms regarding when it is owed."&lt;SEP&gt;"Compensation is the payment or restitution for damages or breach of the betrothal agreement."&lt;SEP&gt;"Compensation is the repayment required for damages caused by a wrongful act, as determined by the court."&lt;SEP&gt;"Compensation refers to reimbursement or payment given to a person for loss, damage, or in return for services rendered."&lt;SEP&gt;"Compensation refers to the payment made for damages or sacrifice of land utility resulting from actions like providing passage or allowing utility installation."&lt;SEP&gt;"Compensation refers to the payment made to cover damage or expenses incurred in relation to the pledged property."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-6674ed785a247829af22e22520fa7260&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-94b10cff960517b2c4edf0f1af70e53c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b3971476de4ec8b22a6311d4e55caca0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-32f0865d6629c46fe99f13ae20d441f7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5e64aa2c471a9da88427c4d97b3a6c7c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fb415930f5508ba24d6b39a4a2237451</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;TRANSPORTATION COSTS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Transportation Costs refer to the financial responsibility of transporting property to a location other than the place of performance, usually borne by the buyer."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9ca3fcb51a635c23cbd4974dd21e277f</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1598/39&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1598/39 refers to supplementary legal provisions applicable to claims for living allowances during divorce."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-359c29184e76341f84467fcf371024a6</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;EMPLOYEE AND THIRD PERSON&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"When an Employee commits a wrongful act affecting a third person, the employer is responsible for compensation but can seek reimbursement from the Employee."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-6674ed785a247829af22e22520fa7260</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECURITY FOR PAYMENT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Security for Payment involves providing collateral or assurance to the seller ensuring the buyer fulfills the payment obligation for the property."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9ca3fcb51a635c23cbd4974dd21e277f</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1598/40&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1598/40 outlines additional considerations under the legal framework for managing divorce-related financial claims."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-359c29184e76341f84467fcf371024a6</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;GUARDIAN&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A Guardian is a legal representative appointed to manage the affairs and property of a ward, with specific duties and obligations defined by law."&lt;SEP&gt;"A Guardian is a person legally appointed to manage the affairs of someone who is unable to manage their own affairs."&lt;SEP&gt;"A Guardian is a person responsible for the supervision of incapacitated individuals and may be liable for wrongful acts committed during supervision."&lt;SEP&gt;"A Guardian is a person who is legally responsible for the care of someone unable to manage their own affairs, such as a minor or a person of unsound mind."&lt;SEP&gt;"A Guardian is an individual appointed to manage the affairs and property of a minor, especially when parental power ceases or is otherwise required by the court."&lt;SEP&gt;"A Guardian is an individual legally responsible for managing the affairs of a minor or an incompetent person."&lt;SEP&gt;"A Guardian is an individual who has rights and duties regarding the care of a minor or incompetent person, similar to a Controller of Property but without the necessity of appointment by a will."&lt;SEP&gt;"A Guardian is appointed by the Court to oversee the welfare of a person adjudged incompetent."&lt;SEP&gt;"A guardian is a person appointed to manage the affairs of a minor or someone incapable of managing their own affairs."&lt;SEP&gt;"A guardian is an individual appointed to manage the affairs of a person who is unable to do so themselves, relevant in ratifying voidable acts."&lt;SEP&gt;"An individual legally appointed to manage the affairs of a minor or an incompetent person when parents are not available."&lt;SEP&gt;"Guardian is a person appointed to care for an adopted child in the event of a child adopter's death or adoption dissolution, unless the court decides otherwise."&lt;SEP&gt;"Guardian refers to an individual appointed to manage the affairs and welfare of someone deemed incapable, particularly in cases of insanity or incompetence."&lt;SEP&gt;"Guardian is a person who may be responsible for the care of a child and can be held liable for harm caused by the child according to the law."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9fb8ecc1d3b7f08bd11bfbe372805373&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d45ed62b6b0bfc44f2c1ae4fe430c9c0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6674ed785a247829af22e22520fa7260&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6158dfc7a7c5c354484d988186bd2709&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-42fad725aa98ee40547f7a36e0de09d6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4e5197de768063837bf5a455698da0aa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6f29560483a94cdf780f52af44990dd1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d82b5d0a885fc8b96ea11f873f6f0c0a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e6503e3e2e955a071268b1be787bc7d1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9926eb44610bf5182e4fad6451742c28&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d10f80809fc56f611edbadcb4809bc4e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-553b3730ac4ba8b3212a7d230dbc31ad&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7770756870427eb344039070455f889c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-99e04c388a7385a4978847a999d423f1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;DEFICIENCY OR EXCESS IN PROPERTY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Deficiency or Excess in Property involves instances where the delivered property is less or more than contracted, granting the buyer certain rights to accept or reject."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9ca3fcb51a635c23cbd4974dd21e277f</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1598/41&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1598/41 provides further legal guidance on the right to claim living allowances and related divorced financial settlements."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-359c29184e76341f84467fcf371024a6</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;CONTRACTOR&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A Contractor is an independent party hired to perform work, with limited liability placed on the employer unless specific faults are proven."&lt;SEP&gt;"The contractor is responsible for performing work as per the contract but is not liable for delays or defects under certain conditions."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-6674ed785a247829af22e22520fa7260&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7c177d209afa32287351a7f88d669f7a</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;LIABILITY FOR EVICTION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Liability for Eviction pertains to the seller's responsibility if the buyer's peaceful possession of the property is disturbed by third-party claims existing at the time of sale."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9ca3fcb51a635c23cbd4974dd21e277f</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE FOUNDATION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Foundation represents any legal entity established to pursue specific objectives, which must comply with its regulations and legal requirements, and is subject to oversight by the Registrar."&lt;SEP&gt;"The foundation is a juristic entity subject to dissolution and liquidation under specific legal conditions."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-a8f2d8db15aae9334e2b0c36d4ea99c8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-86deb2357b8656ccf8680e27cbac71ec</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;INCAPACITATED PERSON&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"An Incapacitated Person may be liable for their wrongful acts despite minority or unsound mind, with possible joint liability on their guardian or parents."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-6674ed785a247829af22e22520fa7260</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;JOINT LEGAL ACTION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Joint Legal Action allows the buyer to summon the seller to participate in a court case involving a third party's disturbance of the buyer's possession of the property."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9ca3fcb51a635c23cbd4974dd21e277f</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE MINISTRY OF INTERIOR&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Ministry of Interior oversees the execution of relevant provisions and appoints the registrar, also issues Ministerial Regulations."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-86deb2357b8656ccf8680e27cbac71ec</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;ANIMAL OWNER&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"An Animal Owner is liable for damages caused by their animals unless proper care is proven."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-6674ed785a247829af22e22520fa7260</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;BANKRUPTCY OF THE BUYER&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Bankruptcy of the Buyer refers to the financial insolvency of the buyer, affecting the seller's rights to retain or demand security on the property."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9ca3fcb51a635c23cbd4974dd21e277f</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;PARTNERS WITH LIMITED LIABILITY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Partners with limited liability are individuals in a partnership whose financial liability is limited to the amount they invested."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-fd4f265f6be599f877d85099036f52dc</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;ESTATE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A legal entity comprising all the assets, rights, and obligations of the deceased person, to be managed, settled, and distributed according to law and the will."&lt;SEP&gt;"An estate encompasses all the property, rights, and obligations of a deceased person, which are subject to succession."&lt;SEP&gt;"Estate encompasses the properties, rights, duties, and liabilities of a deceased person that transfer to the heirs, subject to legal provisions."&lt;SEP&gt;"The estate refers to the collection of assets and liabilities left behind by a deceased person, subject to partition among heirs."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-a7a64e6f6e939634750f7cc32da6d781&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d021e006377bbbff9ec8f8e90f54f2a1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-63871d590b9819463b4e112a2305a28f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e6503e3e2e955a071268b1be787bc7d1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;BUYER&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Buyer is the person in a contract of sale who agrees to pay a price for ownership of property."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Buyer is the party in a sale contract who acquires property from the seller and has certain rights and duties, such as taking delivery and paying the agreed price."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-94b10cff960517b2c4edf0f1af70e53c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-33f27ab34f7ee4094ebd4f5171db4171</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE KINGDOM&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Kingdom refers to Thailand, within which the Criminal Code and associated legal processes are enforced."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Kingdom refers to the geographical location where the company's registered office is situated."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Kingdom refers to the jurisdiction of Thailand where the provisions of the law, including punishment for crimes, apply."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Kingdom refers to the jurisdiction or country where these laws and legal codes are applicable, likely Thailand."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-fd4f265f6be599f877d85099036f52dc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4d20d8c7e43c4c0033ebd04d8b30c380&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bf2e9ba1c433d67ab7eef97426e05cd4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-78de612c5be2681a856b09899b977bd3</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;CO-HEIRS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Co-heirs are individuals who share a common inheritance from a deceased person and have joint rights and obligations regarding the estate until its partition."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-63871d590b9819463b4e112a2305a28f</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SELLER&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Seller is the person in a contract of sale responsible for transferring property ownership to the buyer."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Seller is the party in a sale contract responsible for transferring property to the buyer and may have liability for eviction or defects."&lt;SEP&gt;"The seller is the owner of the property being auctioned, with conditions under which they may or may not bid."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-43ec5cbbc3a7ffd98dbfc1b8a6281865&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-94b10cff960517b2c4edf0f1af70e53c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-33f27ab34f7ee4094ebd4f5171db4171</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;PROMOTERS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Promoters are individuals who initiate the formation of a limited company by subscribing their names to a memorandum."&lt;SEP&gt;"Promoters are the individuals who initiate the formation of the company and are responsible for organizing the statutory meeting and initial operations."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-d67f818d289a7a42a391ffd601a49336&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fd4f265f6be599f877d85099036f52dc</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;PARTITION OF AN ESTATE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Partition of an estate involves dividing an estate among heirs, covered in Sections 1745 to 1755 of the Civil and Commercial Code."&lt;SEP&gt;"Partition of an estate is the process by which the common estate is divided among co-heirs, either physically or through the sale of assets and distribution of proceeds."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-5429b702233c5b142e4f7e7899dffac1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-63871d590b9819463b4e112a2305a28f</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;EVICTION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Eviction refers to the event where a buyer loses possession of property due to superior claims by a third party."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-33f27ab34f7ee4094ebd4f5171db4171</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1091&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1091 allows limited liability partners to transfer their shares without consent from other partners."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 1091 refers to a legal clause regarding the transferability of shares by partners with limited liability without needing consent from other partners."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-855466dea5984defb1f279860dbf5504&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fd4f265f6be599f877d85099036f52dc</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;RIGHTS OF CREDITORS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Rights of creditors pertain to the entitlements creditors have concerning repayment from the estate of a deceased person, before any partition among heirs."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-63871d590b9819463b4e112a2305a28f</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;IMMOVABLE PROPERTY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Immovable Property includes real estate like land and buildings, which are subject to particular rules and ownership rights."&lt;SEP&gt;"Immovable Property refers to property that is fixed to a location, such as land or buildings, which can be subject to preferential rights."&lt;SEP&gt;"Immovable Property refers to real estate or property that cannot be moved, such as land or buildings involved in a sale with specific rights and liabilities."&lt;SEP&gt;"Immovable properties refer to fixed pieces of real estate, such as land or buildings, which are involved in legal scenarios such as sales and securities."&lt;SEP&gt;"Immovable property includes land and things permanently affixed to it, along with associated real rights."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-86deb2357b8656ccf8680e27cbac71ec&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-23624fb7fffe655b4b7087bd796a908a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0ffc320382a3c1523b402789d6bfce44&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-33f27ab34f7ee4094ebd4f5171db4171&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-880c1ecd6c4ca0a05ce8398767d6a999</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;STATE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
      <data key="d1">"State refers to the government or national authority that owns and regulates public domain properties, making them inalienable except through special law or Royal Decree."&lt;SEP&gt;"State refers to the governmental authority that receives wasteland and other lands that have reverted or been surrendered according to land law."&lt;SEP&gt;"The State refers to the government entity that receives the remaining assets of an association if no transferee is designated."&lt;SEP&gt;"The State refers to the government, which may inherit property if there are no Statutory Heirs or effective will."&lt;SEP&gt;"The state refers to the governmental entity that receives the estate in the absence of statutory heirs, legatees, or foundation creation under a will."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-182a2b244fdc4ad235c762ab46288dca&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e69f756c60167e54cbfb8769b0011720&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-63871d590b9819463b4e112a2305a28f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-553b3730ac4ba8b3212a7d230dbc31ad&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-880c1ecd6c4ca0a05ce8398767d6a999</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;RIGHT OF REDEMPTION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Right of Redemption is a contractual term allowing the original seller to repurchase or reclaim the sold property under specific conditions or timeframes."&lt;SEP&gt;"Right of Redemption is a legal provision allowing individuals to reclaim ownership of property by meeting certain conditions."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-ad85db58921b57d9188908867cdfdeba&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-33f27ab34f7ee4094ebd4f5171db4171</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1092&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1092 outlines the conditions under which a limited partnership is not dissolved, such as the death or incapacity of a partner with limited liability."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 1092 states that a limited partnership is not dissolved due to the death, bankruptcy, or incapacitation of a limited liability partner unless otherwise specified in the contract."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-855466dea5984defb1f279860dbf5504&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fd4f265f6be599f877d85099036f52dc</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1745 TO 1755&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"These sections of legal texts outline specific laws related to the partition of an estate, liability for eviction, vacant estates, and applicable prescription periods for legal actions."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-63871d590b9819463b4e112a2305a28f</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;NON-LIABILITY CLAUSE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Non-Liability Clause is a contractual agreement where the seller attempts to limit liability for defects or eviction, not excluding liability for known or concealed issues."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-33f27ab34f7ee4094ebd4f5171db4171</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1093&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1093 outlines the transition of partnership status to heirs if a limited liability partner dies."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 1093 specifies that when a partner with limited liability dies, their heirs become partners unless otherwise stated in the contract."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-855466dea5984defb1f279860dbf5504&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fd4f265f6be599f877d85099036f52dc</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1094&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1094 mandates that if a partner with limited liability becomes bankrupt, their share must be sold as part of the bankruptcy assets."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-fd4f265f6be599f877d85099036f52dc</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;LEGATEES&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Legatees are individuals or entities designated to receive specific assets from an estate according to a will."&lt;SEP&gt;"Legatees are individuals who are entitled to inherit property or specific items bequeathed to them in a will."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-a7a64e6f6e939634750f7cc32da6d781&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-63871d590b9819463b4e112a2305a28f</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;PRICE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Price represents the monetary value agreed upon by buyers and sellers for the sale of property, which can be predetermined or reasonable depending on the contract."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-33f27ab34f7ee4094ebd4f5171db4171</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1095&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1095 concerns the rights of creditors of a limited partnership regarding actions against partners with limited liability."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-fd4f265f6be599f877d85099036f52dc</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;DE CUJUS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"De Cujus refers to the deceased individual whose estate is subject to administration and distribution among heirs and creditors."&lt;SEP&gt;"De cujus is a legal term referring to the deceased individual whose estate is subject to inheritance and distribution."&lt;SEP&gt;"De cujus refers to the person who has died and whose estate is being discussed in terms of inheritance distribution."&lt;SEP&gt;"The term 'De Cujus' refers to the deceased person whose estate is being distributed through succession."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-a7a64e6f6e939634750f7cc32da6d781&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-82d56e3add17387eb012a80a933cb63c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d021e006377bbbff9ec8f8e90f54f2a1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-63871d590b9819463b4e112a2305a28f</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;REDEMPTION PERIOD&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Redemption Period is the timeframe within which the right of redemption can be exercised, typically ten years for immovable and three years for movable properties."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-33f27ab34f7ee4094ebd4f5171db4171</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1096&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1096 defines a limited company and the nature of shareholder liability."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-fd4f265f6be599f877d85099036f52dc</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;EVICTION COMPENSATION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Eviction compensation pertains to the obligation of co-heirs to compensate an heir who loses their allotted property due to eviction under certain conditions."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-63871d590b9819463b4e112a2305a28f</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE LETTER&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Letter refers to the individual or entity leasing immovable property, receiving security money, and having certain preferential rights."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-23624fb7fffe655b4b7087bd796a908a</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1101&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1101 discusses the potential for directors of a limited company to have unlimited liability and the requirements for such cases."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-fd4f265f6be599f877d85099036f52dc</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;PRESCRIPTION PERIOD&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Prescription period refers to the legally defined time frame within which an action concerning inheritance or legacy must be initiated after the death of the de cujus."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-63871d590b9819463b4e112a2305a28f</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE PROPRIETOR&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Proprietor is the owner of an inn, hotel, or similar establishment, with preferential rights over lodging and services provided."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-23624fb7fffe655b4b7087bd796a908a</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1102&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1102 states that no public invitation to subscribe for shares should be made."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-fd4f265f6be599f877d85099036f52dc</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THAI GOVERNMENT GAZETTE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Thai Government Gazette is an official publication in which legal texts, including the Thai Civil Code, are published and hold legal force."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Thai Government Gazette is the official publication for legal texts and announcements in Thailand, ensuring legal force of documents in their original Thai script."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-8ce6f1498128f5fc6034c5e3b827db4f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-63871d590b9819463b4e112a2305a28f</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE TRAVELER OR GUEST&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Traveler or Guest is an individual receiving lodgings and services at an inn, whose property could be subject to preferential rights."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-23624fb7fffe655b4b7087bd796a908a</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE TESTATOR&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Testator is an individual who creates a will to dispose of their property and can make specifications regarding legacies and foundations."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-a2aa959400bcd6663682a867aebf2801</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE CARRIER&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Carrier is responsible for transporting passengers or goods, holding a preferential right over carriage charges and related expenses."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-23624fb7fffe655b4b7087bd796a908a</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;CREDITORS OF THE TESTATOR&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Creditors of the Testator are individuals or entities that are owed debts by the testator and can challenge testamentary dispositions that prejudice them."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-a2aa959400bcd6663682a867aebf2801</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;WARD&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Ward is an individual under guardianship who relies on a guardian to manage their financial and personal affairs."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-d10f80809fc56f611edbadcb4809bc4e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE PLEDGEE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A Pledgee is an entity involved in holding goods as security for a debt, whose enforcement rights can be compared to those with preferential rights."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-23624fb7fffe655b4b7087bd796a908a</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 110 OF THE CODE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 110 of the Code lays out provisions regarding the creation or appropriation of property for specific purposes within a legal framework."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-a2aa959400bcd6663682a867aebf2801</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THAI GOVERNMENT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Thai Government is responsible for making legal requests in cases prosecuted overseas and is involved in the legal procedures within the Kingdom."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Thai Government is the central authority of Thailand, involved in the enforcement of laws and regulations."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Thai Government is the governing body of Thailand responsible for enforcing laws, including those detailed in the Criminal Code Amendment Act."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Thai Government issues or guarantees bonds that guardians may invest in on behalf of their wards."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-d10f80809fc56f611edbadcb4809bc4e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-526a0b152c10330561e4c72c14e89416&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-78de612c5be2681a856b09899b977bd3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e8a12bcf29dd0e194c7a3e4a71523199</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;PRESERVATION OF A MOVABLE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"This refers to the efforts and expenses incurred to maintain the condition and value of a movable asset, which grant preferential rights."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-23624fb7fffe655b4b7087bd796a908a</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 114 OF THE CODE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 114 of the Code involves the process of authorizing a foundation's creation as a juristic person by the government."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-a2aa959400bcd6663682a867aebf2801</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECURITY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Security refers to a guarantee, often financial, provided by a property owner to safeguard commitments associated with property charges."&lt;SEP&gt;"Security refers to an asset or collateral that ensures the fulfillment of an obligation, often mentioned in the context of juristic acts."&lt;SEP&gt;"Security refers to the requirement for guardians to provide assurance for the proper management and return of the ward's property."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-d42bf94e7a02b8cef96bd3ed9bc3ceaf&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d82b5d0a885fc8b96ea11f873f6f0c0a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d10f80809fc56f611edbadcb4809bc4e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SALE OF A MOVABLE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Sale of a Movable refers to transactions involving movable property, where preferential rights exist for the price and interest of the sold item."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-23624fb7fffe655b4b7087bd796a908a</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE WILL&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Will is a legal document specifying the disposal of a person's property and their intentions for legacy distribution and foundation creation."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-a2aa959400bcd6663682a867aebf2801</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;INVENTORY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Inventory is a detailed list of the ward's property that the guardian must compile and submit to The Court for approval."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-d10f80809fc56f611edbadcb4809bc4e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SUPPLY OF SEEDS, YOUNG PLANTS, OR MANURE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"This involves provisioning agricultural inputs, granting preferential rights over the produce grown using these inputs."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-23624fb7fffe655b4b7087bd796a908a</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;CHARGE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A Charge is a legal obligation or claim on an Immersed Property benefitting a beneficiary by granting certain uses or periodic performances."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-d42bf94e7a02b8cef96bd3ed9bc3ceaf</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1479&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1479 discusses legal provisions requiring written consent for certain acts between spouses."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9acfb88a2614f5c4b2f078b95a067e71</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;DISSOLUTION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Dissolution is the process of legally ending or dissolving a partnership."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-81d63dbc17e3f3707788a6e2552b764c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1399&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Legal guidance on servitude extinction via a ten-year period of non-usage."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-0e69519b80d6cad28fe98f2e9235bd60</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1373&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1373 states that the person listed in a land register is presumed to have possessory rights."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-bb67153d31d305a18c3208696a748f1b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1400&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Outlines servitude reviving conditions when it benefits the dominant property again, unless time lapse criteria aren't met."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-0e69519b80d6cad28fe98f2e9235bd60</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;BENEFICIARY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"ROLE"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A Beneficiary is an individual or entity entitled to benefits from a charge on an immersed property, receiving either periodic performances or specific uses."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-d42bf94e7a02b8cef96bd3ed9bc3ceaf</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1480&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1480 provides regulations for managing Sin Somros jointly or with the consent of the other spouse."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9acfb88a2614f5c4b2f078b95a067e71</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;FINANCIAL YEAR&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The financial year is a one-year period used for accounting purposes and preparing financial statements of a partnership."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-81d63dbc17e3f3707788a6e2552b764c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;PENALTY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Penalty refers to a sum or other consequence imposed due to the debtor's failure to perform obligations as promised."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-5352b86091aaab4f6715c44efa017b05</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;INSURANCE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Insurance is a financial protection purchased to safeguard a property against potential losses, which must be maintained by the usufructuary."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-d42bf94e7a02b8cef96bd3ed9bc3ceaf</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1481&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1481 outlines the limitations on disposing of Sin Somros by will."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9acfb88a2614f5c4b2f078b95a067e71</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SCOPE OF AUTHORITY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Scope of authority refers to the range of actions and decisions managing partners are empowered to make as outlined in the partnership agreement."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-81d63dbc17e3f3707788a6e2552b764c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1401&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A rule permitting servitude acquisition by prescription, referring to other related legal provisions."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-0e69519b80d6cad28fe98f2e9235bd60</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1575&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1575 refers to a legal provision outlining situations where the interests of those exercising parental power may conflict with the interests of a minor and requires the intervention of the court to resolve such conflicts."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9926eb44610bf5182e4fad6451742c28</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;MINOR&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A Minor is an individual under a certain legal age, requiring consent from specified guardians or parents to engage in betrothal legal agreements."&lt;SEP&gt;"A Minor is an individual under the age of majority who may require a guardian or person exercising parental power for legal and property management decisions."&lt;SEP&gt;"A Minor is an individual under the legal age of full capacity, for whom a Controller of Property may be appointed to manage their property."&lt;SEP&gt;"A Minor refers to an individual under legal age who may have claims affected by prescription rules."&lt;SEP&gt;"A minor is a person under the age of legal majority who has restricted capacity to engage in juridical acts."&lt;SEP&gt;"A minor is an individual under the age of legal adulthood who cannot undertake certain legal actions without consent."&lt;SEP&gt;"Minor denotes an individual who is not yet of legal age and requires a guardian or parent to manage their affairs."&lt;SEP&gt;"Minor refers to individuals under a specified age who have specific legal capacities and rights."&lt;SEP&gt;"Minor refers to individuals under the legal age of adulthood whose domicile is aligned with their legal representative or parental figure."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-d45ed62b6b0bfc44f2c1ae4fe430c9c0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4e5197de768063837bf5a455698da0aa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-42fad725aa98ee40547f7a36e0de09d6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d42bf94e7a02b8cef96bd3ed9bc3ceaf&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-933d505d06605d728d8a7325e6245238&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-553b3730ac4ba8b3212a7d230dbc31ad&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9926eb44610bf5182e4fad6451742c28&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-99e04c388a7385a4978847a999d423f1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4c5aad3770b3111c6e3b4171b1b6cb5c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1482&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1482 explains the rights of the non-manager spouse to manage household affairs."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9acfb88a2614f5c4b2f078b95a067e71</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;LIQUIDATOR&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A Liquidator is responsible for winding up the affairs of a dissolved partnership or company and submitting liquidation returns to the Registrar."&lt;SEP&gt;"An individual, potentially a partner with limited liability, appointed to settle the accounts and bring a partnership to an end."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-855466dea5984defb1f279860dbf5504&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-691e23128e3c79c43c11b76dcdb0c630</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1402&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Details the right of habitation allowing a person to occupy a building rent-free."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-0e69519b80d6cad28fe98f2e9235bd60</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1576&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1576 outlines the interests of persons exercising parental power, particularly in relation to partnerships and business interests, where conflicts of interest with a minor may arise and require court intervention."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9926eb44610bf5182e4fad6451742c28</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;GOOD FAITH&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Good Faith refers to the expectation that individuals act with honesty and integrity, particularly in exercising rights and fulfilling obligations."&lt;SEP&gt;"Good faith refers to honest intent in legal conduct, affecting liabilities and restitution obligations."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-fcc1f7edc6fff66f0cf31baecb707aad&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-defdbb96b53889e12ccecd5ae2a14554</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1483&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1483 allows a spouse to request a court order to prevent undue loss in the management of Sin Somros."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9acfb88a2614f5c4b2f078b95a067e71</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;MANAGING PARTNER&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A Managing Partner is responsible for overseeing the operations and management of a partnership and retains liability if the partnership is struck off."&lt;SEP&gt;"A managing partner is an individual responsible for overseeing the operations and management of a partnership, often with authority to make decisions on behalf of the partnership."&lt;SEP&gt;"A partner responsible for the daily management of a limited partnership, who must handle specific processes in case of resignation or change."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-30e7eef2c9f266924b324154eca432d3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-691e23128e3c79c43c11b76dcdb0c630&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-855466dea5984defb1f279860dbf5504</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1403&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Regulations regarding creating a right of habitation for specific timeframes or the grantee's life, including renewal conditions."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-0e69519b80d6cad28fe98f2e9235bd60</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1577&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1577 discusses the transfer of property to minors by means of legacy or gift, requiring management by a designated person other than the one exercising parental power, as per legal stipulations."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9926eb44610bf5182e4fad6451742c28</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;FORCE MAJEURE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Force Majeure is an event characterized by its unavoidable nature, where even appropriate preventative actions cannot avert its consequences."&lt;SEP&gt;"Force Majeure refers to extraordinary events or circumstances beyond human control that exempt the carrier from liability for loss, damage, or delay."&lt;SEP&gt;"Force Majeure refers to unforeseeable circumstances that prevent fulfilling a contract, such as natural disasters, which might affect deposit agreements."&lt;SEP&gt;"Force Majeure refers to unforeseen and unavoidable events that prevent the creditor from taking action to interrupt prescription."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-d45ed62b6b0bfc44f2c1ae4fe430c9c0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7289405ac6638bb4a476489ae0c1b33d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-629bbfda7f476a27cd4f982000bd902b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-defdbb96b53889e12ccecd5ae2a14554</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1484&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1484 details circumstances under which a court order can change the management of Sin Somros."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 1484 discusses the division of Sin Somros by operation of law, particularly upon adjudication of bankruptcy or other legal actions."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9acfb88a2614f5c4b2f078b95a067e71&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2f3971fdef62800a7dabb59d8dfbd427</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;MANAGING OFFICER&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A Managing Officer is responsible for the daily operations of a company and may face liabilities if the company loses its juristic status."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-691e23128e3c79c43c11b76dcdb0c630</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1404&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"States that the right of habitation cannot be transferred or inherited."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-0e69519b80d6cad28fe98f2e9235bd60</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1578&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1578 details the procedure for the transfer of property and account documentation from the person who exercised parental power to a minor when they become sui juris or to a guardian under other circumstances."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9926eb44610bf5182e4fad6451742c28</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 4&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 4 outlines the requirement for law to be applied in cases within its provisions and provides guidance on cases where no direct provision is applicable."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-defdbb96b53889e12ccecd5ae2a14554</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1484/1&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1484/1 allows changes or revocation of court orders regarding Sin Somros management powers."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9acfb88a2614f5c4b2f078b95a067e71</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;BUSINESS OPERATION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Business Operation refers to the day-to-day activities undertaken by a partnership or company to generate revenue and profit."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-691e23128e3c79c43c11b76dcdb0c630</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1405&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Allows family and household members to reside with the grantee unless limited by the grantor’s specification."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-0e69519b80d6cad28fe98f2e9235bd60</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1579&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1579 addresses the property management and transfer in cases where one spouse dies and the surviving spouse remarries, involving specific legal requirements and possible court intervention."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9926eb44610bf5182e4fad6451742c28</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 5&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 5 emphasizes the principle that every person must act in good faith when exercising rights and fulfilling obligations."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-defdbb96b53889e12ccecd5ae2a14554</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1485&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1485 allows a spouse to apply for managerial rights over a particular Sin Somros for greater benefit."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9acfb88a2614f5c4b2f078b95a067e71</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;LIQUIDATION PROCESS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Liquidation Process is the legal procedure of winding up a company's or partnership's affairs, distributing assets, and settling liabilities."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-691e23128e3c79c43c11b76dcdb0c630</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1406&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Permits grantees to utilize land products necessary for household needs except if restricted by the grantor."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-0e69519b80d6cad28fe98f2e9235bd60</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1580&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1580 involves the certification of property management by the person exercising parental right or the guardian to a minor who has reached the age of majority."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9926eb44610bf5182e4fad6451742c28</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 6&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 6 presumes every person is acting in good faith, establishing a foundational principle in legal interpretation."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-defdbb96b53889e12ccecd5ae2a14554</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1486&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1486 addresses the court's responsibility to notify the Marriage Registrar after legal decisions."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9acfb88a2614f5c4b2f078b95a067e71</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;FOUNDATION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A Foundation is an entity that can be created by a will and must be authorized as a juristic person by the government."&lt;SEP&gt;"A foundation is a juristic person that can be created through registration following the death of an applicant or via testamentary disposition."&lt;SEP&gt;"Foundations are organizations consisting of property appropriated for public charity or other public benefits, registered under specific legal provisions."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-faf5131f5750e774e912cf9b536d485e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-46940167ee3908fb358c9a82647ea322&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a2aa959400bcd6663682a867aebf2801</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1407&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Stipulates that the grantor is not obligated for maintenance, nor reimburses improvements undertaken by the grantee."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-0e69519b80d6cad28fe98f2e9235bd60</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;PERSON EXERCISING PARENTAL POWER&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A Person Exercising Parental Power is an individual, typically a parent or appointed guardian, who holds legal rights and responsibilities over a minor's well-being and property."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9926eb44610bf5182e4fad6451742c28</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 7&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 7 establishes the interest rate at seven and a half percent per year when not fixed by law or juristic act."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-defdbb96b53889e12ccecd5ae2a14554</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1487&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1487 specifies conditions under which spouses can seize each other's property."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9acfb88a2614f5c4b2f078b95a067e71</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE MINISTER OF INTERIOR&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Minister of Interior is a government official responsible for overseeing the execution of regulations related to associations, and has the power to appoint the Registrar and issue regulations."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-182a2b244fdc4ad235c762ab46288dca</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1408&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Requires the grantee to return habitation property to the grantor upon expiry of rights."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-0e69519b80d6cad28fe98f2e9235bd60</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;ESTATE CREDITORS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Creditors are individuals or entities to whom the estate owes debts and are entitled to be paid from the estate's property."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-89b8c822a665cc12b23359be3cc927d4</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 8&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 8 defines 'Force Majeure' as an event whose occurrence or harmful result could not be prevented."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-defdbb96b53889e12ccecd5ae2a14554</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1488&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1488 discusses how obligations incurred by one spouse are to be met using Sin Suan Tua and Sin Somros."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9acfb88a2614f5c4b2f078b95a067e71</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE GOVERNMENT GAZETTE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Government Gazette is the official public record where announcements, such as the dissolution of associations, are published by the Registrar."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-182a2b244fdc4ad235c762ab46288dca</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1409&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Application of duties and liabilities from another legal code section concerning hirers."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-0e69519b80d6cad28fe98f2e9235bd60</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1721&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1721 details the conditions under which an estate administrator can receive remuneration from the estate."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-89b8c822a665cc12b23359be3cc927d4</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 9&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 9 specifies requirements for documents where a signature is necessary, including acceptable alternatives to a traditional signature."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-defdbb96b53889e12ccecd5ae2a14554</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1489&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1489 determines how common debts of both spouses are satisfied."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9acfb88a2614f5c4b2f078b95a067e71</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;MINISTERIAL REGULATIONS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Ministerial Regulations are established by the Minister of Interior to manage foundations and their registrations, including fee structures."&lt;SEP&gt;"Ministerial Regulations are rules issued by the Minister of Interior for the application, registration, inspection, and liquidation of associations."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-182a2b244fdc4ad235c762ab46288dca&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-86deb2357b8656ccf8680e27cbac71ec</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;TITLE V - HABITATION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Outlines the rights and obligations related to habitation agreements between grantors and grantees."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-0e69519b80d6cad28fe98f2e9235bd60</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1722&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1722 restricts estate administrators from engaging in juristic acts that conflict with the estate's interests unless permitted by will or Court."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-89b8c822a665cc12b23359be3cc927d4</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THAI LANGUAGE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Thai Language is specified as the governing language for documents executed in multiple languages if discrepancies cannot be resolved."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-defdbb96b53889e12ccecd5ae2a14554</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 746&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 746 describes the requirement for registration by a competent official to modify a mortgage or obligation and its enforceability against third parties."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-f92e53c4b928412441b1d00eeb6aab74</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;LIQUIDATION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Liquidation refers to the process of winding up an association's affairs, distributing its assets according to the law."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-182a2b244fdc4ad235c762ab46288dca</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;TITLE VI - SUPERFICIES&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Describes regulations surrounding the right to own buildings or structures on another's land."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-0e69519b80d6cad28fe98f2e9235bd60</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1723&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1723 mandates personal action by estate administrators unless authorized to act through an agent by will or Court order."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-89b8c822a665cc12b23359be3cc927d4</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 10&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 10 provides guidance on interpreting clauses in documents, favoring interpretations that give effect rather than none."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-defdbb96b53889e12ccecd5ae2a14554</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 747&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 747 explains a pledge as a contract where the pledgor delivers movable property to a pledgee as security for an obligation."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-f92e53c4b928412441b1d00eeb6aab74</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;CHARITY PURPOSES&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Charity purposes are objectives aimed at promoting the welfare of others, especially through donations of money or resources."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-182a2b244fdc4ad235c762ab46288dca</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE PRINCIPAL&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Principal is the individual for whom the affairs are being managed without their explicit consent or knowledge."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-fb415930f5508ba24d6b39a4a2237451</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1724&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1724 binds heirs to the acts of the administrator within their authority, excluding acts benefiting the administrator personally."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-89b8c822a665cc12b23359be3cc927d4</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 11&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 11 prescribes that in cases of doubt, interpretation should favor the party who incurs the obligation."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-defdbb96b53889e12ccecd5ae2a14554</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 748&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 748 outlines the pledge as security for obligation performance and related accessories like interest and compensation."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-f92e53c4b928412441b1d00eeb6aab74</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;TITLE II&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Title II refers to a section of legal text dealing with inheritance laws, detailing how inheritances are divided among descendants and other involved parties."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-82d56e3add17387eb012a80a933cb63c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;MANAGEMENT OF AFFAIRS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Management of Affairs refers to the actions undertaken by an unauthorized individual to manage another person's affairs for their benefit."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-fb415930f5508ba24d6b39a4a2237451</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1725&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1725 obligates estate administrators to notify interested persons of testamentary dispositions within a reasonable time."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-89b8c822a665cc12b23359be3cc927d4</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;NATURAL PERSONS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Natural Persons are defined as individuals with rights and obligations, including specifics about personality beginning with birth and ending with death."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-defdbb96b53889e12ccecd5ae2a14554</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 752&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 752 describes how a pledged instrument issued to a named person must be stated on the instrument and notified to the debtor or third persons."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-f92e53c4b928412441b1d00eeb6aab74</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;DESCENDANTS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Descendants are individuals who are the children or further lineage of a deceased person and are entitled to inherit based on varying conditions and degrees of relation."&lt;SEP&gt;"Descendants refer to individuals who are the offspring or lineal descendants of a person, eligible for inheritance."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-82d56e3add17387eb012a80a933cb63c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c2ac78f2ab241f4845c5c94a44c0ffb6</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;AFFAIR&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"An Affair in this context refers to the personal or business matters or activities being managed by another person without a formal mandate."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-fb415930f5508ba24d6b39a4a2237451</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1726&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1726 allows for the majority voting among administrators or Court decision-making in case of disagreements, unless otherwise specified by will."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-89b8c822a665cc12b23359be3cc927d4</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 395&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 395 outlines the obligations of a person managing another's affair without a formal mandate, emphasizing acting in the principal's interest."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-fb415930f5508ba24d6b39a4a2237451</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 15&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 15 indicates when personality begins and ends, granting rights to children en ventre sa mère if born alive."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-defdbb96b53889e12ccecd5ae2a14554</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 755&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 755 stipulates that a pledged right cannot be extinguished or modified without the pledgee's consent."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-f92e53c4b928412441b1d00eeb6aab74</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;CIVIL AND COMMERCIAL CODE BOOK V&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Civil and Commercial Code Book V contains legal provisions, including those related to inheritance and the legal status of spouses."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-82d56e3add17387eb012a80a933cb63c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1727&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1727 allows interested persons to discharge an administrator for neglect or other causes, with Court approval required for administrator resignation."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-89b8c822a665cc12b23359be3cc927d4</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1448&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1448 provides provisions regarding marriage and how a minor attains sui juris status upon marriage."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 1448 sets forth legal conditions under which marriages must comply to avoid being voidable."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 1448 stipulates the minimum age for marriage at seventeen, with court exceptions allowed for younger individuals."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-f3a1cd577a93157d9b1c759e9c604a8c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fc29664ee0997602190bcc550d1eddec&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-defdbb96b53889e12ccecd5ae2a14554</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 757&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 757 indicates that the provisions apply to contracts of pledge with licensed pawnbrokers unless contrary to pawnbroker laws."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-f92e53c4b928412441b1d00eeb6aab74</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SIN DERM&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Sin Derm refers to the separate property of a spouse prior to marriage, which is considered in legal stipulations for compensations if insurance on life exists."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-82d56e3add17387eb012a80a933cb63c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;PUBLIC INTEREST&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Public Interest signifies an affair of general concern or benefit to the community as a whole."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-fb415930f5508ba24d6b39a4a2237451</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1734&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1734 confers the right of estate creditors to be paid only from the property of the estate."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-89b8c822a665cc12b23359be3cc927d4</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 20&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 20 outlines that all offenses punishable by both imprisonment and fine can be addressed by the Court with only the punishment of imprisonment, if deemed advisable."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 20 states that a minor becomes sui juris through completion of twenty years or through lawful marriage."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-edf03699076f42c474bd2d773c684e42&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-defdbb96b53889e12ccecd5ae2a14554</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 758&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 758 grants the pledgee the right to retain pledged property until full obligation and accessory performance is received."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-f92e53c4b928412441b1d00eeb6aab74</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1629&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1629 provides specific conditions and classifications for identifying heirs and determining their shares in inheritance."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 1629 specifies the six classes of statutory heirs and their order of inheritance, including special provisions for surviving spouses."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-82d56e3add17387eb012a80a933cb63c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c2ac78f2ab241f4845c5c94a44c0ffb6</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;LEGAL DUTY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Legal Duty refers to an obligation enforced by law, such as the duty to provide maintenance to others."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-fb415930f5508ba24d6b39a4a2237451</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1736&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1736 states that succession remains under management until all known creditors and legatees are satisfied, allowing necessary steps to manage estate debts."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-89b8c822a665cc12b23359be3cc927d4</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;ADMINISTRATOR&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"An Administrator is appointed to manage the property bequeathed under certain conditions until those conditions are fulfilled."&lt;SEP&gt;"An individual entitled to execute necessary acts of management for an estate under administration. Responsible for collecting debts and managing the estate until all creditors and legatees are satisfied."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-d021e006377bbbff9ec8f8e90f54f2a1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a2aa959400bcd6663682a867aebf2801</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 760&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 760 stipulates that the pledgee is liable for loss or damage to the pledged property if they use it or let third parties have custody."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-f92e53c4b928412441b1d00eeb6aab74</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1635&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1635 outlines how a surviving spouse is entitled to inherit in various scenarios involving other heirs."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-82d56e3add17387eb012a80a933cb63c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;WILLFUL DEFAULT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Willful Default refers to the intentional failure to perform a legal obligation or duty."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-fb415930f5508ba24d6b39a4a2237451</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;ESTATE MANAGEMENT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Estate Management involves overseeing the distribution of assets, satisfying creditors, and ensuring compliance with legal duties, typically by the administrator."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-89b8c822a665cc12b23359be3cc927d4</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;HEIR&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"An Heir is a person designated to receive property through a will and may apply to the court for related legal actions concerning a testamentary disposition."&lt;SEP&gt;"An heir is a person legally entitled to inherit a deceased person's estate."&lt;SEP&gt;"An heir is a person who inherits or is entitled to inherit the property or title of a deceased individual. There are statutory heirs and legatees depending on whether they inherit by law or by will."&lt;SEP&gt;"An individual entitled to a portion of the decedent's estate according to inheritance laws or a will. May be responsible for debts and obligations relative to their share of the estate."&lt;SEP&gt;"The heir is an individual who may ratify a voidable juristic act after the death of the person who committed it, if the right to avoid the act has not been extinguished."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-a2aa959400bcd6663682a867aebf2801&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d82b5d0a885fc8b96ea11f873f6f0c0a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a7a64e6f6e939634750f7cc32da6d781&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-933d505d06605d728d8a7325e6245238&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d021e006377bbbff9ec8f8e90f54f2a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 761&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 761 discusses the appropriation of legal fruits from pledged property by the pledgee towards any interest or principal obligation due."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-f92e53c4b928412441b1d00eeb6aab74</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1636&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1636 provides guidelines on how multiple surviving wives, who gained legal status before certain laws, share inheritance."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-82d56e3add17387eb012a80a933cb63c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;GROSS NEGLIGENCE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Gross Negligence is a severe lack of care that demonstrates a blatant disregard for the safety or rights of others."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-fb415930f5508ba24d6b39a4a2237451</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;RULES ON WITNESSES FOR INVENTORY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Rules regarding who may or may not serve as witnesses during the estate's inventory process, as specific restrictions are articulated in Section 1729."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-89b8c822a665cc12b23359be3cc927d4</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1737&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A specified law section that outlines the enforcement of claims by creditors against heirs before the division of the estate."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-d021e006377bbbff9ec8f8e90f54f2a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;ARREARS OF INTEREST&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Arrears of Interest refers to the overdue interest payments on a mortgage that cannot be enforced for more than five years as per Section 746."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-f92e53c4b928412441b1d00eeb6aab74</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1637&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1637 discusses the entitlement of a surviving spouse to life insurance sums and the responsibilities for compensating shared marital assets, if applicable."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-82d56e3add17387eb012a80a933cb63c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;UNDUE ENRICHMENT PROVISIONS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Undue Enrichment Provisions are legal guidelines determining circumstances when a person must return what they have unjustly acquired from another."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-fb415930f5508ba24d6b39a4a2237451</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 179&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 179 deals with the consequences of fabricating false evidence to mislead investigation officials."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 179 outlines the conditions under which a ratification of a voidable act is considered valid after the grounds of voidability have ceased."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-e417732f0f4e36ea8784fa2cc5dd8a85&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d82b5d0a885fc8b96ea11f873f6f0c0a</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1738&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A specified law section detailing the procedures for creditors to enforce full payment of claims from the estate and the rights of heirs regarding performance."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-d021e006377bbbff9ec8f8e90f54f2a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;COMPETENT OFFICIAL&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A Competent Official is a government authority responsible for authorizing and registering legal property-related contracts."&lt;SEP&gt;"A Competent Official is a person authorized to register performances, modifications, or extinguishers of mortgages to make them enforceable against third parties."&lt;SEP&gt;"A competent official is an authority responsible for registering transactions such as gifts to ensure validity."&lt;SEP&gt;"A competent official is a person who, by virtue of their duties, may acquire private secrets and is regulated under the Criminal Code."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-f92e53c4b928412441b1d00eeb6aab74&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-78127285a70d48835c00c4ab2953f9f8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-43ec5cbbc3a7ffd98dbfc1b8a6281865&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ad85db58921b57d9188908867cdfdeba</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1638&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1638 addresses situations where both spouses have invested in an annuity, outlining compensation rules for common assets used in the investment."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-82d56e3add17387eb012a80a933cb63c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;CERTIFICATES TO BEARER&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Certificates to Bearer represent shares that can be transferred by mere delivery and offer a simplified form of share ownership transfer for fully paid-up shares."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-6cd60bb5f8e5d886648c66def090b185</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 180&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 180 describes penalties for adducing false evidence in court."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 180 specifies actions that, if performed by the entitled person, imply ratification of a voidable act unless stated otherwise."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-e417732f0f4e36ea8784fa2cc5dd8a85&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d82b5d0a885fc8b96ea11f873f6f0c0a</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1739&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A specified law section defining the order of payment for debts due by the estate, including preferential rights of creditors."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-d021e006377bbbff9ec8f8e90f54f2a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;MOVABLE PROPERTY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Movable Property refers to assets that can be moved from one location to another, subject to specific preferential rights as detailed."&lt;SEP&gt;"Movable Property refers to items or assets that can be transferred or delivered, used as security in pledge contracts."&lt;SEP&gt;"Movable Property refers to items that can be moved and are subject to different contractual terms, such as rights of redemption and timelines for retraction."&lt;SEP&gt;"Movable properties consist of items that are not fixed to a location and can be transferred or relocated, often relevant in legal contexts such as preferential rights or pledges."&lt;SEP&gt;"Movable property encompasses all things not classified as immovable, along with associated rights."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-f92e53c4b928412441b1d00eeb6aab74&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-86deb2357b8656ccf8680e27cbac71ec&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-23624fb7fffe655b4b7087bd796a908a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0ffc320382a3c1523b402789d6bfce44&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-33f27ab34f7ee4094ebd4f5171db4171</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1639&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1639 allows descendants of a deceased heir to represent and receive the inheritance of their forebear."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-82d56e3add17387eb012a80a933cb63c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;ORDINARY GENERAL MEETING&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Ordinary General Meeting is an annual event where company shareholders gather to discuss and make decisions about the company's affairs."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-6cd60bb5f8e5d886648c66def090b185</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 181&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 181 defines enhanced penalties for false evidence related to serious offences."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 181 describes the time limits within which a voidable act can be avoided, emphasizing a one-year or ten-year period depending on circumstances."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-e417732f0f4e36ea8784fa2cc5dd8a85&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d82b5d0a885fc8b96ea11f873f6f0c0a</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1740&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A specified law section outlining the order of property appropriation for debt payment from the deceased's estate."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-d021e006377bbbff9ec8f8e90f54f2a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;WRITTEN INSTRUMENT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A Written Instrument represents a right and is necessary to be delivered and notified in specific pledge arrangements."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-f92e53c4b928412441b1d00eeb6aab74</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1640&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1640 describes representation for inheritance when a person is deemed legally dead under specific code provisions."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-82d56e3add17387eb012a80a933cb63c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;PREFERENCE SHARES&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Preference Shares are a type of share that carries preferential rights, such as priority in dividend payments or during company liquidation, over ordinary shares."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-6cd60bb5f8e5d886648c66def090b185</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 182&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 182 allows offenders to avoid punishment if they apologize and reveal the truth before their statement concludes."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 182 defines a condition as a clause that affects the validity of a juristic act based on future uncertain events."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-e417732f0f4e36ea8784fa2cc5dd8a85&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d82b5d0a885fc8b96ea11f873f6f0c0a</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1741&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A specified law section allowing creditors to raise objections to the auction or appraisal of estate property."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-d021e006377bbbff9ec8f8e90f54f2a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;DEPOSITED OFFICE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Deposited Office is an institution where payment must be made jointly to pledgee and pledgor if they cannot agree, ensuring the benefit for both."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-f92e53c4b928412441b1d00eeb6aab74</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1641&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1641 clarifies inheritance distribution when certain heirs are deceased or excluded, denying representation for particular heir classes."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-82d56e3add17387eb012a80a933cb63c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;NAME CERTIFICATE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A Name Certificate is a document representing ownership of shares and must be surrendered to receive a Certificate to Bearer for fully paid-up shares."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-6cd60bb5f8e5d886648c66def090b185</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 183&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 183 allows reduced punishment for offenders who apologize and declare the truth before the judgment."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 183 explains the effects of conditions precedent and subsequent on juristic acts, determining their commencement or cessation of effect."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-e417732f0f4e36ea8784fa2cc5dd8a85&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d82b5d0a885fc8b96ea11f873f6f0c0a</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1742&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A specified law section concerning creditors designated as beneficiaries of life insurance and the conditions under which they may be required to return premiums."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-d021e006377bbbff9ec8f8e90f54f2a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;LICENSED PAWNBROKERS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Licensed Pawnbrokers are entities or individuals authorized to engage in pledge contracts, subject to specific legal provisions."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-f92e53c4b928412441b1d00eeb6aab74</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1642&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1642 restricts representation for inheritance purposes to statutory heirs only."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-82d56e3add17387eb012a80a933cb63c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;FIFTY SATANG&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Fifty Satang is the fee required for shareholders requesting a copy of the register of shareholders, calculated per hundred words copied."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-6cd60bb5f8e5d886648c66def090b185</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 184&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 184 outlines penalties for destroying or tampering with evidence to help another person evade punishment."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 184 restricts any actions by one party that would impair the benefits derived from a condition being fulfilled."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-e417732f0f4e36ea8784fa2cc5dd8a85&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d82b5d0a885fc8b96ea11f873f6f0c0a</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1743&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A specified law section stating the obligations of statutory heirs or legatees under general title in executing legacies."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-d021e006377bbbff9ec8f8e90f54f2a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE PUBLIC PROSECUTOR&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Public Prosecutor is an official who can apply for actions related to the management of minors’ properties and decisions involving deprivation of parental power."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Public Prosecutor is an official who can apply for judicial interventions, such as dismissing directors or dissolving the foundation."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Public Prosecutor is an official who may enter legal actions on behalf of an adopted individual and submit petitions to the court related to adoption and maintenance cases."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-a8f2d8db15aae9334e2b0c36d4ea99c8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e6503e3e2e955a071268b1be787bc7d1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4c5aad3770b3111c6e3b4171b1b6cb5c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1643&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1643 states that representation for receiving an inheritance is available only to direct descendants and not ascendants."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-82d56e3add17387eb012a80a933cb63c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;CO-OWNER&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A co-owner is an individual who shares ownership and possesses certain rights and responsibilities regarding the management, use, and disposition of a property."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-bb67153d31d305a18c3208696a748f1b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 185&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 185 addresses the rights and duties of parties concerning a pending condition, asserting their ability to be disposed of or inherited according to law."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 185 deals with penalties for damaging or destroying property or documents in court custody."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-e417732f0f4e36ea8784fa2cc5dd8a85&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d82b5d0a885fc8b96ea11f873f6f0c0a</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1744&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A specified law section that outlines conditions under which an administrator is bound to deliver the estate to heirs."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-d021e006377bbbff9ec8f8e90f54f2a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;NATURAL PARENTS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Natural Parents regain parental power upon the death of an adopter or dissolution of adoption, provided the child has not reached legal adulthood."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-e6503e3e2e955a071268b1be787bc7d1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1644&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1644 mandates that a descendant must have complete rights to the inheritance to represent for inheritance purposes."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-82d56e3add17387eb012a80a933cb63c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;COMMON PROPERTY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Common Property refers to property owned jointly by co-owners, including real estate or assets, requiring management and partition decisions."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-bb67153d31d305a18c3208696a748f1b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 186&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 186 considers a condition to be fulfilled if one party wrongfully prevents its fulfillment, or vice versa if fulfilled in bad faith."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 186 specifies penalties for damaging property forfeited by court judgment."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-e417732f0f4e36ea8784fa2cc5dd8a85&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d82b5d0a885fc8b96ea11f873f6f0c0a</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1745&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A specified law section describing the rights and duties of co-heirs until the completion of estate partition."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-d021e006377bbbff9ec8f8e90f54f2a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;CHILD ADOPTER&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Child Adopter is an individual or couple who adopt a child but whose rights may cease if certain conditions occur like their death or dissolution of adoption."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-e6503e3e2e955a071268b1be787bc7d1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1645&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1645 states that renouncing an inheritance does not prevent a person from representing another in inheriting from a different individual."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-82d56e3add17387eb012a80a933cb63c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;POSSESSOR&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A possessor is an individual who holds or occupies a property, presumed to do so with good faith, peacefulness, and rights over the property."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-bb67153d31d305a18c3208696a748f1b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 187&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 187 clarifies the validity of juristic acts based on whether conditions are fulfilled or certain at the time of the act."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 187 refers to the law concerning the penalty for damaging or concealing property to prevent the execution of a court judgment."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 187 targets those who damage property to prevent the execution of court judgments or orders."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-e417732f0f4e36ea8784fa2cc5dd8a85&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d82b5d0a885fc8b96ea11f873f6f0c0a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-268065f480c7c2e17bd0004a31f0f454</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;GOVERNMENT GAZETTE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Government Gazette is the official publication where the registration of foundations becomes effective."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Government Gazette is an official publication for the dissemination of legal orders and announcements."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Government Gazette is an official publication used for disseminating summaries of registered documents and matters."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Government Gazette is the medium through which court orders are published, making legal decisions public."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Government Gazette is the publication where adjudications of disappearance and their revocations are made public."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Government Gazette is the publication where official notices, such as those regarding the dissolution of foundations, are published."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Government Gazette is the publication where the registration of an association is made public once it is approved."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Government Gazette is the official publication where the Criminal Code B.E. 2499 was published to come into force."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-91e6c9c6ece02f3027772a9577efdcd4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-86deb2357b8656ccf8680e27cbac71ec&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ddd247e62a952c755b8e64cbea59a2d3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-42fad725aa98ee40547f7a36e0de09d6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-46940167ee3908fb358c9a82647ea322&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-99e04c388a7385a4978847a999d423f1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e0099557ffbf92309faf8ac19f118ba2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5b0b36a0f64bbdfdfd692bde041dc3f5</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;HEIRS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Heirs are individuals entitled to inherit from the estate and are impacted by the acts performed by the administrator within their scope of authority."&lt;SEP&gt;"Heirs are individuals entitled to inherit the estate of a deceased person according to law or by will."&lt;SEP&gt;"Heirs are individuals entitled to receive a share of the deceased person’s estate, typically determined by a will or, in its absence, by laws of intestate succession."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-6f29560483a94cdf780f52af44990dd1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e6503e3e2e955a071268b1be787bc7d1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-89b8c822a665cc12b23359be3cc927d4</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE BROKER&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Broker is an individual engaged in facilitating contracts between parties, with specific rights and limitations regarding remuneration and liability."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-b004bfce3d731fd6bae3b797ccb93662</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1358&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1358 outlines the rights and management decisions of co-owners regarding common property."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-bb67153d31d305a18c3208696a748f1b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 188&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 188 renders a juristic act void if it is subject to an unlawful condition or one contrary to public morals."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 188 specifies penalties for damaging, destroying, or concealing documents or wills that could harm another person or public."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-d82b5d0a885fc8b96ea11f873f6f0c0a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-268065f480c7c2e17bd0004a31f0f454</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;LEGAL REPRESENTATIVE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A Legal Representative is an individual appointed to act on behalf of a child in legal matters, especially if the child is a minor and not capable of representing themselves."&lt;SEP&gt;"A Legal Representative is someone who acts on behalf of a minor or person of unsound mind in legal proceedings."&lt;SEP&gt;"A legal representative is a person who is authorized to act on behalf of someone, especially in legal matters."&lt;SEP&gt;"A legal representative is someone authorized to act on behalf of another person, particularly in relation to the ratification of voidable acts."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Legal representative is someone who represents a minor and has the authority to permit or terminate certain activities."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-a0818329731c6e20f0c0c43a0133253c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d45ed62b6b0bfc44f2c1ae4fe430c9c0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d82b5d0a885fc8b96ea11f873f6f0c0a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-933d505d06605d728d8a7325e6245238&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-99e04c388a7385a4978847a999d423f1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;CHILD ADOPTION DISSOLUTION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Child Adoption Dissolution refers to the legal termination of an adoption, where the relationships and responsibilities are reversed or reassigned according to court judgment."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-e6503e3e2e955a071268b1be787bc7d1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;MINISTER RESPONSIBLE FOR REGISTRATION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Minister responsible for Registration establishes regulations for the registration of partnerships and companies and sets fees related to these services."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-b004bfce3d731fd6bae3b797ccb93662</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1359&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1359 details the rights of a co-owner to exercise ownership against third persons with specific conditions for property recovery."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-bb67153d31d305a18c3208696a748f1b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 189&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 189 outlines penalties for aiding a person who has committed an offense, helping them avoid arrest and punishment."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 189 states that acts with an impossible condition precedent are void, whereas those with an impossible condition subsequent are valid."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-d82b5d0a885fc8b96ea11f873f6f0c0a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-268065f480c7c2e17bd0004a31f0f454</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;CURATOR&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A Curator is appointed by the Court to manage the affairs of a person adjudged quasi-incompetent."&lt;SEP&gt;"A curator is an individual assigned the responsibility to assist or manage the affairs of a quasi-incompetent person."&lt;SEP&gt;"A curator is appointed to take care of the property and rights of someone who cannot manage them personally."&lt;SEP&gt;"A curator is responsible for managing the affairs of someone unable to do so, specifically excluded in certain contexts of ratifying juristic acts."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-99e04c388a7385a4978847a999d423f1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4e5197de768063837bf5a455698da0aa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-42fad725aa98ee40547f7a36e0de09d6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d82b5d0a885fc8b96ea11f873f6f0c0a</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SUI JURIS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Sui Juris is a legal status indicating that a person possesses full legal capacity to act on their own behalf without parental or guardian support."&lt;SEP&gt;"Sui Juris refers to an individual who possesses full legal rights and is not under any legal disability, particularly relevant to certain parental duties."&lt;SEP&gt;"Sui juris refers to a legal status of having full legal capacity and the ability to act independently, typically applied when an individual reaches adulthood or is legally permitted to manage their own affairs."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-140da0bea780fb9ec8b35168f6556b93&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e6503e3e2e955a071268b1be787bc7d1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4c5aad3770b3111c6e3b4171b1b6cb5c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;A CONTRACT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A contract is a legal agreement between parties that outlines obligations and rights, potentially affected by circumstances such as the involvement of a broker."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-b004bfce3d731fd6bae3b797ccb93662</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1360&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1360 defines a co-owner's entitlement to use common property as long as it does not infringe on other co-owners' rights."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-bb67153d31d305a18c3208696a748f1b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 190&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 190 defines the penalties for escaping confinement and provides heavier penalties for escape using violence or weapons."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 190 voids a juristic act if its condition precedent depends solely on the debtor's will."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-d82b5d0a885fc8b96ea11f873f6f0c0a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-268065f480c7c2e17bd0004a31f0f454</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;PERSON OF UNSOUND MIND&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A person of unsound mind is an individual who is legally recognized as unable to manage their own affairs."&lt;SEP&gt;"A person with mental incapacities, potentially adjudged incompetent by legal authorities."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-99e04c388a7385a4978847a999d423f1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4e5197de768063837bf5a455698da0aa</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;STATUTORY HEIRS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Statutory Heirs are individuals who are entitled by law to inherit the estate of a deceased person when no will is present."&lt;SEP&gt;"Statutory Heirs are individuals who inherit by law as outlined in the Civil and Commercial Code, as opposed to legatees who inherit by will."&lt;SEP&gt;"Statutory Heirs are individuals who inherit property according to the laws of succession when there is no effective will in place."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-e6503e3e2e955a071268b1be787bc7d1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a7a64e6f6e939634750f7cc32da6d781&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-553b3730ac4ba8b3212a7d230dbc31ad</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;TITLE XVII: COMPROMISE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Title XVII: Compromise refers to the legal provisions governing agreements made to settle disputes between parties through mutual concessions."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-b004bfce3d731fd6bae3b797ccb93662</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1361&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1361 discusses the rights and limitations of a co-owner to dispose, mortgage, or create a charge on their share of the property."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-bb67153d31d305a18c3208696a748f1b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 191&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 191 details penalties for releasing persons from confinement, with more severe penalties for serious offenders or using violence."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 191 specifies that juristic acts cannot be executed before their commencement time or after their ending time."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-d82b5d0a885fc8b96ea11f873f6f0c0a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-268065f480c7c2e17bd0004a31f0f454</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;QUASI-INCOMPETENT PERSON&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A Quasi-Incompetent Person is an individual who has been legally deemed partially incapable of managing their affairs, impacting their authority as a manager."&lt;SEP&gt;"A Quasi-incompetent person is someone with certain incapacities requiring oversight, but not entirely devoid of legal capacity."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-99e04c388a7385a4978847a999d423f1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-055e2a0c9f60207819211360d38e04f8</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;DEFAULT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Default refers to non-payment or breach of contract terms, potentially leading to early termination of hire agreements and forfeiture of previous payments."&lt;SEP&gt;"Default refers to the failure of a debtor or creditor to perform an obligation in the legally agreed manner. It can lead to legal actions such as claims for damages or compulsory performance."&lt;SEP&gt;"Default refers to the failure to fulfill an obligation, which can affect all parties involved in a joint debtor or creditor situation."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-aac23a1f6cf12366451f6be3ff0a3ed2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e7fb2f4e3c8f089ed58aad2cf781f6f9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bd6efc93031ebfde67a4ae4a12bbe3ce</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;TITLE XVIII: GAMBLING AND BETTING&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Title XVIII: Gambling and Betting describes legal stipulations related to gambling, betting, and the validity of obligations arising from such activities."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-b004bfce3d731fd6bae3b797ccb93662</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1362&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1362 specifies the obligations of co-owners to bear costs related to property management and preservation proportionate to their share."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-bb67153d31d305a18c3208696a748f1b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;GOODS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Goods refers to the items being transported, which may have specific terms such as declarations of value or nature if dangerous."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-7289405ac6638bb4a476489ae0c1b33d</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 25&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 25 describes rights and responsibilities of persons confined to a designated place, including receiving maintenance and selecting work categories."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 25 is a legal provision that allows minors over fifteen years of age to make a will."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-edf03699076f42c474bd2d773c684e42&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-99e04c388a7385a4978847a999d423f1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;COMPULSORY PERFORMANCE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Compulsory performance is a legal demand by a creditor for the performance of an obligation by a debtor, including potential court actions if the debtor fails to perform."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-e7fb2f4e3c8f089ed58aad2cf781f6f9</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;TITLE XXII: PARTNERSHIPS AND COMPANIES&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Title XXII: Partnerships and Companies outlines the formation, registration, and regulation of business entities formed by individuals for shared profit."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-b004bfce3d731fd6bae3b797ccb93662</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1363&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1363 allows co-owners to demand partition of property except when restricted by a juristic act or purpose of co-ownership."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-bb67153d31d305a18c3208696a748f1b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SPECIE, CURRENCY, VALUABLES&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"These include items like specie, currency notes, banknotes, and other valuables, for which the carrier's liability is limited unless their value is declared."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-7289405ac6638bb4a476489ae0c1b33d</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 26&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 26 addresses the rights of confined persons to continue their profession or occupation within the place of confinement and the setting of conditions by the Court."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 26 describes the conditions under which a minor may dispose of property with or without the legal representative's permission."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-edf03699076f42c474bd2d773c684e42&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-99e04c388a7385a4978847a999d423f1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;PERFORMANCE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Performance refers to the act of fulfilling the obligations or duties by the debtor towards the creditor."&lt;SEP&gt;"Performance refers to the execution of an obligation by a debtor to a creditor, as mandated by an agreement or contract."&lt;SEP&gt;"Performance refers to the fulfillment of an obligation, which may involve payment or other actions to satisfy a debt or requirement."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-6cd9b0e3cf4adfb36e41fca038140314&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c35036965b446b68b1f64bc55f989965&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e7fb2f4e3c8f089ed58aad2cf781f6f9</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 847&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 847 outlines the circumstances under which a broker is not entitled to remuneration if their actions conflict with their engagement or good faith."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-b004bfce3d731fd6bae3b797ccb93662</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1364&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1364 describes the process of partitioning property through division or sale, potentially overseen by the Court."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-bb67153d31d305a18c3208696a748f1b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;PASSENGER&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A Passenger is a person traveling using the carrier’s service, having rights regarding personal injuries and luggage, particularly if entrusted to the carrier."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-7289405ac6638bb4a476489ae0c1b33d</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 27&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 27 is a part of the Criminal Code that deals with the detention of individuals and has been amended by the Criminal Code Amendment Act (No. 15), B.E. 2545."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 27 outlines the rights of a minor in carrying on a business or entering into employment with permission from a legal representative or Court."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 27 provides guidance on transitioning detention to imprisonment based on violations or non-fulfillment of conditions by the detained person."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-edf03699076f42c474bd2d773c684e42&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-99e04c388a7385a4978847a999d423f1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6f75e186ae4f2b6f051c224eadc5d322</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;NEGLIGENCE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Negligence is the failure by a debtor to take reasonable care or diligence in fulfilling an obligation, potentially resulting in legal liability for damages."&lt;SEP&gt;"Negligence refers to the failure to exercise appropriate and ethical care, leading to harm or injury."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-d0507d79984fa42096d2e2bed7526a91&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e7fb2f4e3c8f089ed58aad2cf781f6f9</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 848&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 848 specifies the liability limits of a broker regarding contract performance and the communication of party names."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-b004bfce3d731fd6bae3b797ccb93662</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1365&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1365 provides conditions for co-owners' obligations towards third parties and inter-co-owner liabilities at the time of partition."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-bb67153d31d305a18c3208696a748f1b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;LUGGAGE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Luggage refers to the items a Passenger carries during transit, which must be delivered upon arrival and can be sold at auction if not claimed."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-7289405ac6638bb4a476489ae0c1b33d</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 28&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 28 allows for the adjudication of a person of unsound mind as incompetent through various applicants including family members and legal authorities."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 28 outlines the requirement for payment of fines as determined by the Court's judgment."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 28 specifies the obligation of a person who has been fined to pay the determined amount to the Court."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-edf03699076f42c474bd2d773c684e42&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-99e04c388a7385a4978847a999d423f1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6f75e186ae4f2b6f051c224eadc5d322</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;DAMAGES&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Damages are monetary compensation claimed by a creditor from a debtor for any loss or injury suffered due to non-performance of an obligation."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-e7fb2f4e3c8f089ed58aad2cf781f6f9</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 849&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 849 presumes a broker's lack of authority to receive payments or performances due under a contract."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-b004bfce3d731fd6bae3b797ccb93662</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1366&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1366 outlines the liabilities of co-owners as comparable to a seller in terms of the partitioned property they receive."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-bb67153d31d305a18c3208696a748f1b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;INDORSEMENT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Indorsement refers to the act of signing a document to assign its rights to another party; applicable in transferring a consignment note unless forbidden."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-7289405ac6638bb4a476489ae0c1b33d</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 29&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 29 declares that any act done by a person adjudged incompetent is voidable."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 29 outlines the procedures and consequences if a fined person fails to pay the fine within the specified period, including seizure of property or confinement."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-6f75e186ae4f2b6f051c224eadc5d322&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-99e04c388a7385a4978847a999d423f1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;IMPOSSIBILITY OF PERFORMANCE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Impossibility of performance occurs when a debtor cannot fulfill an obligation due to unforeseen circumstances for which they are not responsible."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-e7fb2f4e3c8f089ed58aad2cf781f6f9</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 850&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 850 defines compromise as settling disputes by mutual concessions, requiring written evidence for enforceability."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-b004bfce3d731fd6bae3b797ccb93662</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1367&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1367 establishes that a person acquires possessory rights by holding a property with the intention of possession."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-bb67153d31d305a18c3208696a748f1b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;CHAPTER I&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Chapter I outlines the rules and liabilities concerning the carriage of goods, covering the responsibilities of carriers, senders, and consignees."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-7289405ac6638bb4a476489ae0c1b33d</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 30&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 30 discusses details regarding detention in lieu of unpaid fines, including the calculation of detention periods and exceptions."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 30 is referenced in the context of a voidable juristic act involving persons adjudged incompetent or of unsound mind."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 30 specifies that acts of a person of unsound mind, not adjudged incompetent, are voidable if the unsoundness was known to the other party."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-6f75e186ae4f2b6f051c224eadc5d322&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-99e04c388a7385a4978847a999d423f1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d82b5d0a885fc8b96ea11f873f6f0c0a</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;QUASI-INCOMPETENT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A quasi-incompetent person is partially unable to handle personal and legal matters, often requiring a curator."&lt;SEP&gt;"Quasi-incompetent refers to individuals deemed by the Court to have limited capacity to manage their own affairs."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-42fad725aa98ee40547f7a36e0de09d6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-933d505d06605d728d8a7325e6245238</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 851&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 851 states that a contract of compromise must have written evidence signed by the liable party to be enforceable by action."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-b004bfce3d731fd6bae3b797ccb93662</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;POSSESSION TITLE III&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Possession Title III contains sections regarding the acquisition and rights of property possession."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-bb67153d31d305a18c3208696a748f1b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 630, 631, 632&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Sections 630, 631, and 632 refer to specific laws or rules not detailed in this text but applicable to the rights described for freight and accessories."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-7289405ac6638bb4a476489ae0c1b33d</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 31&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 31 provides for the revocation of an incompetency adjudication if the cause of incompetency ceases to exist."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-99e04c388a7385a4978847a999d423f1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;INCOMPETENT PERSON&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A person adjudged by the Court as unable to manage their own affairs, affecting their ability to apply for marriage cancellation."&lt;SEP&gt;"An Incompetent Person is an individual adjudged by law as unable to manage their property and affairs, for whom a Controller of Property may be appointed."&lt;SEP&gt;"Incompetent Person refers to individuals who cannot fully manage their own affairs and require legal guardianship."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-cb8c8544779f197bfe5eef0d6b3bba3c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-42fad725aa98ee40547f7a36e0de09d6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-553b3730ac4ba8b3212a7d230dbc31ad</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 852&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 852 explains the effect of compromise in extinguishing abandoned claims and securing declared rights."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-b004bfce3d731fd6bae3b797ccb93662</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1368&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1368 describes acquiring possessory rights through someone holding property on behalf of another person."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-bb67153d31d305a18c3208696a748f1b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 680&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 680 defines suretyship as a contract where a surety binds themselves to a creditor to satisfy a debtor's obligation in case of default."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-5806a4ac5edf0880beed390e35f10ef7</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 32&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 32 addresses the adjudication of a person as quasi-incompetent due to physical or mental infirmities or mismanagement."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-99e04c388a7385a4978847a999d423f1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;MANAGER OF PROPERTY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A Manager of Property is appointed by the court to oversee the property of a missing person if their whereabouts are unknown."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-42fad725aa98ee40547f7a36e0de09d6</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 853&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 853 declares that no legal obligation results from gambling or betting activities, affecting claims arising from these activities."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-b004bfce3d731fd6bae3b797ccb93662</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1369&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1369 presumes a person holding property does so for themselves."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-bb67153d31d305a18c3208696a748f1b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 681&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 681 specifies that suretyship can be given only for a valid obligation and may secure future or conditional obligations."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-5806a4ac5edf0880beed390e35f10ef7</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 33&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 33 covers the transition between judgments of incompetency and quasi-incompetency based on the suitability determined by the Court."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-99e04c388a7385a4978847a999d423f1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;DEPOSIT OFFICE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Deposit Office is a designated location where the debtor can deposit the subject of the obligation when the creditor is unable to accept performance."&lt;SEP&gt;"Deposit Office refers to a government or private entity designated to hold or manage property deposits and handle related financial transactions or legal obligations."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Deposit Office is an institution where payments related to the obligations or property must be deposited as per certain sections."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Deposit Office is likely a financial or governmental institution where sums of money can be deposited for the common benefit of involved parties."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-cc95f23cfbd6112c8327703d8101a010&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5806a4ac5edf0880beed390e35f10ef7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c35036965b446b68b1f64bc55f989965&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ac44eff8208c6427b97025d89925979e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 854&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 854 states that lottery or raffle contracts are binding if authorized by the government, otherwise following other legal provisions."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-b004bfce3d731fd6bae3b797ccb93662</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1370&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1370 presumes that possession is held in good faith, peacefully, and openly."</data>
