    <node id="&quot;BAHT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Baht is the currency of Thailand, mentioned in the context of financial transactions related to company operations, such as payment for share copies."&lt;SEP&gt;"Baht is the currency of Thailand, used to denote fines imposed on officials as penalties for their misconduct according to the Criminal Code."&lt;SEP&gt;"Baht is the currency used for fines and financial penalties in various sections mentioned."&lt;SEP&gt;"Baht is the currency used for fines imposed for legal infractions such as counterfeiting, according to the statutes."&lt;SEP&gt;"Baht is the currency used in Thailand, mentioned as a unit of fine in the legal sections."&lt;SEP&gt;"Baht is the currency used in Thailand, referenced in the fines and penalties according to Thai law."&lt;SEP&gt;"Baht is the currency used in the context of fines and penalties in the Thai legal system."&lt;SEP&gt;"Baht is the currency used in the fines mentioned throughout the document for various offenses."&lt;SEP&gt;"Baht is the official currency of Thailand, used as a unit of fines in the legal sections."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Baht is the currency of Thailand, used here to denote fines associated with various offences."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-e1e198b1f8b66564b0fae2fbe893a4c6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c70ada6cc5febef9164203734d211889&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-de71dcf326342843893937651bd927f6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4b333b466a8e220c02cd14e77e8fb935&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b04ccf793557331808974ade6067d896&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6fd5b0ac67c6f4aafc6e1ef0e7ce2a77&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3a03e095c966911fdfbf17177a6fd05e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-78127285a70d48835c00c4ab2953f9f8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d0507d79984fa42096d2e2bed7526a91&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3aa47916d44030b53f9aac3e17c9da38</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 440&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 440 allows the injured party to demand interest on compensation for diminished value due to taking or damage."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-4b290ec6a69d1ce11295ee43b1785323</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;ADOPTOR'S SPOUSE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The spouse of a person seeking to adopt or be adopted, whose consent is required for the process."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-6158dfc7a7c5c354484d988186bd2709</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 206&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 206 concerns obligations arising from unlawful acts, indicating that the debtor is in default from the moment the act is committed."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-2b194bfa1a18d3dffd302b027ba18352</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 357&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 357 states that an offer ceases to be binding if refused or not accepted in due time according to earlier sections."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-54fa1d3a7c7433d0d90d3817cefe57fa</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SATANG&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Satang is a subdivision of the Thai Baht, used in the context of small fees for company services such as the issuance of share certificates."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-4b333b466a8e220c02cd14e77e8fb935</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 441&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 441 outlines compensation obligations even if a compensated item is owned by a third party, except when such a right is known or discovered."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-4b290ec6a69d1ce11295ee43b1785323</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;MINOR'S PARENTS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Parents of a minor, whose consent is typically required for adoption, unless certain conditions allow the Court to intervene."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-6158dfc7a7c5c354484d988186bd2709</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 208&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 208 contains legal rules regarding the actual tender of performance to a creditor, addressing conditions under which non-acceptance occurs."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-2b194bfa1a18d3dffd302b027ba18352</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 358&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 358 defines the offense of mischief, detailing penalties for damaging or destroying property."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 358 provides instructions for the offeror when acceptance notice arrives out of time but should have arrived in due time under normal circumstances."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-54fa1d3a7c7433d0d90d3817cefe57fa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a5d0229c550b9e954016797ed8a8ac12</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 359&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 359 defines that late acceptance is considered a new offer and any offer modification results in refusal and a new offer."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 359 includes specific items and conditions that incur higher penalties under the offense of mischief."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-54fa1d3a7c7433d0d90d3817cefe57fa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a5d0229c550b9e954016797ed8a8ac12</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 442&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 442 applies provisions when the injured party's fault contributes to their injury."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-4b290ec6a69d1ce11295ee43b1785323</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;REGISTER OF SHAREHOLDERS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Register of Shareholders contains the addresses of shareholders where notices are sent, ensuring communication compliance."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Register of Shareholders is a record maintained by the company, listing names, addresses, and share details of its shareholders and is used for legal evidence."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-28aaa22d510e3f49e80675454af7f8a3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6cd60bb5f8e5d886648c66def090b185</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;COMPETENT MINISTER&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Competent Minister is a government authority responsible for issuing regulations related to registration and partnership matters."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-ddd247e62a952c755b8e64cbea59a2d3</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;DEPOSITOR&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A Depositor is an individual who places property into the care of a depositary under a deposit contract."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Depositor is the individual or entity who places property or money in the custody of another party, called the depositary, for safekeeping under a contractual agreement."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-cc95f23cfbd6112c8327703d8101a010&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-629bbfda7f476a27cd4f982000bd902b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 360&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 360 clarifies that certain provisions do not apply if the offeror has declared a contrary intention or learns of death or incapacity before acceptance."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-54fa1d3a7c7433d0d90d3817cefe57fa</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 443&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 443 mandates compensation for death-related expenses and additional compensations if death wasn't immediate."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-4b290ec6a69d1ce11295ee43b1785323</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;REGISTER&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Register refers to the Registrar where company transformations and notifications are filed."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-28aaa22d510e3f49e80675454af7f8a3</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;ORDINARY PARTNERSHIP&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A type of partnership where all partners have joint and unlimited liability for the obligations of the partnership."&lt;SEP&gt;"Ordinary partnership is a type of partnership where all partners are jointly and unlimitedly liable for all obligations."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-ddd247e62a952c755b8e64cbea59a2d3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-855466dea5984defb1f279860dbf5504</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;DEPOSITARY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A Depositary is a person who receives property from a depositor and is obligated to protect and return the property at the depositor's request."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Depositary is the individual or entity who receives property or money from the depositor to hold and is obligated to return it under specified conditions."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-cc95f23cfbd6112c8327703d8101a010&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-629bbfda7f476a27cd4f982000bd902b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 361&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 361 explains the conditions under which a long-distance contract is formed upon notice of acceptance reaching the offeror."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-54fa1d3a7c7433d0d90d3817cefe57fa</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 444&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 444 provides for reimbursement and damages for injuries leading to work disability."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-4b290ec6a69d1ce11295ee43b1785323</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;PARTNERSHIP&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A business organization in which two or more individuals manage and operate the business with shared profits and liabilities."&lt;SEP&gt;"A business structure where two or more individuals manage and operate a business in accordance with agreed-upon terms and conditions."&lt;SEP&gt;"A partnership is a legal form of business operation between two or more individuals who share management and profits."&lt;SEP&gt;"A partnership is a legal relationship existing between two or more persons who jointly undertake to conduct business."&lt;SEP&gt;"A registered partnership or limited partnership can be transformed into a limited company by following legal consent and procedures."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-34e7b7cbd3efe1f3b5bdd00742010ed6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-28aaa22d510e3f49e80675454af7f8a3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ddd247e62a952c755b8e64cbea59a2d3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-81d63dbc17e3f3707788a6e2552b764c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e319f375a4d832025273d5a023fbe5e9</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;REGISTRATION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Registration is the process of recording documents or particulars in an official register as required by law."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-ddd247e62a952c755b8e64cbea59a2d3</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;PROPRIETOR&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Proprietor is the owner or manager of an inn, hotel, or similar establishment, responsible for the safekeeping of lodgers' property while they stay at the venue."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-cc95f23cfbd6112c8327703d8101a010</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 362&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 362 addresses promises involving rewards, binding the promisor to anyone performing the act regardless of the intent to claim the reward."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 362 describes the offense of trespassing with the intent to take possession of immovable property."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-54fa1d3a7c7433d0d90d3817cefe57fa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a5d0229c550b9e954016797ed8a8ac12</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 445&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 445 involves compensation to a third party if the injured provided services to them."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-4b290ec6a69d1ce11295ee43b1785323</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;NEW COMPANY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The New Company is formed as a result of amalgamation or transformation, inheriting rights and liabilities from previous entities."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-28aaa22d510e3f49e80675454af7f8a3</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;PART I AND PART II&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Part I defines ordinary partnerships, and Part II discusses the relations of partners within such partnerships."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-ddd247e62a952c755b8e64cbea59a2d3</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;INN&quot;\">
      <data key="d0">EVENT</data>
      <data key="d1">"temporary lodgings or accommodations, often providing a bed and breakfast or hotel-like service to travelers or guests."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-cc95f23cfbd6112c8327703d8101a010</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 363&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 363 allows for the withdrawal of a public reward offer by the same means it was advertised unless withdrawal is restricted by the terms."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 363 includes provisions regarding the removal or destruction of boundary marks or property."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-54fa1d3a7c7433d0d90d3817cefe57fa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a5d0229c550b9e954016797ed8a8ac12</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 446&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 446 covers compensation claims for non-pecuniary losses from body or health injuries."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-4b290ec6a69d1ce11295ee43b1785323</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1237 TO 1246/3&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"These sections outline legal provisions for company dissolution, amalgamation, notice serving, and conversion of partnerships to limited companies."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-28aaa22d510e3f49e80675454af7f8a3</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THAILAND CIVIL AND COMMERCIAL CODE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Thailand Civil and Commercial Code comprises the legal framework that governs civil and commercial transactions in Thailand, including contracts, obligations, property law, and estate matters."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Thailand Civil and Commercial Code is a comprehensive legal code governing civil and commercial practices, including property and real rights."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-8ce6f1498128f5fc6034c5e3b827db4f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-af5697d7b87ddc73215d01d7439bac2b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;TRAVELLER OR GUEST&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Traveller or Guest is an individual staying temporarily at an inn, hotel, or similar establishment, whose property may be subject to the proprietor's responsibility and limitations of liability."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-cc95f23cfbd6112c8327703d8101a010</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 364&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 364 defines the offense of entering or hiding in another's dwelling or property without consent."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 364 states the rights concerning rewards when multiple people complete an act, and details how distribution occurs if the reward is divisible or not."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-54fa1d3a7c7433d0d90d3817cefe57fa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a5d0229c550b9e954016797ed8a8ac12</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 447&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 447 allows courts to order measures for reputation rehabilitation when reputation is injured."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-4b290ec6a69d1ce11295ee43b1785323</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;STATUTORY REPORT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A statutory report is a legal document that must be filed by a company, the non-filing of which can result in dissolution by the Court."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Statutory Report is a mandatory document limited companies must file, failure of which can lead to court-ordered dissolution."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-07706a49d3b190ef1fa2b1178a2e275f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-28aaa22d510e3f49e80675454af7f8a3</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE ROYAL THAI GOVERNMENT GAZETTE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Royal Thai Government Gazette is the official publication where Thai legal texts are published and have legal force."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-af5697d7b87ddc73215d01d7439bac2b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;LIABILITY LIMITATION NOTICE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Liability Limitation Notice is a posted communication in inns or hotels that attempts to exclude or limit the proprietor's liability for loss or damage to guests' property."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-cc95f23cfbd6112c8327703d8101a010</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 365&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 365 describes enhanced penalties for criminal trespass committed under specific aggravating conditions."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 365 discusses the validity of reward promises in competitions, requiring a fixed time period and provides for the decision-making process."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-54fa1d3a7c7433d0d90d3817cefe57fa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a5d0229c550b9e954016797ed8a8ac12</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 448&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 448 sets a one-year prescription period for damage claims from wrongful acts, with exceptions for criminal acts with longer prescriptions."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-4b290ec6a69d1ce11295ee43b1785323</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;STATUTORY MEETING&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A statutory meeting is a mandatory meeting required by law, failure to hold which can lead to company dissolution by the Court."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Statutory Meeting is a formal gathering to discuss and approve various aspects of the company, such as regulations, contracts, and appointments."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Statutory Meeting is a regulatory requirement where the company must convene to present the statutory report and discuss company affairs as part of compliance."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-d67f818d289a7a42a391ffd601a49336&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-07706a49d3b190ef1fa2b1178a2e275f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-28aaa22d510e3f49e80675454af7f8a3</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THAILAND&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A Southeast Asian country where the described laws apply, including those related to public peace and religious impersonation."&lt;SEP&gt;"Thailand is the country referenced in relation to the debtor's whereabouts being unknown, affecting the surety's responsibilities."&lt;SEP&gt;"Thailand is the country where the Civil and Commercial Code is enacted, and its legal environment is governed by this document."&lt;SEP&gt;"Thailand is the country where the laws and legal codes referenced in the document apply."&lt;SEP&gt;"Thailand is the country where the legal proceedings concerning child legitimacy and parental power are taking place. It is involved in extending time periods related to consent for legitimation when parties are outside the country."&lt;SEP&gt;"Thailand is the jurisdiction in which the discussed sections of the Civil and Commercial Code apply, with legal texts in Thai holding authoritative value."&lt;SEP&gt;"Thailand is the country where the Criminal Code B.E. 2499 was enacted to address changes in the country's circumstances since the previous Criminal Law in B.E. 2451."&lt;SEP&gt;"Thailand is the country whose laws and regulations are being translated and discussed in the document."&lt;SEP&gt;"Thailand is the country whose legal code is described in these sections, underlining the geographical jurisdiction."&lt;SEP&gt;"Thailand is the country whose legal system and laws are being discussed, as indicated by references such as www.ThaiLaws.com."&lt;SEP&gt;"Thailand is the geographical location where the laws mentioned in the document apply, as indicated by references to Thai laws and currency."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-5429b702233c5b142e4f7e7899dffac1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8ddccbf45ec50ee6c41104c7f6c4c61b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d274c9e863fb793abab4dc5884e523b8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cbd1a08621190b50907588a23e2a2a3d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5806a4ac5edf0880beed390e35f10ef7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1429bffff14b8577c8748fc8f14a6678&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-af5697d7b87ddc73215d01d7439bac2b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c8c3be6aeb4b1e7e1a17d53346a1d923&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6e4efb3313af866dc7bcaba7c4daff62&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a5d0229c550b9e954016797ed8a8ac12&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5b0b36a0f64bbdfdfd692bde041dc3f5</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;FIVE THOUSAND BAHT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Five Thousand Baht is a monetary limit on the liability of the proprietor for certain types of property loss or damage, unless explicitly deposited with the inn for safekeeping."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-cc95f23cfbd6112c8327703d8101a010</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;LENDER&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Lender is responsible for providing a loan and has the authority to claim the return of the property lent under specified conditions."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Lender is the entity or individual who provides a loan for use, allowing a borrower to utilize property under specific conditions. May terminate the contract under certain conditions."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-629bbfda7f476a27cd4f982000bd902b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7289405ac6638bb4a476489ae0c1b33d</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 366&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 366 explains that no contract is concluded if the points of agreement are unsettled and outlines uncertainties about written agreements."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-54fa1d3a7c7433d0d90d3817cefe57fa</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;CHAPTER III&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Chapter III discusses justifiable acts and the conditions under which a person is not liable for compensation."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-4b290ec6a69d1ce11295ee43b1785323</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;AMALGAMATION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Amalgamation refers to the process by which two limited companies combine into a new entity."&lt;SEP&gt;"Amalgamation refers to the process where two or more registered partnerships combine to form a new entity, subject to agreement by partners and notification to creditors."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-28aaa22d510e3f49e80675454af7f8a3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-30e7eef2c9f266924b324154eca432d3</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1298&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1298 outlines the creation of real rights according to the Thailand Civil and Commercial Code."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-af5697d7b87ddc73215d01d7439bac2b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;BORROWER&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Borrower is someone who receives a loan and is responsible for maintaining and returning the property or repaying the money lent."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Borrower is the individual or entity who receives property under a loan for use, obligated to return it and handle it with due care."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-629bbfda7f476a27cd4f982000bd902b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7289405ac6638bb4a476489ae0c1b33d</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 917&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 917 involves reindorsement in the context of civil and commercial transactions, indicating legal provisions applicable under specific circumstances."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-54fa1d3a7c7433d0d90d3817cefe57fa</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 449&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 449 exempts from liability those acting in lawful defense or under a lawful command."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 449 outlines legal provisions regarding compensation liability for injury caused in lawful defense or under legal command."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-94b10cff960517b2c4edf0f1af70e53c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4b290ec6a69d1ce11295ee43b1785323</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;MEMORANDUM OF ASSOCIATION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A memorandum of association is a foundational legal document that sets out the structure and purpose of a company."&lt;SEP&gt;"Memorandum of Association is a legal document required for the formation and registration of a company, outlining its structure and purpose."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-d67f818d289a7a42a391ffd601a49336&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-28aaa22d510e3f49e80675454af7f8a3</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1299&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1299 describes the legal requirements for the acquisition and registration of immovable or real rights."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-af5697d7b87ddc73215d01d7439bac2b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE PROMISOR&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Promisor is a person who promises a reward for completing an act or activity as stipulated in public advertisements."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-54fa1d3a7c7433d0d90d3817cefe57fa</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 450&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 450 indicates non-liability for damage caused to avert immediate common danger."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 450 provides guidelines on compensation related to damage or destruction of property in immediate danger situations."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-94b10cff960517b2c4edf0f1af70e53c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4b290ec6a69d1ce11295ee43b1785323</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;ARTICLES OF ASSOCIATION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Articles of association are regulations for the governance of a company and specify the duties of its members."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-28aaa22d510e3f49e80675454af7f8a3</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1300&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1300 covers the rights of persons in registering the transfer of immovable property to prevent prejudice."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-af5697d7b87ddc73215d01d7439bac2b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;LOAN FOR USE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A Loan for Use is a contractual agreement where a lender allows a borrower to use a property for free, with certain obligations for care and return."&lt;SEP&gt;"A Loan for Use refers to a contract where the lender provides property to the borrower for use, and the borrower must return it after use."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-629bbfda7f476a27cd4f982000bd902b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7289405ac6638bb4a476489ae0c1b33d</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE OFFEROR&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Offeror is a person making an offer in a contract, responsible for adhering to acceptance and withdrawal regulations as specified in various sections."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-54fa1d3a7c7433d0d90d3817cefe57fa</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;GOVERNMENT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Government authorizes the creation of foundations as juristic persons based on the conditions in a will."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Government is involved in imposing taxes, rates, and handling claims related to obligations."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-a2aa959400bcd6663682a867aebf2801&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3d46b5b738f6e0830f256b8e2ed69058</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;BOARD OF DIRECTORS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Board of Directors is a group of individuals elected to represent shareholders and manage the company’s affairs following transformation or merger."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Board of Directors is responsible for overseeing the company's management and ensuring that partners comply with financial and legal obligations during conversion and liquidation processes."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-237bd5a5c70b356f874e427eb5f0128b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-28aaa22d510e3f49e80675454af7f8a3</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1301&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1301 applies the rules of modification, extinction, and revival of real rights under the Thailand Civil and Commercial Code."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-af5697d7b87ddc73215d01d7439bac2b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;LOAN FOR CONSUMPTION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A Loan for Consumption is a contract where the lender transfers the ownership of consumable property to the borrower, who must return an equivalent type and amount of property."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-629bbfda7f476a27cd4f982000bd902b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;REASONABLE TIME&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Reasonable Time is the duration set forth for certain actions in contracts, which must be fair and appropriate under the circumstances."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-629bbfda7f476a27cd4f982000bd902b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SUBSCRIBERS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Subscribers refer to individuals or entities who have subscribed to shares in the company and are involved in the statutory meeting process."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-d67f818d289a7a42a391ffd601a49336</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;CHAPTER II: PERIOD OF PRESCRIPTION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"This category discusses the different periods of prescription for various claims and obligations as defined by law."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-3d46b5b738f6e0830f256b8e2ed69058</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE CREDITOR&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Creditor is the entity that can demand compensation or interest for damages and is involved in transactions around default and subrogation."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-2c01a4f68c167448d4624c0e8d938db0</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1302&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1302 extends the provisions to ships, floating houses, and beasts of burden."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-af5697d7b87ddc73215d01d7439bac2b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;WRITTEN EVIDENCE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Written Evidence is the documentation needed to enforce certain types of loans, ensuring certainty and legality."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-629bbfda7f476a27cd4f982000bd902b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;COMPANY REGISTRATION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Company Registration is the formal process of registering the company after fulfilling statutory meeting decisions, including share subscriptions and director appointments."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-d67f818d289a7a42a391ffd601a49336</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 193/30&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 193/30 outlines the standard period of prescription for unspecified claims, set at ten years."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-3d46b5b738f6e0830f256b8e2ed69058</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;DEFAULT INTEREST RATE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Default Interest Rate is set at seven and a half percent per annum, applicable during periods of default on debt."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-2c01a4f68c167448d4624c0e8d938db0</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1303&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1303 deals with the possession and claims of movable property under different titles."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-af5697d7b87ddc73215d01d7439bac2b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;MARKET VALUE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Market Value is the price at which property or goods may be exchanged in the market, used for evaluating loans repaid with goods."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-629bbfda7f476a27cd4f982000bd902b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SHARES&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Shares refer to units of ownership interest in the company, which are subscribed to by subscribers and discussed at the statutory meeting."&lt;SEP&gt;"Shares represent ownership in the company. The company can only mention its capital in documents if the proportion paid up is clearly stated."&lt;SEP&gt;"Shares represent units of ownership interest in a company, allowing shareholders to participate in profits and influencing the management through voting rights."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-d67f818d289a7a42a391ffd601a49336&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-83644292281589f5325e70fbbf9a5034&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4b333b466a8e220c02cd14e77e8fb935</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 193/31&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 193/31 specifies the period of prescription for government claims related to taxes and rates, also set at ten years."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-3d46b5b738f6e0830f256b8e2ed69058</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;MUTATIS MUTANDIS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Mutatis Mutandis is a legal concept indicating that certain alterations have been made to ensure the proper application of a rule under different circumstances."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-2c01a4f68c167448d4624c0e8d938db0</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1304&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1304 defines the domaine public of State including state property for public interest or reserved for common benefit."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-af5697d7b87ddc73215d01d7439bac2b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;RECIPROCAL CONTRACT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A reciprocal contract is an agreement where each party has obligations to the other, often involving the exchange of goods or services."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-23efb3388014eb72630dbca0d161e5c7</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 193/32&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 193/32 discusses the ten-year prescription period for claims established by a final judgment or compromise contract."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-3d46b5b738f6e0830f256b8e2ed69058</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;REAL SUBROGATION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Real Subrogation involves substituting one property for another in the same legal position as the original property."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-2c01a4f68c167448d4624c0e8d938db0</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1305&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1305 states that any property forming part of the state's domaine public is inalienable except by special law or Royal Decree."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-af5697d7b87ddc73215d01d7439bac2b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;PROSPECTUS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Prospectus is a formal legal document that companies issue to potential investors, detailing investment offerings and providing essential company information."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-d67f818d289a7a42a391ffd601a49336</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;EARNEST&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Earnest refers to an initial payment or deposit given to demonstrate commitment to a contract, serving as proof and security for agreement performance."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-23efb3388014eb72630dbca0d161e5c7</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 193/33&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 193/33 lists claims that have a five-year prescription period, such as arrears of interest and various periodical payments."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-3d46b5b738f6e0830f256b8e2ed69058</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;PREFERENTIAL RIGHT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A Preferential Right is a legal privilege that allows certain claims to be prioritized over others during processes such as compulsory execution or bankruptcy."&lt;SEP&gt;"Preferential Right refers to a creditor's priority over others in claims against a debtor's assets, often associated with mortgages or pledges."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-aac23a1f6cf12366451f6be3ff0a3ed2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2c01a4f68c167448d4624c0e8d938db0</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1306&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1306 notes that no prescription can be set up against the State regarding its domaine public property."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-af5697d7b87ddc73215d01d7439bac2b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;FIRST DIRECTORS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"First Directors are initially appointed officials responsible for managing a company's operations and overseeing its strategic direction from inception."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-d67f818d289a7a42a391ffd601a49336</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;STIPULATED PENALTY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A stipulated penalty is a pre-determined sum of money that a debtor agrees to pay if they fail to fulfill their contractual obligations."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-23efb3388014eb72630dbca0d161e5c7</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 193/34&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 193/34 details claims that are subject to a two-year prescription period, including those made by merchants and artisans."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-3d46b5b738f6e0830f256b8e2ed69058</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;INSURANCE INDEMNITY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Insurance Indemnity refers to the compensation paid by an insurance company to a preferred creditor or assured party for damages or loss of insured property."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-2c01a4f68c167448d4624c0e8d938db0</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1307&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1307 affirms that there can be no seizure of State property, whether it is part of the domaine public or not."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-af5697d7b87ddc73215d01d7439bac2b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;BUSINESS OFFICE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Business Office is the principal location where a company's primary operations and management activities are conducted, as registered in official documents."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-d67f818d289a7a42a391ffd601a49336</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 367&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 367 concerns penal offenses related to refusing to provide a name or address to an official."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 367 deals with scenarios where a contract considered concluded lacks agreement on a specific point and explains the validity of other agreed parts."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 367 outlines the penalty for refusing to give one's name or address or providing false information when required by an official."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-3a03e095c966911fdfbf17177a6fd05e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a5d0229c550b9e954016797ed8a8ac12&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-23efb3388014eb72630dbca0d161e5c7</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;FORMER SURETY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Former Surety is an individual or entity that previously guaranteed the obligations of a debtor, and against whom claims cannot be referred in certain situations."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-3d46b5b738f6e0830f256b8e2ed69058</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;LAND REGISTRY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Land Registry is a governmental body responsible for maintaining records of land ownership and rights, ensuring they are known to insurers."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-2c01a4f68c167448d4624c0e8d938db0</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE ASSOCIATION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Association is a collective entity subject to dissolution under specific regulatory conditions, such as bankruptcy, expiration, or non-compliance."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Association is a structured group that operates under specific regulations, laws, and meetings to manage its activities and members."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-182a2b244fdc4ad235c762ab46288dca&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1f4064eab77e56a7c7daab785bacf7e8</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1078/1&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1078/1 defines the process for a managing partner's resignation, including the necessary notifications to other partners and the Registrar."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-855466dea5984defb1f279860dbf5504</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1078/2&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1078/2 mandates the registration of changes in managing partners within fourteen days of such changes."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-855466dea5984defb1f279860dbf5504</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 368&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 368 describes the punishment for non-compliance with an official order issued under the authority of law."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 368 involves the offense of refusing to comply with an official order authorized by law."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 368 outlines that contracts should be interpreted in good faith, considering ordinary usage."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-3a03e095c966911fdfbf17177a6fd05e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a5d0229c550b9e954016797ed8a8ac12&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-23efb3388014eb72630dbca0d161e5c7</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;MERCHANTS, INDUSTRIALISTS, AND MANUFACTURERS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"This category includes individuals and businesses involved in commerce and production, with specific claims subject to a two-year prescription period."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-3d46b5b738f6e0830f256b8e2ed69058</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;ABSENT PERSON&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Absent Person refers to individuals whose whereabouts are unknown, potentially driving legal proceedings concerning their property and rights."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-055e2a0c9f60207819211360d38e04f8</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE COMMITTEE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Committee is responsible for summoning meetings and managing the general and extraordinary assemblies of The Association."&lt;SEP&gt;"The committee is responsible for notifying the registrar of the dissolution of a foundation, according to the legal process outlined."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-86deb2357b8656ccf8680e27cbac71ec&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1f4064eab77e56a7c7daab785bacf7e8</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1079&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1079 deems a limited partnership as an ordinary partnership until it is registered, making partners jointly and unlimitedly liable."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-855466dea5984defb1f279860dbf5504</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 369&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 369 details the fine for tampering with official notifications, posters, or documents."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 369 explains that a party to a reciprocal contract may withhold performance until the other party performs, with exceptions."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-3a03e095c966911fdfbf17177a6fd05e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-23efb3388014eb72630dbca0d161e5c7</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;AGRICULTURE AND FORESTRY WORKERS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Individuals engaged in agriculture or forestry, with specific claims related to the delivery of products for domestic use, subject to a two-year prescription period."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-3d46b5b738f6e0830f256b8e2ed69058</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE MANAGER&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Manager is a person appointed by the court to handle the property and affairs of an absent person, subject to specific legal guidelines and court approval."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Manager is an individual who takes charge of an affair for another person without a mandate, responsible for managing it in the interest of the principal."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-fb415930f5508ba24d6b39a4a2237451&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-055e2a0c9f60207819211360d38e04f8</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;GENERAL MEETINGS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"General Meetings are regular gatherings of members of The Association to discuss and decide on various matters related to the organization."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-1f4064eab77e56a7c7daab785bacf7e8</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1080&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1080 applies provisions of ordinary partnerships to limited partnerships, unless specifically excluded."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-855466dea5984defb1f279860dbf5504</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 370&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 370 details scenarios in a reciprocal contract where a real right is involved, addressing loss or damage."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 370 explains the penalty for creating a noise or disturbance in public without reasonable cause."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-3a03e095c966911fdfbf17177a6fd05e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-23efb3388014eb72630dbca0d161e5c7</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;CARRIERS AND MESSENGERS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Transport workers responsible for passengers or goods, with claims for fare and freight subject to a two-year prescription period."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-3d46b5b738f6e0830f256b8e2ed69058</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;AGENT WITH GENERAL AUTHORITY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Agent with General Authority is a representative authorized to manage the absent person's affairs, with limitations and requiring court permission for actions beyond their scope of authority."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-055e2a0c9f60207819211360d38e04f8</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;EXTRAORDINARY MEETINGS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Extraordinary Meetings are special gatherings called by the Committee or members of The Association to address urgent or specific issues."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-1f4064eab77e56a7c7daab785bacf7e8</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1081&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1081 prohibits the use of names of limited liability partners in the firm name."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-855466dea5984defb1f279860dbf5504</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 371&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 371 describes situations where the subject of a contingent reciprocal contract is lost or damaged under pending conditions."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 371 specifies the punishment for carrying arms openly or without reason in public areas or gatherings."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-3a03e095c966911fdfbf17177a6fd05e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-23efb3388014eb72630dbca0d161e5c7</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;INNKEEPERS AND HOSTEL KEEPERS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Individuals or businesses providing lodging and food services, with claims subject to a two-year prescription period."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-3d46b5b738f6e0830f256b8e2ed69058</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;INTERESTED PERSON&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"An Interested Person is any individual who has a vested interest in the affairs of an absent person and can apply to the court for actions or changes in management."&lt;SEP&gt;"An Interested Person is any individual with a legitimate concern in the affairs of the foundation, who can request the intervention of the court."&lt;SEP&gt;"An Interested Person is any individual with a vested concern in the legitimation process, who can apply to the court for cancellation of a registration of legitimation."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-a0818329731c6e20f0c0c43a0133253c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a8f2d8db15aae9334e2b0c36d4ea99c8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-055e2a0c9f60207819211360d38e04f8</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;MEMBERS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Members are individuals who belong to The Association and have rights and responsibilities, including attending meetings and voting."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-1f4064eab77e56a7c7daab785bacf7e8</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1082&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1082 states that if a limited liability partner's name is used in the firm name, they become liable as if they had unlimited liability."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-855466dea5984defb1f279860dbf5504</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 372&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 372 addresses impossibility of contract performance not attributable to either party and corresponding rights."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 372 lists the fine for quarreling or causing disturbances in public places."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-3a03e095c966911fdfbf17177a6fd05e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-23efb3388014eb72630dbca0d161e5c7</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;LOTTERY TICKET SELLERS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Individuals or businesses selling lottery or similar tickets, with claims for these tickets subject to a two-year prescription period unless specified otherwise."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-3d46b5b738f6e0830f256b8e2ed69058</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;MANAGEMENT SECURITY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Management Security refers to the legal requirement for a manager to ensure proper handling of an absent person's property, which can be mandated by the court."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-055e2a0c9f60207819211360d38e04f8</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;REGULATIONS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Regulations are the rules and guidelines that govern the operations and activities of The Association, including meetings and membership conditions."&lt;SEP&gt;"Regulations refer to the set of rules adopted by the company to govern its internal management and operations, subject to ratification at the statutory meeting."&lt;SEP&gt;"Regulations refer to the specific rules and laws that govern the formation, operation, and dissolution of associations."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-182a2b244fdc4ad235c762ab46288dca&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d67f818d289a7a42a391ffd601a49336&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1f4064eab77e56a7c7daab785bacf7e8</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1083&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1083 requires contributions from limited liability partners to be in money or other properties."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-855466dea5984defb1f279860dbf5504</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;TEACHERS AND EDUCATIONAL INSTITUTIONS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Individuals and institutions providing educational services, with specific claims for fees subject to a two-year prescription period."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-3d46b5b738f6e0830f256b8e2ed69058</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;ADJUDICATION OF DISAPPEARANCE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Adjudication of Disappearance is a judicial decision declaring a person disappeared and setting terms for their presumed death."&lt;SEP&gt;"Adjudication of Disappearance is a legal process by which the court declares a person officially disappeared after a certain period of uncertainty about their status."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-e0099557ffbf92309faf8ac19f118ba2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-055e2a0c9f60207819211360d38e04f8</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SUBSCRIPTION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Subscription refers to the payment required by members to maintain their membership in The Association."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-1f4064eab77e56a7c7daab785bacf7e8</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 373&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 373 declares that a pre-agreement exonerating a debtor for fraud or gross negligence is void."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 373 outlines the penalty for failing to supervise an insane person who is allowed to wander alone."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-3a03e095c966911fdfbf17177a6fd05e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-23efb3388014eb72630dbca0d161e5c7</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1084&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1084 restricts distribution of dividends or interest to limited partners to profits only, and only if capital losses are rectified."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-855466dea5984defb1f279860dbf5504</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;MEDICAL PRACTITIONERS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Professionals offering medical services, such as doctors and nurses, with claims for services rendered subject to a two-year prescription period."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-3d46b5b738f6e0830f256b8e2ed69058</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;BATTLE OR WAR&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Battle or War is referred to as a situation that marks the starting point for calculating the period after which a person engaged is deemed disappeared."&lt;SEP&gt;"Battle or War refers to situations that can expedite the legal declaration of disappearance if a person was involved in them and disappeared."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-e0099557ffbf92309faf8ac19f118ba2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-055e2a0c9f60207819211360d38e04f8</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;DIVORCE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Divorce refers to the legal dissolution of a marriage by the Court based on various grounds such as misconduct, serious harm, desertion, and other specified conditions."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9a509ac47b9337aeb655dc7474ade913</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 374&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 374 describes the punishment for failing to assist someone in danger when help can be given without risk."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 374 elaborates on third-party rights arising from a contract granting them performance directly from the debtor."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-3a03e095c966911fdfbf17177a6fd05e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-23efb3388014eb72630dbca0d161e5c7</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 375&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 375 details the fine for obstructing or causing inconvenience to public waterways."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 375 states that once a third-party right is established under the provisions, it cannot be rescinded or changed by contract parties."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-3a03e095c966911fdfbf17177a6fd05e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-23efb3388014eb72630dbca0d161e5c7</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1085&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1085 makes a limited liability partner liable for greater contributions if they misrepresent their registered contribution amount."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-855466dea5984defb1f279860dbf5504</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;LAWYERS AND LEGAL PROFESSIONALS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Individuals offering legal services, with claims for legal fees subject to a two-year prescription period."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-3d46b5b738f6e0830f256b8e2ed69058</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;VEHICLE LOSS OR DESTRUCTION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Vehicle Loss or Destruction is a perilous event used as a legal benchmark for reducing the period after which a person can be declared disappeared."&lt;SEP&gt;"Vehicle Loss or Destruction is an event marking the starting point for calculating the disappearance period for a person traveling in it."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-e0099557ffbf92309faf8ac19f118ba2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-055e2a0c9f60207819211360d38e04f8</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;GROUNDS FOR DIVORCE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Grounds for Divorce are the specific reasons or conditions, such as misconduct or desertion, under which a divorce may be legally pursued."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9a509ac47b9337aeb655dc7474ade913</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 378&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 378 lists the fine for public intoxication and riotous behavior."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 378 outlines that defenses from a contract can be set up against the beneficiary third person."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-3a03e095c966911fdfbf17177a6fd05e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-23efb3388014eb72630dbca0d161e5c7</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1086&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1086 explains that changes to contributions of limited partners do not take effect until registered, affecting post-registration obligations."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-855466dea5984defb1f279860dbf5504</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 407&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 407 describes the conditions under which a person is not entitled to restitution after voluntarily performing an obligation."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-fcc1f7edc6fff66f0cf31baecb707aad</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;MINISTER&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Minister is involved in the regulation of the liquidation process of partnerships and companies."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-237bd5a5c70b356f874e427eb5f0128b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;REGISTRATION OFFICE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
      <data key="d1">"An official entity where legal and financial documents related to the liquidation process must be submitted and stored."&lt;SEP&gt;"An official entity where liquidators must deposit reports of their activities and accounts of liquidation every three months."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Registration Office is responsible for registering partnerships and companies and recording any amendments according to legal requirements."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Registration Office is the official body responsible for processing and approving the registration of companies, ensuring compliance with legal requirements."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-34e7b7cbd3efe1f3b5bdd00742010ed6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b004bfce3d731fd6bae3b797ccb93662&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d67f818d289a7a42a391ffd601a49336</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 377&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 377 explains the concept of earnest as proof of contract conclusion and performance security."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 377 specifies the punishment for allowing a dangerous animal to roam freely."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-3a03e095c966911fdfbf17177a6fd05e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-23efb3388014eb72630dbca0d161e5c7</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1087&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1087 mandates that only partners with unlimited liability can manage a limited partnership."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-855466dea5984defb1f279860dbf5504</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 408&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 408 outlines specific situations where individuals are not allowed restitution, including actions performed before a due time, after an obligation has expired, or to fulfill moral duties."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-fcc1f7edc6fff66f0cf31baecb707aad</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;LIQUIDATORS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Individuals appointed to carry out the liquidation of a partnership as per the decision of a majority vote of partners."&lt;SEP&gt;"Individuals appointed to manage the winding up of a partnership or company, responsible for settling affairs, paying debts, and ensuring the proper conduct of the liquidation process."&lt;SEP&gt;"Liquidators are individuals or entities responsible for settling a partnership's or company's affairs, paying debts, and distributing assets during liquidation."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-34e7b7cbd3efe1f3b5bdd00742010ed6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-237bd5a5c70b356f874e427eb5f0128b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e319f375a4d832025273d5a023fbe5e9</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;ASSETS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Resources owned by a partnership or company that have economic value and can provide future benefits."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-34e7b7cbd3efe1f3b5bdd00742010ed6</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 378 (EARNEST)&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 378 discusses conditions regarding the return or forfeiture of earnest depending on contract performance scenarios."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-23efb3388014eb72630dbca0d161e5c7</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1088&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1088 states that limited liability partners become fully liable if they interfere with partnership management, but not for involvement in manager appointments or dismissals."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-855466dea5984defb1f279860dbf5504</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 409&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 409 discusses the conditions that apply when a non-debtor erroneously completes an obligation, and the creditor, in good faith, loses evidence of the obligation."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-fcc1f7edc6fff66f0cf31baecb707aad</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;PARTNERS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Individuals involved in a partnership who have shared ownership and responsibilities in the business operations."&lt;SEP&gt;"Partners are individuals or entities involved in a registered or limited partnership, responsible for financial contributions and obligations during conversion and liquidation processes."&lt;SEP&gt;"Partners are individuals who share joint liability in an ordinary partnership and contribute either money, property, or service."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-34e7b7cbd3efe1f3b5bdd00742010ed6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-237bd5a5c70b356f874e427eb5f0128b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ddd247e62a952c755b8e64cbea59a2d3</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;LIABILITIES&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Financial obligations or debts of a partnership or company that are required to be paid to creditors."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-34e7b7cbd3efe1f3b5bdd00742010ed6</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 379&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 379 describes the penalty for displaying arms during a fight."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 379 details the conditions under which a stipulated penalty is forfeited by the debtor in case of default."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-3a03e095c966911fdfbf17177a6fd05e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-23efb3388014eb72630dbca0d161e5c7</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1089&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1089 allows limited liability partners to be appointed as liquidators."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-855466dea5984defb1f279860dbf5504</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 410&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 410 specifies that a person is not entitled to restitution if they perform with the knowledge that the intended outcome was impossible or hindered by bad faith."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-fcc1f7edc6fff66f0cf31baecb707aad</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;REGISTERED PARTNERSHIP&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A Registered Partnership is a business entity that undergoes legal processes for conversion into a limited company or liquidation."&lt;SEP&gt;"A Registered Partnership is a form of business entity whose existence and operation are subject to compliance with legal requirements and can be struck off if deemed inactive."&lt;SEP&gt;"A partnership that has been officially recorded and recognized according to Section 1064, providing certain legal formalities and protections."&lt;SEP&gt;"A registered partnership is a business arrangement where two or more partners manage and operate a business in accordance with terms set out in its founding agreement. It has legal implications regarding responsibilities and liabilities among partners."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-237bd5a5c70b356f874e427eb5f0128b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-30e7eef2c9f266924b324154eca432d3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-691e23128e3c79c43c11b76dcdb0c630&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e319f375a4d832025273d5a023fbe5e9</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;REGISTRAR'S OFFICE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
      <data key="d1">"An official entity responsible for the safekeeping and inspection of the books, accounts, and documents of a liquidated partnership or company for a specified duration."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-34e7b7cbd3efe1f3b5bdd00742010ed6</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 380&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 380 allows the creditor to demand a stipulated penalty in lieu of performance by the debtor."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 380 outlines the punishment for contaminating public water sources."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-3a03e095c966911fdfbf17177a6fd05e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-23efb3388014eb72630dbca0d161e5c7</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1090&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1090 permits limited liability partners to conduct their own business, even if similar to the partnership's business."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-855466dea5984defb1f279860dbf5504</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 411&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 411 states that acts against legal prohibition or good morals cannot be reclaimed through restitution."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-fcc1f7edc6fff66f0cf31baecb707aad</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;LIMITED PARTNERSHIP&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A Limited Partnership is a business entity subject to conversion into a limited company or liquidation, with distinct liability among partners."&lt;SEP&gt;"A Limited Partnership is a business organization with partners having limited liability, subject to legal regulations and potential dissolution if inactive."&lt;SEP&gt;"A business structure wherein partners have limited liability based on their contribution and are not allowed to manage the partnership unless otherwise specified."&lt;SEP&gt;"A limited partnership is a business organization where some partners have limited liability and others have unlimited liability."&lt;SEP&gt;"A limited partnership is a type of partnership where some partners have limited liability, up to the extent of their investment, while others have unlimited liability."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-30e7eef2c9f266924b324154eca432d3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fd4f265f6be599f877d85099036f52dc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-237bd5a5c70b356f874e427eb5f0128b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-691e23128e3c79c43c11b76dcdb0c630&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-855466dea5984defb1f279860dbf5504</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;CIVIL AND COMMERCIAL CODE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Civil and Commercial Code refers to the legal framework governing the procedures related to wills and property control."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Civil and Commercial Code (ประมวลกฎหมายแพ่งและพาณิชย์) is a legal document that governs civil and commercial laws in Thailand, coming into force on January 1, B.E. 2468. It encompasses various sections and provisions addressing different legal aspects such as property, marriage, guardianship, and succession."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-5429b702233c5b142e4f7e7899dffac1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-553b3730ac4ba8b3212a7d230dbc31ad</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1701&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1701 refers to the rules governing the period of inalienability of property, specifying duration based on the type of beneficiary."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-8ddccbf45ec50ee6c41104c7f6c4c61b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;PARTNER WITH LIMITED LIABILITY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"ROLE"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A partner in a limited partnership whose liability is limited to their contribution, with specific restrictions on management and identity use."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-855466dea5984defb1f279860dbf5504</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 413&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 413 covers restitution of non-monetary property, specifying responsibilities based on the recipient's good or bad faith."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-fcc1f7edc6fff66f0cf31baecb707aad</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;LIMITED COMPANY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A Limited Company is a corporate entity that must comply with legal processes to remain active and can be dissolved if it fails to operate or comply."&lt;SEP&gt;"A Limited Company is a type of business entity that is subject to specific regulations regarding inspection, capital changes, and dissolution."&lt;SEP&gt;"A Limited Company is a type of corporation resulting from the conversion of partnerships, possessing all the previous entity's assets, obligations, and rights."&lt;SEP&gt;"A limited company is a type of company where the liability of shareholders is limited to the unpaid part of their shares."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-237bd5a5c70b356f874e427eb5f0128b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-07706a49d3b190ef1fa2b1178a2e275f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fd4f265f6be599f877d85099036f52dc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-691e23128e3c79c43c11b76dcdb0c630</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;GAMBLING AND BETTING&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Gambling and Betting refers to Sections 853 to 855 in the Civil and Commercial Code, regulating activities under this category."&lt;SEP&gt;"Gambling and Betting refers to activities that do not create legal obligations, with specific provisions for lotteries and repayment of gambling debts."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-5429b702233c5b142e4f7e7899dffac1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b004bfce3d731fd6bae3b797ccb93662</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1702&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1702 discusses the conditions under which inalienability clauses apply to different types of property, emphasizing registration requirements."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-8ddccbf45ec50ee6c41104c7f6c4c61b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;TRANSFEROR&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Transferor is a person who transfers ownership of shares to another party and may still have liabilities related to those shares under certain conditions."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Transferor is an entity that transfers the rights of an obligation to another party, known as the transferee."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-6cd60bb5f8e5d886648c66def090b185&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6cd9b0e3cf4adfb36e41fca038140314</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 414&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 414 discusses restitution impossibility and obligations based on the recipient's good or bad faith."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-fcc1f7edc6fff66f0cf31baecb707aad</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SPOUSE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A Spouse is an individual party in a marriage, involved in managing joint and individual properties, as well as family responsibilities."&lt;SEP&gt;"A spouse is a husband or wife in a marital relationship, with legal rights to inheritance under the code."&lt;SEP&gt;"Spouse is a term used to refer to one member of a married couple who may be involved in divorce proceedings if certain grounds are met."&lt;SEP&gt;"Spouse refers to an individual involved in a marital relationship, who may be subject to legal proceedings such as divorce or claims of incompetence."&lt;SEP&gt;"The person in a marriage who may apply for its cancellation based on specific conditions such as duress or fraud."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-cb8c8544779f197bfe5eef0d6b3bba3c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9a509ac47b9337aeb655dc7474ade913&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-359c29184e76341f84467fcf371024a6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9acfb88a2614f5c4b2f078b95a067e71&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c2ac78f2ab241f4845c5c94a44c0ffb6</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;PARTNERSHIPS AND COMPANIES&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Partnerships and Companies are addressed in the Civil and Commercial Code under various sections, including ordinary partnerships, limited partnerships, and limited companies."&lt;SEP&gt;"Partnerships and Companies entail contracts to unite individuals for a common, profit-driven undertaking, categorized into ordinary partnerships, limited partnerships, and limited companies."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-5429b702233c5b142e4f7e7899dffac1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b004bfce3d731fd6bae3b797ccb93662</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;LAWFUL DEFENCE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Lawful Defence refers to actions taken in defense when done legally, exempting the person from liability for injury caused."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-94b10cff960517b2c4edf0f1af70e53c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;GARDEN LAND&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Garden Land is a type of land presumed to be hired for a one-year period under the contract of hire."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-bd6efc93031ebfde67a4ae4a12bbe3ce</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1675&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1675 allows a beneficiary to seek court assistance for administering a legacy that is conditional."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-950a514fa4e2ba58663fe41bd3a39da9</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;COMMAND&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Command refers to instructions given that may influence legal responsibility for actions resulting in injury."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-94b10cff960517b2c4edf0f1af70e53c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;PADDY LAND&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Paddy Land is land hired for agricultural purposes, presumed for the agricultural year, with specific conditions when the contract is terminated."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-bd6efc93031ebfde67a4ae4a12bbe3ce</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;DEPOSIT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A Deposit involves a contract where a depositor provides a property to a depositary, who agrees to keep it and return it upon request."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Deposit is an asset held for a certain period, the right to which the creditor can claim within a ten-year period following receipt of notice."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-629bbfda7f476a27cd4f982000bd902b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8ced30eeca0d6aa10b4e6af82a8bb160</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;IMMEDIATE COMMON DANGER&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Immediate Common Danger relates to situations where actions are taken to prevent widespread harm, affecting liability for damages."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-94b10cff960517b2c4edf0f1af70e53c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;OWNERSHIP TRANSFER&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Ownership Transfer refers to the change in property owner, which does not extinguish the existing contract of hire for the property."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-bd6efc93031ebfde67a4ae4a12bbe3ce</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;RELEASE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Release refers to the act by which a creditor declares an intention to extinguish an obligation, which must be done in writing if originally documented."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-8ced30eeca0d6aa10b4e6af82a8bb160</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;IMMEDIATE INDIVIDUAL DANGER&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Immediate Individual Danger pertains to situations involving personal threat, with legal implications for restitution."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-94b10cff960517b2c4edf0f1af70e53c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;TERMINATION OF CONTRACT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Termination of Contract is the end of a hire agreement, which can occur upon the expiry of terms, loss of property, or other conditions stipulated."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-bd6efc93031ebfde67a4ae4a12bbe3ce</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SET-OFF DECLARATION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Set-off Declaration is the act by which a party indicates their intention to settle mutual obligations by offsetting them against each other."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-8ced30eeca0d6aa10b4e6af82a8bb160</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;CONTRACT OF SALE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Contract of Sale defines the legal agreement where ownership of property is transferred from seller to buyer for a price."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-94b10cff960517b2c4edf0f1af70e53c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;NOTICE PERIOD&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Notice Period indicates the time frame given to terminate the hire contract, typically at least equal to one rent period but not more than two months."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-bd6efc93031ebfde67a4ae4a12bbe3ce</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 338&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 338 outlines the costs associated with the deposit or auction, which are borne by the creditor, unless the deposit is withdrawn by the debtor."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 338 outlines the crime of blackmail and describes its associated punishments."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-8ced30eeca0d6aa10b4e6af82a8bb160&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b04ccf793557331808974ade6067d896</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 451&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 451 details the use of force for protecting one's rights and conditions under which compensation is not required."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-94b10cff960517b2c4edf0f1af70e53c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 493&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 493 outlines the agreement between parties regarding the disposal of property sold and the liability of the buyer if they dispose of it against the agreement."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-ad85db58921b57d9188908867cdfdeba</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 354&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 354 describes the rule regarding withdrawal of an offer when a period for acceptance is specified in a contract."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 354 refers to the initial phase of contract formation, detailing the process and obligations involved in making a contract offer."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-54fa1d3a7c7433d0d90d3817cefe57fa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8ced30eeca0d6aa10b4e6af82a8bb160</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 452&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 452 discusses the entitlements of possessor of immovable property to retain or kill animals causing damage, and related liability."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-94b10cff960517b2c4edf0f1af70e53c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 494&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 494 specifies the time limits on exercising the right of redemption for immovable and movable property."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-ad85db58921b57d9188908867cdfdeba</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THIRD DEBTOR&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Third Debtor is an entity that may receive a court order prohibiting payment, which affects their ability to set off obligations."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-8ced30eeca0d6aa10b4e6af82a8bb160</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 453&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 453 defines what constitutes a Sale contract and the obligations of the seller."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-94b10cff960517b2c4edf0f1af70e53c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 495&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 495 addresses the maximum duration of the right of redemption and conditions for extending it."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-ad85db58921b57d9188908867cdfdeba</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;DOMINANT PROPERTY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Dominant Property refers to the property that benefits from a servitude, where the owner has specific rights to maintain and use the servitude."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Dominant Property is the property benefiting from the servitude imposed on the Servient Property."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-0e69519b80d6cad28fe98f2e9235bd60&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9f9bc4a4809d7c6d989c8e5d2ab6f09f</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 454&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 454 explains how a previous promise of sale becomes effective and the notification requirements involved."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-94b10cff960517b2c4edf0f1af70e53c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 496&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 496 details the conditions for extending the redemption period, emphasizing the need for written evidence."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-ad85db58921b57d9188908867cdfdeba</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SERVIENT PROPERTY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Servient Property is the property that bears the burden of a servitude, requiring the owner to allow certain actions or refrain from certain rights for the benefit of another property."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Servient Property is the property that bears the burden of servitude and may have obligations towards the Dominant Property."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-0e69519b80d6cad28fe98f2e9235bd60&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9f9bc4a4809d7c6d989c8e5d2ab6f09f</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 455&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 455 specifies the time referred to as the 'time of sale' when the contract is considered complete."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-94b10cff960517b2c4edf0f1af70e53c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 497&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 497 identifies the entities who can exercise the right of redemption: the original seller, his heirs, the transferee of the right, or any person allowed by contract."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-ad85db58921b57d9188908867cdfdeba</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1374&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1374 outlines the legal rights of a possessor when disturbed in possession, allowing for removal of disturbance and application for an injunction."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 1374 provides recourse for possessors against disturbance, allowing for injunctions within a year of the disturbance."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-bb67153d31d305a18c3208696a748f1b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9f9bc4a4809d7c6d989c8e5d2ab6f09f</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 456&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 456 highlights the requirements for written and registered sale contracts of immovable property, ships, motor boats, floating houses, and beasts of burden."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-94b10cff960517b2c4edf0f1af70e53c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 498&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 498 explains who the right of redemption can be exercised against: the original buyer or the transferee under certain conditions."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-ad85db58921b57d9188908867cdfdeba</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1375&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1375 addresses the right of a possessor unlawfully deprived of possession to have it returned unless the other party has a superior claim."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9f9bc4a4809d7c6d989c8e5d2ab6f09f</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 457&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 457 describes the cost allocations associated with a contract of sale."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-94b10cff960517b2c4edf0f1af70e53c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 499&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 499 discusses the conditions for redemption reimbursement when no redemption price is fixed."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-ad85db58921b57d9188908867cdfdeba</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1376&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1376 specifies the conditions for the return of property and the applicable Sections concerning Undue Enrichment under the Thailand Civil Code."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9f9bc4a4809d7c6d989c8e5d2ab6f09f</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 458&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 458 outlines conditions under which ownership transfer occurs at the moment of entering into a contract of sale."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-94b10cff960517b2c4edf0f1af70e53c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 500&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 500 outlines who bears the costs of sale and redemption."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-ad85db58921b57d9188908867cdfdeba</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1377&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1377 describes when possession ends due to abandonment of intention or continued prevention from holding the property."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9f9bc4a4809d7c6d989c8e5d2ab6f09f</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 459&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 459 explains that ownership transfer is contingent on conditions or time clauses specified in a contract of sale."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-94b10cff960517b2c4edf0f1af70e53c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 501&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 501 stipulates the condition of the property upon redemption and the buyer's compensation obligation for property damage."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-ad85db58921b57d9188908867cdfdeba</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1382&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1382 discusses acquiring ownership through uninterrupted possession over a specified period, both for movable and immovable properties."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9f9bc4a4809d7c6d989c8e5d2ab6f09f</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 460&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 460 details the process for ownership transfer in sales of unascertained and specific property."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-94b10cff960517b2c4edf0f1af70e53c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 502&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 502 ensures the recovered property is free from any rights created by the original buyer prior to redemption."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-ad85db58921b57d9188908867cdfdeba</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1387&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1387 details the establishment of servitude over immovable property for the benefit of another property, affecting ownership rights."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9f9bc4a4809d7c6d989c8e5d2ab6f09f</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE MINISTER&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Minister has the authority to appoint inspectors to investigate the affairs of limited companies, either by request or on their own initiative, and reports to the Government."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-07706a49d3b190ef1fa2b1178a2e275f</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 503&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 503 sets the obligations for the seller in a sale by sample or description."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-ad85db58921b57d9188908867cdfdeba</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;DECLARATION OF INTENTION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A declaration of intention involves expressing a decision or course of action that is conveyed to another person and is crucial in determining legal actions."&lt;SEP&gt;"Declaration of Intention refers to the expression of will aimed at producing a legal effect, which may be void or voidable under certain conditions."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-933d505d06605d728d8a7325e6245238&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-42327e0a2270d0b8c03bcfa35b359606</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;INSPECTORS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Inspectors are competent individuals appointed to examine the affairs of a limited company, requiring access to documents and the testimony of directors and employees."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-07706a49d3b190ef1fa2b1178a2e275f</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 504&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 504 defines the time limit for claiming non-correspondence to sample or description."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-ad85db58921b57d9188908867cdfdeba</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;ACCESSORY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"An Accessory refers to an object that serves a principal thing, following it unless stated otherwise."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-42327e0a2270d0b8c03bcfa35b359606</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;DIRECTORS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Directors are appointed at the statutory meeting to lead the company and oversee its management after the promoters hand over control."&lt;SEP&gt;"Directors are individuals appointed to govern and direct the affairs of the foundation or association, adhering to its established rules."&lt;SEP&gt;"Directors are individuals elected or appointed to manage the operations and decision-making processes of The Association."&lt;SEP&gt;"Directors are individuals responsible for managing and overseeing the activities and decisions of a company, including financial responsibilities and shareholder communications."&lt;SEP&gt;"Directors are individuals responsible for managing the company's affairs. Their number and remuneration are determined by a general meeting, and they are governed by various rules concerning their appointment, removal, and roles within the company."&lt;SEP&gt;"Directors are individuals who manage the affairs of a limited company and are required to cooperate with inspectors by providing access to company books and documents."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-d67f818d289a7a42a391ffd601a49336&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4b333b466a8e220c02cd14e77e8fb935&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-46940167ee3908fb358c9a82647ea322&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1f4064eab77e56a7c7daab785bacf7e8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-07706a49d3b190ef1fa2b1178a2e275f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-83644292281589f5325e70fbbf9a5034</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 505&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 505 defines a sale on approval, allowing the buyer the option to purchase."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-ad85db58921b57d9188908867cdfdeba</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;PRINCIPAL THING&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Principal Thing is the main object to which an accessory is related and must serve."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-42327e0a2270d0b8c03bcfa35b359606</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;EMPLOYEES&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Employees are staff members of the limited company who may be required to provide information or documents to inspectors during an investigation."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-07706a49d3b190ef1fa2b1178a2e275f</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 506&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 506 allows for the setting of a deadline for property verification when it is not specified in the contract."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-ad85db58921b57d9188908867cdfdeba</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;NATURAL FRUIT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Natural Fruit is a natural offspring obtained from a thing during its normal possession or use."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-42327e0a2270d0b8c03bcfa35b359606</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;AGENTS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Agents are representatives of the limited company who, along with directors and employees, are obliged to assist inspectors in their examination."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-07706a49d3b190ef1fa2b1178a2e275f</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 507&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 507 describes the conditions under which a sale contract becomes unbound if verification terms are not met."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-ad85db58921b57d9188908867cdfdeba</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;LEGAL FRUIT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Legal Fruit denotes things or interests periodically obtained by the owner from another person for the use of a thing."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-42327e0a2270d0b8c03bcfa35b359606</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;COMPANY REGULATIONS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Company Regulations dictate specific conditions under which a limited company operates, including provisions for dissolution and other structural changes."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-07706a49d3b190ef1fa2b1178a2e275f</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 508&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 508 lists scenarios in which the sale and purchase are considered completed after property verification."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-ad85db58921b57d9188908867cdfdeba</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;MISTAKE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Mistake is an incorrect understanding that affects the validity of a juristic act, particularly concerning its essential elements."&lt;SEP&gt;"Mistake refers to an incorrect belief or assumption that can impact legal documents like wills, leading to potential annulment if significant."&lt;SEP&gt;"Mistake refers to an incorrect belief or understanding that can affect the validity of a juristic act."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-8ddccbf45ec50ee6c41104c7f6c4c61b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-933d505d06605d728d8a7325e6245238&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-42327e0a2270d0b8c03bcfa35b359606</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;NEW SHARES&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"New Shares are equity offered by a limited company to its existing shareholders or other investors as a method of raising capital."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-07706a49d3b190ef1fa2b1178a2e275f</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 509&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 509 describes when an auction is completed following the auctioneer's acceptance of the final bid."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-ad85db58921b57d9188908867cdfdeba</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;DURESS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Duress refers to force or threats that make someone act contrary to their free will, affecting the validity of a juristic act."&lt;SEP&gt;"Duress refers to situations where a person is compelled to act against their will or judgement, impacting the validity of legal actions such as wills."&lt;SEP&gt;"Duress refers to the practice of compelling someone to act against their will through threats or pressure and is considered a factor that can invalidate juristic acts."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-8ddccbf45ec50ee6c41104c7f6c4c61b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-933d505d06605d728d8a7325e6245238&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-42327e0a2270d0b8c03bcfa35b359606</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;CAPITAL REDUCTION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Capital Reduction is an event where a limited company lowers its capital either by diminishing the value of its shares or reducing their number, requiring creditor consent."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-07706a49d3b190ef1fa2b1178a2e275f</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 510&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 510 requires bidders to adhere to the auction procedure as announced by the auctioneer."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-ad85db58921b57d9188908867cdfdeba</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;TREE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Tree refers to a piece of vegetation that is subject to legal ownership, rights of removal, and can serve as a boundary marker according to property laws."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-5e64aa2c471a9da88427c4d97b3a6c7c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;AN HEIR&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"An heir refers to a person entitled to receive a legacy or inheritance, but may be restricted by legal and parental consent if a minor or a person of unsound mind."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-4e5197de768063837bf5a455698da0aa</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE ORIGINAL SELLER&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Original Seller is the initial owner of the property being discussed in terms of rights of redemption."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-ad85db58921b57d9188908867cdfdeba</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;LAND OWNER&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Land Owner is a person who holds ownership rights over a specific piece of land and is subject to various legal responsibilities and rights concerning neighboring properties."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-5e64aa2c471a9da88427c4d97b3a6c7c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;CIVIL AND COMMERCIAL CODE (B.E. 2535)&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Civil and Commercial Code (B.E. 2535) is a set of laws in Thailand that govern civil and commercial matters, including inheritance and legacy."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-4e5197de768063837bf5a455698da0aa</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE ORIGINAL BUYER&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Original Buyer is the initial purchaser of the property, against whom the right of redemption can be exercised."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-ad85db58921b57d9188908867cdfdeba</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;ADJOINING LAND&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Adjoining Land refers to a piece of land located next to another piece, affecting legal rights concerning tree roots, overhanging branches, and passage."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-5e64aa2c471a9da88427c4d97b3a6c7c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;CUSTODIAN&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A custodian is a person responsible for managing the inheritance or affairs of someone who is unable to do so themselves."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-4e5197de768063837bf5a455698da0aa</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE TRANSFEREE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Transferee is a person or entity who receives the property or the right of redemption from the original entities."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-ad85db58921b57d9188908867cdfdeba</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;PUBLIC WAY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Public Way denotes a publicly accessible route or path that landowners may seek access to when their property is landlocked."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-5e64aa2c471a9da88427c4d97b3a6c7c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;LEGACY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A Legacy refers to property or rights bequeathed to a beneficiary as specified in a will, often subject to certain conditions."&lt;SEP&gt;"A legacy refers to property or money left to someone in a will."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-4e5197de768063837bf5a455698da0aa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a2aa959400bcd6663682a867aebf2801</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SALE BY SAMPLE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A Sale by Sample involves transactions where the seller provides a sample as a reference for the goods being sold."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-ad85db58921b57d9188908867cdfdeba</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;WATER-PIPES, DRAINAGE PIPES, ELECTRIC WIRES&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"These are utility installations that traverse land, requiring landowner permissions and compensations for installation and use."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-5e64aa2c471a9da88427c4d97b3a6c7c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;RENUNCIATION OF INHERITANCE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Renunciation of inheritance is the act of formally declining to accept an inheritance or legacy."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-4e5197de768063837bf5a455698da0aa</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SALE BY DESCRIPTION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A Sale by Description involves selling goods based on a description, requiring correspondence with what is described."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-ad85db58921b57d9188908867cdfdeba</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;CO-OWNERSHIP&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Co-Ownership refers to a legal arrangement where a property is owned by multiple individuals, with specific rules for management and rights."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-5e64aa2c471a9da88427c4d97b3a6c7c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;STATUTORY HEIR&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A statutory heir is an individual recognized by law to have a right to inherit part of the estate from a deceased person according to predetermined legal rules."&lt;SEP&gt;"A statutory heir is an individual who is entitled under law to inherit from a deceased person."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-4e5197de768063837bf5a455698da0aa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c2ac78f2ab241f4845c5c94a44c0ffb6</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SALE ON APPROVAL&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A Sale on Approval is a contract allowing the buyer to confirm the purchase after verifying the goods."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-ad85db58921b57d9188908867cdfdeba</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;BOUNDARY MARK&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A Boundary Mark is a designated point or object used to define the limits or border between two pieces of land."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-5e64aa2c471a9da88427c4d97b3a6c7c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;INSANE PERSON&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"An individual who may be affected by their mental state in legal decisions, particularly in applying for marriage cancellation."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-cb8c8544779f197bfe5eef0d6b3bba3c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;ROYAL STATE RAILWAYS DEPARTMENT OF SIAM&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
      <data key="d1">"This organization is responsible for the carriage of goods or passengers as per the laws and regulations governing it."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-7c177d209afa32287351a7f88d669f7a</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;REMOVAL OF TREE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Removal of Tree is an event that may be mandated by either landowner if the tree is shared, with costs possibly shared or solely borne depending on the owner's choice."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-5e64aa2c471a9da88427c4d97b3a6c7c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1508&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A section of the legal code addressing the conditions under which a marriage may be voided due to mistake, fraud, or duress."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 1508 covers voidable marriages due to mistakes regarding the identity of a spouse, fraud, or duress, and delineates who can apply for such cancellation."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-cb8c8544779f197bfe5eef0d6b3bba3c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fc29664ee0997602190bcc550d1eddec</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;POST AND TELEGRAPH DEPARTMENT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
      <data key="d1">"This organization handles the carriage of postal articles according to its respective laws and regulations."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-7c177d209afa32287351a7f88d669f7a</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;NEIGHBOR&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Neighbor is an adjacent landowner whose consent and collaboration may be required in cases of land management interference or when changes are made that affect shared boundaries."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-5e64aa2c471a9da88427c4d97b3a6c7c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1509&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A section of the legal code specifying that marriages made without the necessary consent are voidable."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-cb8c8544779f197bfe5eef0d6b3bba3c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;CARRIER&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Carrier is a party responsible for the transport and delivery of goods, assuming liability for loss, damage, or delay unless exemptions apply."&lt;SEP&gt;"The carrier undertakes the responsibility to transport goods or passengers for remuneration in the usual course of business."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-7c177d209afa32287351a7f88d669f7a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7289405ac6638bb4a476489ae0c1b33d</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;PASSAGE RIGHT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Passage Right refers to the legal permission granted to a landlocked landowner to cross adjacent properties to access a public path."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-5e64aa2c471a9da88427c4d97b3a6c7c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1510&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A section of the legal code that outlines who may apply for marriage cancellation when consent is absent and details time limitations for such actions."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-cb8c8544779f197bfe5eef0d6b3bba3c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SENDER&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Sender is the person or entity that initiates the transport of goods, responsible for declaring the nature of dangerous goods and liable for injuries caused if not declared."&lt;SEP&gt;"The sender is the party who makes an agreement with a carrier for the transportation of goods."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-7c177d209afa32287351a7f88d669f7a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7289405ac6638bb4a476489ae0c1b33d</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;CONSTRUCTION OF ROAD&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Construction of Road involves building a pathway through neighboring land for access, potentially requiring compensation for the land used."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-5e64aa2c471a9da88427c4d97b3a6c7c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1511&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A section that details the legal implications and effects of a marriage cancellation judged by the Court."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-cb8c8544779f197bfe5eef0d6b3bba3c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;CONSIGNEE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Consignee is the recipient of the goods, who must surrender the consignment note to obtain delivery or offer proper security."&lt;SEP&gt;"The consignee is the person to whom goods are forwarded by the sender through the carrier."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-7c177d209afa32287351a7f88d669f7a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7289405ac6638bb4a476489ae0c1b33d</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;INSTALLATION OF UTILITIES&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Installation of Utilities involves laying water, drainage, or electrical lines across a landowner's property as necessitated by adjoining land needs."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-5e64aa2c471a9da88427c4d97b3a6c7c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1512&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A legal provision that equates the results of marriage cancellation to those applicable in cases of divorce by judgment."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-cb8c8544779f197bfe5eef0d6b3bba3c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;VISIONS OF THIS CODE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Refers to the legal regulations concerning sales and contracts detailed in the text."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-7c177d209afa32287351a7f88d669f7a</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;LOCAL CUSTOM&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Local Custom refers to community practices or norms that might permit certain actions such as gathering resources from another's land under specific conditions."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-5e64aa2c471a9da88427c4d97b3a6c7c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1513&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A part of the legal code concerning compensation and allowances when a marriage is cancelled and one spouse suffers damages."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-cb8c8544779f197bfe5eef0d6b3bba3c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;RESCISSION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Rescission is a legal right or remedy that allows for the cancellation of a contract under certain conditions."&lt;SEP&gt;"The cancellation of a contract due to unmet conditions, such as delayed delivery when time is of the essence."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-fb415930f5508ba24d6b39a4a2237451&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7c177d209afa32287351a7f88d669f7a</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;WATER-WAY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A Water-Way is a natural or man-made path for water flow across multiple lands, with legal restrictions on the volume withdrawn by each owner."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-5e64aa2c471a9da88427c4d97b3a6c7c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;PARTIALLY TRANSFERRED LAND&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Partially Transferred Land refers to a plot that has been subdivided, possibly affecting access rights and having implications for passage policies."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-5e64aa2c471a9da88427c4d97b3a6c7c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1514&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A section that defines the grounds and conditions under which a divorce can occur, either by mutual consent or Court judgment."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-cb8c8544779f197bfe5eef0d6b3bba3c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;WAY-BILL&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A document provided by the sender to the carrier with specific details about the goods being transported."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-7c177d209afa32287351a7f88d669f7a</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1347-1358&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Sections 1347-1358 are legal codes pertaining to property management, land use, co-ownership, and neighborly obligations in the provided legal text."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-5e64aa2c471a9da88427c4d97b3a6c7c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;MUTUAL CONSENT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"An agreement by both parties in a marriage to divorce, requiring documentation and witness signatures."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-cb8c8544779f197bfe5eef0d6b3bba3c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;CONSIGNMENT NOTE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A Consignment Note is a document that serves as proof of shipment and typically includes details such as recipient, contents, and conditions of the transport. It can be transferred by endorsement unless prohibited."&lt;SEP&gt;"A document requested by the sender and provided by the carrier, detailing the conditions of transportation."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-7c177d209afa32287351a7f88d669f7a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7289405ac6638bb4a476489ae0c1b33d</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;CHILD MAINTENANCE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Child Maintenance refers to the financial and legal obligations parents have to support their children, including providing education and necessary living expenses."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-140da0bea780fb9ec8b35168f6556b93</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;ADULTERY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A ground for divorce involving sexual relations outside marriage, providing the basis for legal action."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-cb8c8544779f197bfe5eef0d6b3bba3c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 596-615&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Legal codes and regulations stipulating the responsibilities and liabilities of contractors and carriers."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-7c177d209afa32287351a7f88d669f7a</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;LEGAL GUARDIANSHIP&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Legal Guardianship pertains to the responsibility of a legally appointed guardian to care for the personal and property interests of a minor or incompetent individual."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-140da0bea780fb9ec8b35168f6556b93</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;MISCONDUCT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Behavior by a spouse that can cause legal consequences and grounds for divorce, affecting the other spouse's reputation or well-being."&lt;SEP&gt;"Misconduct refers to inappropriate or improper behavior by a spouse that can be one of the grounds for seeking a divorce."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-cb8c8544779f197bfe5eef0d6b3bba3c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9a509ac47b9337aeb655dc7474ade913</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;KROMAKARN AMPHOE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Kromakarn Amphoe is an official responsible for certifying and recording the will as per the legal requirements."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Kromakarn Amphoe is a Thai authority with powers and duties related to enforcing legal procedures for wills."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-950a514fa4e2ba58663fe41bd3a39da9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-96ca137e685d301646809ca5adf41812</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 532&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 532 outlines the conditions under which a gift can be revoked, particularly if the donee has unlawfully harmed the donor."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-8ce6f1498128f5fc6034c5e3b827db4f</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;PRACTITIONERS IN MEDICINE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Practitioners in Medicine include professionals in fields such as medicine, dentistry, nursing, midwifery, and veterinary surgery who provide various healthcare services."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-2b194bfa1a18d3dffd302b027ba18352</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1658&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1658 refers to the legal guidelines for making a will by public document, outlining specific procedures and requirements."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-96ca137e685d301646809ca5adf41812</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 533&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 533 describes limitations on the revocation of gifts, specifying conditions under which a gift cannot be revoked after a period."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-8ce6f1498128f5fc6034c5e3b827db4f</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;DENTIST&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Dentists are healthcare professionals specializing in oral health, including the diagnosis, prevention, and treatment of diseases and conditions of the oral cavity."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-2b194bfa1a18d3dffd302b027ba18352</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;AMPHOE OFFICE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Amphoe Office is a location associated with official duties including the recording and certification of wills."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-96ca137e685d301646809ca5adf41812</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 534&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 534 provides for the return of property as per the provisions of the code on Undue Enrichment when a gift is revoked."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-8ce6f1498128f5fc6034c5e3b827db4f</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;NURSES&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Nurses are healthcare professionals who provide care and support to patients, often working in various healthcare settings alongside doctors and other medical staff."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-2b194bfa1a18d3dffd302b027ba18352</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1660&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1660 outlines the procedures for making a will by a secret document, requiring the presence of witnesses and the Kromakarn Amphoe."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-96ca137e685d301646809ca5adf41812</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 535&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 535 lists types of gifts that cannot be revoked on grounds of ingratitude, including remuneratory gifts and those related to moral duty or marriage."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-8ce6f1498128f5fc6034c5e3b827db4f</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;MIDWIVES&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Midwives are healthcare professionals specializing in pregnancy, childbirth, postpartum, and newborn care, providing support and advising women during these stages."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-2b194bfa1a18d3dffd302b027ba18352</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1661&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1661 provides guidelines for deaf-mute individuals or those unable to speak to make wills by a secret document, involving written statements."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-96ca137e685d301646809ca5adf41812</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;VETERINARY SURGEONS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Veterinary Surgeons are professionals who diagnose, treat, and care for animals, both large and small, performing medical procedures and surgeries as needed."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-2b194bfa1a18d3dffd302b027ba18352</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1662&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1662 specifies the confidentiality requirements for wills made by public or secret documents, prohibiting disclosure during the testator's life."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-96ca137e685d301646809ca5adf41812</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 536&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 536 indicates that gifts effective upon the donor's death are governed by inheritance and will laws."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-8ce6f1498128f5fc6034c5e3b827db4f</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;LAWYERS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Lawyers are legal professionals who provide advice, represent clients in legal matters, and interpret laws and regulations to resolve disputes and facilitate justice."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-2b194bfa1a18d3dffd302b027ba18352</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1663&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1663 allows for the creation of oral wills under exceptional circumstances, requiring at least two witnesses to verify the declaration."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-96ca137e685d301646809ca5adf41812</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 537&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 537 defines a hire of property as a contract where the letter lets the hirer use the property for a specified period in exchange for rent."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-8ce6f1498128f5fc6034c5e3b827db4f</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;GENERAL PROVISIONS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"General Provisions are sections within the Thailand Civil and Commercial Code, outlining the basic legal framework and principles."&lt;SEP&gt;"General Provisions refer to the overarching principles that govern juristic acts, including conditions under which acts are void or voidable."&lt;SEP&gt;"General Provisions is a section in the Criminal Code that includes provisions applicable to general offences, covering various chapters such as definitions, application, and criminal liability."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-8db429ff50410ec3964e2dd051739fba&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-42327e0a2270d0b8c03bcfa35b359606&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5b0b36a0f64bbdfdfd692bde041dc3f5</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;OWNERSHIP&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Ownership is the legal right to possess and use property, detailed from Section 1308 to Section 1366 in the Civil and Commercial Code."&lt;SEP&gt;"Ownership is the legal right to possess, use, and dispose of land or goods as dictated by law."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-5429b702233c5b142e4f7e7899dffac1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-880c1ecd6c4ca0a05ce8398767d6a999</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1703&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1703 states that a will made by a person under fifteen years of age is void due to insufficient legal capacity."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-8ddccbf45ec50ee6c41104c7f6c4c61b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;PERSONS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Persons refers to sections within the Thailand Civil and Commercial Code, discussing legal identities and statuses such as natural persons."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-8db429ff50410ec3964e2dd051739fba</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SUCCESSION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Succession includes the processes of heirship, disinheritance, and related matters, described in Sections 1599 to 1619 of the Civil and Commercial Code."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-5429b702233c5b142e4f7e7899dffac1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1704&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1704 provides conditions under which a will made by a person adjudged incompetent can be annulled."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-8ddccbf45ec50ee6c41104c7f6c4c61b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;DOMICILE AND DISAPPEARANCE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Domicile and Disappearance are sections in the Thailand Civil and Commercial Code related to legal concepts of residence and missing persons."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-8db429ff50410ec3964e2dd051739fba</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;ORDINARY PARTNERSHIPS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Ordinary Partnerships refer to a category within the Civil and Commercial Code that covers dissolution and registration procedures, detailed in Sections 1012 to 1024."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-5429b702233c5b142e4f7e7899dffac1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1705&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1705 outlines the invalidity of a testamentary disposition if it conflicts with specified legal provisions."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-8ddccbf45ec50ee6c41104c7f6c4c61b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1706&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1706 identifies situations where a testamentary disposition is void due to uncertain legatee conditions or insufficient property descriptions."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-8ddccbf45ec50ee6c41104c7f6c4c61b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;JURISTIC PERSONS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Juristic Persons are sections addressing organizations with legal rights and obligations."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-8db429ff50410ec3964e2dd051739fba</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;LIMITED PARTNERSHIPS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Limited Partnerships are described in the Civil and Commercial Code from Sections 1025 to 1076, focusing on the formation and nature of these business entities."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-5429b702233c5b142e4f7e7899dffac1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1707&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1707 clarifies that conditions imposed on a legatee to bequeath to a third party are considered non-existent."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-8ddccbf45ec50ee6c41104c7f6c4c61b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;ASSOCIATIONS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Associations are sections within the Code discussing group entities with a common purpose."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-8db429ff50410ec3964e2dd051739fba</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;LIMITED COMPANIES&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Limited Companies are discussed in the Civil and Commercial Code under Sections 1077 to 1095, outlining the nature, formation, management, and dissolution of these entities."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-5429b702233c5b142e4f7e7899dffac1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1708&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1708 allows for the cancellation of a will due to duress, but limits this right if the testator survives free of duress for over a year."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-8ddccbf45ec50ee6c41104c7f6c4c61b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;FOUNDATIONS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Foundations are sections dealing with nonprofit entities established for charitable or public benefit purposes."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-8db429ff50410ec3964e2dd051739fba</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;POSSESSION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Possession is covered in the Civil and Commercial Code, from Sections 1367 to 1386, focusing on the legal aspects and rights associated with possessing property."&lt;SEP&gt;"Possession refers to the possessory rights over a property, including the ability to hold and control it. It involves legal processes for recovering and transferring possession."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-5429b702233c5b142e4f7e7899dffac1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9f9bc4a4809d7c6d989c8e5d2ab6f09f</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1709&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1709 permits the cancellation of a will on the grounds of mistake or fraud unless the testator fails to revoke it after discovering issues."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-8ddccbf45ec50ee6c41104c7f6c4c61b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THINGS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Things are sections about property and ownership laws."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-8db429ff50410ec3964e2dd051739fba</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SERVITUDES&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Servitudes relate to certain legal rights over another property, described from Sections 1387 to 1401 in the Civil and Commercial Code."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-5429b702233c5b142e4f7e7899dffac1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1710&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1710 establishes time frames for initiating actions to cancel testamentary dispositions after the testator's death."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-8ddccbf45ec50ee6c41104c7f6c4c61b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;JURISTIC ACTS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Juristic Acts address legal actions or declarations that may affect legal relationships."&lt;SEP&gt;"Juristic Acts are voluntary lawful acts intended to establish, modify, transfer, preserve or extinguish rights and involve legal intentions between persons."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-8db429ff50410ec3964e2dd051739fba&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-42327e0a2270d0b8c03bcfa35b359606</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;HABITATION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Habitation is a legal term discussed in Sections 1402 to 1409 within the Civil and Commercial Code, regarding the right to reside in a property."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-5429b702233c5b142e4f7e7899dffac1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;CIVIL AND COMMERCIAL CODE AMENDMENT ACT, (NO.14), B.E. 2548&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"An amendment to the Civil and Commercial Code, this legal event modified Section 1702 as stated in Thai law."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-8ddccbf45ec50ee6c41104c7f6c4c61b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;OBLIGATIONS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Obligations are the responsibilities or duties that partners must fulfill as part of the partnership arrangement."&lt;SEP&gt;"Obligations cover responsibilities and duties under legal agreements and their effects."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-8db429ff50410ec3964e2dd051739fba&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-81d63dbc17e3f3707788a6e2552b764c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SUPERFICIES&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Superficies covers building rights on another's land, as described in Sections 1410 to 1416 of the Civil and Commercial Code."&lt;SEP&gt;"Superficies is a legal right granted to a person to own buildings, structures, or plantations on or under the land of another person."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-5429b702233c5b142e4f7e7899dffac1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d6852cd5ceee34402f3999c849ff9c9f</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;ROYAL THAI GOVERNMENT GAZETTE (ราชกิจจานุเบกษา)&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The official publication in which Thai laws are published, ensuring they hold legal force."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-8ddccbf45ec50ee6c41104c7f6c4c61b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SUBROGATION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Subrogation deals with rights transferred to a third party after fulfilling an obligation."&lt;SEP&gt;"Subrogation is a legal principle where one party is entitled to enforce the rights of another, typically involving creditors and debtors."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-8db429ff50410ec3964e2dd051739fba&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2c01a4f68c167448d4624c0e8d938db0</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;USUFRUCT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Usufruct is a legal right that allows a person to possess, use, and enjoy a property owned by another person, including managing its resources."&lt;SEP&gt;"Usufruct is covered in the Civil and Commercial Code from Sections 1417 to 1428, relating to the right to enjoy the use and advantages of another’s property."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-5429b702233c5b142e4f7e7899dffac1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d6852cd5ceee34402f3999c849ff9c9f</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;FATHER&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Father is the male parent of a child, whose legal recognition as the father through legitimation affects the child's status and rights."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-a0818329731c6e20f0c0c43a0133253c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;RIGHT OF RETENTION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Right of Retention is the legal ability to retain property until an obligation is satisfied."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Right of Retention refers to the legal ability of a property possessor to retain property until an obligation is performed."&lt;SEP&gt;"The right of retention is a legal right allowing a creditor to retain possession of a debtor's property until a debt owed by the debtor is discharged."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-8db429ff50410ec3964e2dd051739fba&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bac2de5ec87beec114bb4549e917cb4e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ac44eff8208c6427b97025d89925979e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;CHARGE ON IMMOVABLE PROPERTY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Charge on immovable property refers to Sections 1429 to 1434 of the Civil and Commercial Code, outlining the legal implications of charging immovable assets."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-5429b702233c5b142e4f7e7899dffac1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;MOTHER&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Mother is the female parent of a child, whose relationship with the father can impact the legitimation process."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-a0818329731c6e20f0c0c43a0133253c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;PREFERENTIAL RIGHTS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Preferential Rights involve prioritized claims over assets or debts."&lt;SEP&gt;"Preferential rights are legal claims that give a creditor the right to receive payment from a debtor's property before other creditors, based on certain grounds such as common benefit, funeral expenses, taxes, employee salaries, and daily necessaries."&lt;SEP&gt;"Preferential rights are legal privileges granted to individuals or entities, which allow them to receive performance or benefits before others in specific circumstances, particularly in relation to movable and immovable properties."&lt;SEP&gt;"Rights held by certain creditors that give them priority over others in claims against the mortgaged property."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-8db429ff50410ec3964e2dd051739fba&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bac2de5ec87beec114bb4549e917cb4e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e3fe26f521adf40f2978335cdbc054b9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0ffc320382a3c1523b402789d6bfce44</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;PROPERTY OF HUSBAND AND WIFE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Property of husband and wife is a part of the Civil and Commercial Code, from Sections 1465 to 1493, dealing with ownership rights within marriage."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-5429b702233c5b142e4f7e7899dffac1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;REGISTRATION OF LEGITIMATION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Registration of Legitimation is a formal process where legitimation is recorded, potentially affecting the child's legal status and rights."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-a0818329731c6e20f0c0c43a0133253c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;PLURALITY OF DEBTORS AND CREDITORS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"These sections address legal dynamics between multiple parties in obligations."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-8db429ff50410ec3964e2dd051739fba</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;VOID AND TERMINATION OF MARRIAGE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Void and termination of marriage refer to the legal conditions and procedures detailed from Sections 1494 to 1500 of the Civil and Commercial Code."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-5429b702233c5b142e4f7e7899dffac1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;CLOSED RELATIVE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A Closed Relative is a family member other than the parents who may apply to the court to appoint a legal representative for a child in the legitimation process."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-a0818329731c6e20f0c0c43a0133253c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;EXTINCTION OF OBLIGATIONS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"This concerns the termination of legal duties when settled."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-8db429ff50410ec3964e2dd051739fba</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;PARENT AND CHILD&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Parent and Child section of the Civil and Commercial Code, from Sections 1536 to 1585, details rights and responsibilities within this relationship."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-5429b702233c5b142e4f7e7899dffac1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1585&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1585 describes the conditions under which a guardian may be appointed for a minor who is not sui juris and lacks parents with parental power."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-4c5aad3770b3111c6e3b4171b1b6cb5c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SET-OFF&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Set-off involves balancing mutual debts and credits between parties."&lt;SEP&gt;"Set-off occurs when two parties cancel out mutual debts by settling the difference, applicable if both obligations are due and of the same kind."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-8db429ff50410ec3964e2dd051739fba&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8ced30eeca0d6aa10b4e6af82a8bb160</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;GUARDIANSHIP&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Guardianship is covered from Sections 1585 to 1598 in the Civil and Commercial Code, detailing responsibilities and rights of guardians."&lt;SEP&gt;"Guardianship refers to the legal responsibility granted to an individual or organization to care for a minor when the parents are unable or have been deprived of their parental rights."&lt;SEP&gt;"Guardianship refers to the legal responsibility of caring for and managing the rights and property of a child, which can be partially or wholly deprived from a guardian by the court."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-a0818329731c6e20f0c0c43a0133253c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5429b702233c5b142e4f7e7899dffac1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4c5aad3770b3111c6e3b4171b1b6cb5c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;NOVATION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Novation is the act of replacing one obligation with another, involving the cancellation and substitution of a contract or obligation."&lt;SEP&gt;"Novation refers to replacing an old obligation with a new one."&lt;SEP&gt;"Novation refers to the replacement of an obligation with a new one, altering the original obligation's essential elements, creditor, or debtor."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-8db429ff50410ec3964e2dd051739fba&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d82b5d0a885fc8b96ea11f873f6f0c0a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8ced30eeca0d6aa10b4e6af82a8bb160</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;STATUTORY RIGHT OF INHERITANCE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Statutory right of inheritance is outlined in Sections 1620 to 1645, describing legally defined inheritance rights."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-5429b702233c5b142e4f7e7899dffac1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;MANAGEMENT OF PROPERTY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Management of property concerns the legal responsibilities related to overseeing and handling the financial assets and resources owned by a minor."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-4c5aad3770b3111c6e3b4171b1b6cb5c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;CONTRACT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A Contract is a legally binding agreement between parties outlining terms and conditions about loan or deposit transactions."&lt;SEP&gt;"A contract is a formal agreement between two or more parties enforced by law, covering various forms such as hire or contract of offers substantial guidelines under the Thailand Civil and Commercial Code."&lt;SEP&gt;"A contract is a legally binding agreement between parties, involving stipulations such as rents, terms, and responsibilities in hire agreements."&lt;SEP&gt;"A contract is a legally binding agreement between two or more parties, often requiring specific performance or the exchange of value."&lt;SEP&gt;"A formal agreement between a contractor and an employer regarding the delivery and completion of work."&lt;SEP&gt;"A legally binding agreement between parties that outline terms, obligations, and conditions of their engagement."&lt;SEP&gt;"Contracts involve the formation, effect, and potential rescission of agreements."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-8db429ff50410ec3964e2dd051739fba&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8ce6f1498128f5fc6034c5e3b827db4f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-629bbfda7f476a27cd4f982000bd902b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-23efb3388014eb72630dbca0d161e5c7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-86f6e708f5c93636e3a2e9b024058eac&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bd6efc93031ebfde67a4ae4a12bbe3ce&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7c177d209afa32287351a7f88d669f7a</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;WILLS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Wills are covered under Sections 1646 to 1710 in the Civil and Commercial Code, focusing on forms, revocation, and nullity."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-5429b702233c5b142e4f7e7899dffac1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;CLOSE RELATIVE OF THE CHILD&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A close relative of the child refers to family members, often immediate, who may be involved in proceedings related to the child’s welfare and decisions made by the court."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-4c5aad3770b3111c6e3b4171b1b6cb5c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;UNDUE ENRICHMENT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Undue Enrichment is a legal concept that stipulates a person must return what they have gained at the expense of another without legal ground."&lt;SEP&gt;"Undue Enrichment is a legal principle under the Thailand Civil and Commercial Code referring to scenarios where one party is unjustly enriched at the expense of another, leading to the return of property."&lt;SEP&gt;"Undue Enrichment occurs when one party unfairly benefits at another's expense."&lt;SEP&gt;"Undue Enrichment refers to an increase in wealth or assets gained at another's expense without legal justification, subject to reimbursement."&lt;SEP&gt;"Undue enrichment refers to a legal condition where a person unfairly gains at the expense of another, applicable to the return of Khongman or Sinsod."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-e69f756c60167e54cbfb8769b0011720&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8db429ff50410ec3964e2dd051739fba&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8ce6f1498128f5fc6034c5e3b827db4f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-32f0865d6629c46fe99f13ae20d441f7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fb415930f5508ba24d6b39a4a2237451</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;ADMINISTRATION OF AN ESTATE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Administration of an estate is discussed from Sections 1711 to 1744 in the Civil and Commercial Code, detailing management of a deceased person's estate."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-5429b702233c5b142e4f7e7899dffac1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;JURISTIC ACT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A juristic act is a lawful action intended to produce legal consequences or changes in the legal status of a person or matter."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-933d505d06605d728d8a7325e6245238</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;WRONGFUL ACTS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Wrongful Acts pertain to violations causing harm or loss."&lt;SEP&gt;"Wrongful acts involve unlawful harm to another’s life, body, health, liberty, property, or rights, necessitating compensation."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-8db429ff50410ec3964e2dd051739fba&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fcc1f7edc6fff66f0cf31baecb707aad</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;AUCTIONEER&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The auctioneer is responsible for managing the bidding process during an auction and ensuring compliance with the announced procedures."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-43ec5cbbc3a7ffd98dbfc1b8a6281865</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;REVERENTIAL FEAR&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Reverential fear denotes a sense of deep respect mixed with fear, which is not considered duress in legal contexts."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-933d505d06605d728d8a7325e6245238</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SALE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Sale involves rules related to transferring ownership, liabilities, and exchanges."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-8db429ff50410ec3964e2dd051739fba</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;BIDDER&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The bidder is a participant in the auction who places bids and, if successful, must fulfill payment obligations."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-43ec5cbbc3a7ffd98dbfc1b8a6281865</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;VOID ACT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A void act is a legal action that is considered invalid from the beginning and has no legal effect."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-933d505d06605d728d8a7325e6245238</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;GIFT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A gift is a contract where a donor transfers property to a donee gratuitously, conditional on delivery and specific legal provisions."&lt;SEP&gt;"A gift is a transfer of property or assets made voluntarily without compensation, addressed extensively in terms of conditions of revocation within the Thailand Civil and Commercial Code."&lt;SEP&gt;"Gift covers legal aspects of transfer without consideration."&lt;SEP&gt;"Gift involves the voluntary transfer of property or funds to a minor or any individual, which may come with conditions or require management as outlined by legal provisions."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-8db429ff50410ec3964e2dd051739fba&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-43ec5cbbc3a7ffd98dbfc1b8a6281865&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8ce6f1498128f5fc6034c5e3b827db4f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9926eb44610bf5182e4fad6451742c28</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;EXCHANGE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Exchange is a contract where both parties transfer ownership of property to each other, resembling buyer and seller dynamics."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-43ec5cbbc3a7ffd98dbfc1b8a6281865</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;VOIDABLE ACT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A voidable act is initially valid but can be invalidated by certain parties due to factors like mistake, fraud, or duress."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-933d505d06605d728d8a7325e6245238</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;INTENTION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Intention is the mental state of committing to a course of action, important in the execution of juristic acts."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-933d505d06605d728d8a7325e6245238</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;HIRE OF PROPERTY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Hire of Property addresses rental agreements and obligations."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-8db429ff50410ec3964e2dd051739fba</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;DONOR&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The donor is an individual who gives a property to someone else as a gift under specified conditions."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-43ec5cbbc3a7ffd98dbfc1b8a6281865</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;INCOMPETENT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"An incompetent person is someone legally deemed incapable of managing personal affairs, often under guardianship."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-933d505d06605d728d8a7325e6245238</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;HIRE OF SERVICE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Hire of Service involves regulations for personal service contracts."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-8db429ff50410ec3964e2dd051739fba</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;DONEE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The donee is a person who receives property as a gift from a donor."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-43ec5cbbc3a7ffd98dbfc1b8a6281865</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;EXPATS IN THAILAND&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Expats in Thailand refers to foreign nationals living in Thailand who may seek legal advice and information."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-cced3c5fac31674d85b89a0610b1ee09</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;HIRE OF WORK&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Hire of Work concerns contracts for the completion of specific tasks."&lt;SEP&gt;"Hire of Work refers to the contractual agreement between an employer and a contractor to accomplish a definite task, with predefined terms of remuneration and material use."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-8db429ff50410ec3964e2dd051739fba&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2ce8b9dc980462f61e8da5767b5fa7eb</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;BIDDING PROCEDURE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Bidding procedure refers to the set of rules and announcements made by the auctioneer that govern how the auction is conducted."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-43ec5cbbc3a7ffd98dbfc1b8a6281865</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THAI LAW TEXTS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Thai Law Texts are prepared in the official language for legal reference and are published in the Royal Thai Government Gazette."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-cced3c5fac31674d85b89a0610b1ee09</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;LOAN&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Loan deals with agreements for borrowed resources and their terms."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-8db429ff50410ec3964e2dd051739fba</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;PROPERTY AUCTION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Property auction is an event where a property is put up for bidding, and participants place bids to purchase it."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-43ec5cbbc3a7ffd98dbfc1b8a6281865</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;ADMINISTRATOR OF AN ESTATE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"ROLE"</data>
      <data key="d1">"An Administrator of an Estate is a person appointed to manage and distribute a deceased person's estate as per legal and testamentary instructions."&lt;SEP&gt;"The administrator is responsible for the management, distribution, and general administration of an estate, with specific duties and liabilities as outlined in sections of the Code. They can act personally or by an agent with authority, and must compile the estate's inventory."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-cced3c5fac31674d85b89a0610b1ee09&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-89b8c822a665cc12b23359be3cc927d4</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;PLEDGE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A pledge is a security interest in property given by a pledgor to a pledgee to secure an obligation."&lt;SEP&gt;"Pledge refers to a section within the Civil and Commercial Code covering specific legal aspects from Section 747 to Section 769."&lt;SEP&gt;"Pledge refers to security interests in personal assets."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-8db429ff50410ec3964e2dd051739fba&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b3971476de4ec8b22a6311d4e55caca0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5429b702233c5b142e4f7e7899dffac1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;BIDDING TERMS AND CONDITIONS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Bidding terms and conditions outline the rules and allowances for bidding, including who may or may not bid."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-43ec5cbbc3a7ffd98dbfc1b8a6281865</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1711&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1711 outlines who can be appointed as administrators of an estate under Thai law, either by will or court order."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-cced3c5fac31674d85b89a0610b1ee09</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;AGENCY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Agency describes the legal relationship between an agent and a principal, covered under Sections 797 to 844 of the Civil and Commercial Code."&lt;SEP&gt;"Agency discusses legal relationships where one acts on behalf of another."&lt;SEP&gt;"Agency involves a contract where a person (the agent) is authorized to act on behalf of another (the principal), with express or implied authority."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-8db429ff50410ec3964e2dd051739fba&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b3971476de4ec8b22a6311d4e55caca0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5429b702233c5b142e4f7e7899dffac1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;BIDDING PRICE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Bidding price refers to the offers made by bidders during an auction, determining the purchase price of the auctioned property."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-43ec5cbbc3a7ffd98dbfc1b8a6281865</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1712&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1712 details the appointment process of an estate administrator by will, either by the testator or a nominated individual."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-cced3c5fac31674d85b89a0610b1ee09</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;BROKERAGE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Brokerage involves intermediary services in commercial transactions, explained in Sections 845 to 849 of the Civil and Commercial Code."&lt;SEP&gt;"Brokerage involves intermediary services in transactions."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-8db429ff50410ec3964e2dd051739fba&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5429b702233c5b142e4f7e7899dffac1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;AUCTION RENEWAL&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Auction renewal is the process of restarting an auction if the winning bidder fails to pay the said bidding price."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-43ec5cbbc3a7ffd98dbfc1b8a6281865</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1713&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1713 specifies the conditions under which the Court may appoint an administrator of an estate, including if heirs or nominated administrators are unable or unwilling to act."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-cced3c5fac31674d85b89a0610b1ee09</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;COMPROMISE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Compromise concerns settlement agreements for disputes."&lt;SEP&gt;"Compromise is a legal contract where parties settle a dispute through mutual concessions, requiring written evidence for enforcement."&lt;SEP&gt;"Compromise relates to settlement agreements covered in Sections 850 to 852 of the Civil and Commercial Code."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-8db429ff50410ec3964e2dd051739fba&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5429b702233c5b142e4f7e7899dffac1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b004bfce3d731fd6bae3b797ccb93662</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 511&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 511 prohibits the auctioneer from participating in or manipulating the bidding process for personal benefit."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 511 refers to the legal rule that prevents the auctioneer from bidding or allowing personal benefits in the bidding process."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-43ec5cbbc3a7ffd98dbfc1b8a6281865&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ad85db58921b57d9188908867cdfdeba</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1714&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1714 mentions that court-appointed estate administrators are not required to make an inventory unless specifically ordered."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-cced3c5fac31674d85b89a0610b1ee09</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;MARRIAGE REGISTER&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Marriage Register is a formal registry where marriages and related agreements like ante-nuptial contracts are documented."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Marriage Register is an official record where marriages are entered for legal recognition."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9fb8ecc1d3b7f08bd11bfbe372805373&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d9947bc7fb3e59afe960708bcf533e3c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 512&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 512 outlines the conditions under which a seller can participate in bidding during their property auction."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 512 prohibits the seller from bidding or allowing others to bid unless specified in the bidding procedures."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-43ec5cbbc3a7ffd98dbfc1b8a6281865&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ad85db58921b57d9188908867cdfdeba</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1715&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1715 allows a testator to appoint one or more administrators, and presumes joint administrators cannot act separately unless specified."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-cced3c5fac31674d85b89a0610b1ee09</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;ANTI-NUPTIAL AGREEMENT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Anti-nuptial or prenuptial agreements are contracts between spouses that outline the terms regarding their properties before their marriage."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9fb8ecc1d3b7f08bd11bfbe372805373</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 515&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 515 explains the obligations of the highest bidder to pay in cash upon winning the auction."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-43ec5cbbc3a7ffd98dbfc1b8a6281865</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1716&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1716 states that the duties of a court-appointed administrator begin once the court order is communicated."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-cced3c5fac31674d85b89a0610b1ee09</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;HUSBAND&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Husband refers to a male spouse in a marriage, who has rights and obligations including cohabitation and maintenance as per the legal provisions."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Husband is involved in the legal management of property during marriage, with rights and obligations described in the legal text."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9eea79da373e97e5b9f92916632488ba&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9fb8ecc1d3b7f08bd11bfbe372805373</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 516&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 516 provides for the renewal of the auction and liability for the difference if the winning bidder fails to pay."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-43ec5cbbc3a7ffd98dbfc1b8a6281865</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1717&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1717 provides the timeframe within which an administrator must accept or refuse their role following the death of the testator."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-cced3c5fac31674d85b89a0610b1ee09</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;WIFE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Wife is involved in the legal management of property during marriage, with rights and obligations described in the legal text."&lt;SEP&gt;"Wife refers to a female spouse in a marriage, who has rights and obligations including cohabitation and maintenance as per the legal provisions."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9eea79da373e97e5b9f92916632488ba&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9fb8ecc1d3b7f08bd11bfbe372805373</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 518&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 518 defines exchange as a contract involving reciprocal transfer of ownership between two parties."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-43ec5cbbc3a7ffd98dbfc1b8a6281865</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1718&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1718 lists categories of individuals who are prohibited from serving as estate administrators, including persons not of legal age or mind."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-cced3c5fac31674d85b89a0610b1ee09</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THAILAND CIVIL CODE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Thailand Civil Code is a legal framework governing various aspects of property law and civil obligations in Thailand, including provisions related to possession, prescription, and servitude."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Thailand Civil Code is a legal framework governing various aspects of civil life, including marriage, guardianship, and property relations."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Thailand Civil Code is a set of comprehensive laws governing civil affairs in Thailand, including inheritance and wills."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-6f29560483a94cdf780f52af44990dd1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9fb8ecc1d3b7f08bd11bfbe372805373&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9f9bc4a4809d7c6d989c8e5d2ab6f09f</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 521&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 521 defines a gift as a contract where a donor transfers property gratuitously to a donee."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-43ec5cbbc3a7ffd98dbfc1b8a6281865</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1719&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1719 outlines the rights and duties of an estate administrator to fulfill both explicit and implicit testamentary directions."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-cced3c5fac31674d85b89a0610b1ee09</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;MARRIAGE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Marriage is a formal union resulting from the agreement of betrothal that, if not completed, can lead to return of property like Sinsod or Khongman."&lt;SEP&gt;"Marriage is a legal union between individuals, governed by various sections of the law, which can be voided by the Court under specific conditions."&lt;SEP&gt;"Marriage is a legal union between spouses, characterized by rights and obligations regarding cohabitation, support, and property management."&lt;SEP&gt;"Marriage refers to the legal conditions and implications of marital relationships, covered under Sections 1435 to 1500 in the Civil and Commercial Code."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-5429b702233c5b142e4f7e7899dffac1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-32f0865d6629c46fe99f13ae20d441f7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2f3971fdef62800a7dabb59d8dfbd427&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9fb8ecc1d3b7f08bd11bfbe372805373</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 523&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 523 establishes that a gift is valid with the delivery of the property to the donee."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-43ec5cbbc3a7ffd98dbfc1b8a6281865</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1720&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1720 discusses the liability of estate administrators towards heirs and third parties as per specified legal sections."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 1720 outlines the liabilities of the estate administrator to heirs and third parties, specifying applicable legal provisions."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-cced3c5fac31674d85b89a0610b1ee09&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-89b8c822a665cc12b23359be3cc927d4</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;MAINTENANCE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Maintenance refers to financial support provided by one spouse to another, mandated by law under certain conditions."&lt;SEP&gt;"Maintenance refers to the provision of financial support between spouses or between parents and children, decided by the Court based on circumstances."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-e6503e3e2e955a071268b1be787bc7d1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9fb8ecc1d3b7f08bd11bfbe372805373</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 530&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 530 describes the donor's liability for defects or eviction in the property given as a gift, limited to the charge's value."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-43ec5cbbc3a7ffd98dbfc1b8a6281865</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;ACQUISITIVE PRESCRIPTION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A legal concept that allows for acquiring rights, including servitudes, through prolonged and continuous usage."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-0e69519b80d6cad28fe98f2e9235bd60</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;INCAPACITY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Incapacity refers to a legal status where an individual is deemed unable to manage their affairs due to mental or physical incapabilities."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9fb8ecc1d3b7f08bd11bfbe372805373</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1526&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1526 defines the right to claim living allowances in divorce cases based on the guilt of one party leading to financial destitution of the other."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 1526 provides guidelines for furnishing living allowances to a spouse who is insane or suffering from a communicable disease post-divorce."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 1526 refers to regulations related to claims for living allowances in certain void marriages."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-359c29184e76341f84467fcf371024a6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fc29664ee0997602190bcc550d1eddec&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3eb681d2c9c192f73e0418def1ff82e7</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;HABITATION (ARSAI)&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A legal right allowing a person to occupy a building as a dwelling without payment of rent, subject to conditions and limitations."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-0e69519b80d6cad28fe98f2e9235bd60</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;EMERGENCY MEASURES&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Emergency Measures are temporary legal actions or provisions determined by the Court to protect a spouse in urgent situations."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9fb8ecc1d3b7f08bd11bfbe372805373</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1528&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1528 dictates rules on claiming living allowances concerning void marriages."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 1528 states that if the party receiving living allowances remarries, the right to receive such allowances is extinguished."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-3eb681d2c9c192f73e0418def1ff82e7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fc29664ee0997602190bcc550d1eddec</data>
