    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 1582&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 1582 addresses circumstances under which parental power can be deprived from one spouse in a divorce scenario."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 1582 outlines the legal circumstances under which the person exercising parental power can be deprived of that power, either in part or entirely, due to misconduct or incompetence."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 1582 provides the legal basis for depriving a spouse of parental power under certain conditions."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-4c5aad3770b3111c6e3b4171b1b6cb5c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-359c29184e76341f84467fcf371024a6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fc29664ee0997602190bcc550d1eddec</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;RIGHT OF SUPERFICIES&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A right allowing one to have ownership of structures on or beneath a piece of land belonging to another, which is transferable and inherits."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Right of Superficies is a legal entitlement allowing an individual, the superficiary, to have ownership over buildings, structures, or plantations on someone else's land."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-d6852cd5ceee34402f3999c849ff9c9f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0e69519b80d6cad28fe98f2e9235bd60</data>
