    </node>
    <node id="&quot;DEBTOR&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">A Debtor is a person or institution, whether an individual or an entity, that owes money or an obligation to another party, known as the creditor. Debtors are subject to various laws and regulations, including those concerning prescription and the validity and execution of juristic acts. They have specific obligations and rights under contract law, which include performing the obligation or repaying a debt unless prevented by circumstances beyond their control. In some cases, debtors may be involved in restitution processes if the obligation is impaired, and they can face repercussions for non-performance or improper performance. Additionally, debtors may be required to notify the creditor about certain actions, such as auctions, and could be liable for compensation in the event of a failure to provide such notice. They may also need to acknowledge liability in writing or provide security concerning their financial obligations. The debtor is responsible for fulfilling obligations in a legal context, which can involve giving security, settling payments, or performing certain acts. In scenarios involving co-debtors or multiple creditors, managing obligations can become complex, and the debtor might be liable for any deficit upon the sale of pledged property under a pledge or suretyship agreement.</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-b3971476de4ec8b22a6311d4e55caca0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8ced30eeca0d6aa10b4e6af82a8bb160&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bac2de5ec87beec114bb4549e917cb4e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fcc1f7edc6fff66f0cf31baecb707aad&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c35036965b446b68b1f64bc55f989965&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d45ed62b6b0bfc44f2c1ae4fe430c9c0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5806a4ac5edf0880beed390e35f10ef7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-aac23a1f6cf12366451f6be3ff0a3ed2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d82b5d0a885fc8b96ea11f873f6f0c0a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5352b86091aaab4f6715c44efa017b05&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e7fb2f4e3c8f089ed58aad2cf781f6f9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5f23a6639e72b69e61fefaaa9a0d77c3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ac44eff8208c6427b97025d89925979e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3d46b5b738f6e0830f256b8e2ed69058&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a51405b734dd6683f138a8765370d40b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f92e53c4b928412441b1d00eeb6aab74&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-23efb3388014eb72630dbca0d161e5c7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6cd9b0e3cf4adfb36e41fca038140314&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2b194bfa1a18d3dffd302b027ba18352</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;CREDITOR&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">A Creditor is an individual or entity to whom a financial obligation or debt is owed by a debtor, whether that debtor is a person, company, or partnership. Creditors have the right to demand performance of the obligations, claim payment, and may engage in legal actions to recover debts if obligations are not met. Creditors may receive preferential treatment in debt recovery and can influence legal proceedings, such as advocating for company restoration or interrupting the prescription of debts. They have rights and obligations under contract law and may claim performance from a surety if the debtor defaults. In financial agreements, creditors often permit borrowing with the expectation of future repayment and may be entitled to make claims on behalf of a debtor if their interests are prejudiced. Additionally, creditors have the right to be informed and may bear the costs associated with auctions unless otherwise stipulated. In cases involving estates, creditors can enforce their claims against heirs or the estate under specific legal conditions. Creditors play a crucial role in financial and legal systems by ensuring that debts and obligations are fulfilled.</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-fcc1f7edc6fff66f0cf31baecb707aad&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c35036965b446b68b1f64bc55f989965&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2b194bfa1a18d3dffd302b027ba18352&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-30e7eef2c9f266924b324154eca432d3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5f23a6639e72b69e61fefaaa9a0d77c3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ac44eff8208c6427b97025d89925979e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d45ed62b6b0bfc44f2c1ae4fe430c9c0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bac2de5ec87beec114bb4549e917cb4e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-aac23a1f6cf12366451f6be3ff0a3ed2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5806a4ac5edf0880beed390e35f10ef7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-23efb3388014eb72630dbca0d161e5c7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-237bd5a5c70b356f874e427eb5f0128b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-691e23128e3c79c43c11b76dcdb0c630&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8ced30eeca0d6aa10b4e6af82a8bb160&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a51405b734dd6683f138a8765370d40b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6cd9b0e3cf4adfb36e41fca038140314&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e7fb2f4e3c8f089ed58aad2cf781f6f9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d021e006377bbbff9ec8f8e90f54f2a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE COURT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
      <data key="d1">The Court is a multifaceted legal and judicial institution with extensive powers and responsibilities. It serves as the authoritative body for making legal decisions on a wide array of matters. Its primary functions include adjudicating cases of defamation, theft, and other offenses, as well as handling more specialized legal contexts such as the appointment of auditors when shareholders fail to elect them. The Court has the authority to impose fines, detentions, and social service alternatives and can issue judgments, orders, and determinations regarding the forfeiture of properties and the enforcement of legal obligations. It is pivotal in enforcing legal consequences, administering punishment, and managing rehabilitation under the criminal code.

In addition to criminal matters, The Court also plays a critical role in family and civil law. It is responsible for handling cases related to marriage, including granting marriages under Section 277 and addressing issues of divorce, living allowances, parental power, and guardianship. The Court manages minors' properties and legitimation cases and oversees the fulfillment of testamentary conditions. It also possesses the authority to order the dissolution of associations or to declare them bankrupt, among other responsibilities.

Moreover, The Court oversees processes involving the treatment and punishment of children and young individuals who commit offenses. It ensures the correct performance of guardianship duties, replacing guardians when necessary, and manages legal processes related to child adoption, dissolution, and maintenance. It supervises property management, particularly for absent individuals, by appointing managers and making relevant judicial decisions.

The Court determines compensation for wrongful acts, oversees inheritance matters, and approves actions involving minors and people of unsound mind. It also handles judgments concerning the division of Sin Somros, voiding marriages, marriage cancellations, and declarations of legal capacity. Finally, The Court is involved in managing various legal processes, such as appointing a Receiver, ordering property management, and influencing the distribution of assets through judgments on dissolutions and bankruptcies of foundations.</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-a0818329731c6e20f0c0c43a0133253c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a8f2d8db15aae9334e2b0c36d4ea99c8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cb6f943ed567718e3b0963e9f80b3c0b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3eb681d2c9c192f73e0418def1ff82e7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-268065f480c7c2e17bd0004a31f0f454&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d42bf94e7a02b8cef96bd3ed9bc3ceaf&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-edf03699076f42c474bd2d773c684e42&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ee7dd29b88d53ea4523197532d9851fe&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-30e7eef2c9f266924b324154eca432d3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ce00bf86a210ec770e6555803254e48b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a2aa959400bcd6663682a867aebf2801&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4e5197de768063837bf5a455698da0aa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2f3971fdef62800a7dabb59d8dfbd427&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4b290ec6a69d1ce11295ee43b1785323&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1f4064eab77e56a7c7daab785bacf7e8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6f75e186ae4f2b6f051c224eadc5d322&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e6503e3e2e955a071268b1be787bc7d1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c8c3be6aeb4b1e7e1a17d53346a1d923&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-182a2b244fdc4ad235c762ab46288dca&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-86deb2357b8656ccf8680e27cbac71ec&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bd062f5650ed30bf931f3a519e8693ce&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b3afe90ab72cbd500e64a92888a58319&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7770756870427eb344039070455f889c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4c5aad3770b3111c6e3b4171b1b6cb5c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cb8c8544779f197bfe5eef0d6b3bba3c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bf2e9ba1c433d67ab7eef97426e05cd4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-359c29184e76341f84467fcf371024a6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b23ff2ff58dfd16196c0503c1c3ca1b2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-52f915665c66fcbe0e7563608cbf7287&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d10f80809fc56f611edbadcb4809bc4e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-055e2a0c9f60207819211360d38e04f8</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;COURT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
      <data key="d1">The "Court" is a comprehensive judicial institution responsible for a broad range of legal functions and proceedings. It serves as the legal body involved in trial, adjudication, and issuing judgments, referenced in both criminal and civil codes. The Court is tasked with adjudicating legal disputes, issuing writs or orders, and rendering judgments, with the authority to impose, suspend, increase, or reduce punishments based on various considerations and as per legal guidelines, including those outlined in the Thailand Criminal Code.

As a governmental entity, the Court is empowered to oversee corporate operations, such as appointing or removing liquidators, declaring bankruptcy, and restoring partnerships or companies unjustly eliminated. It plays a pivotal role in personal and family law matters, including adjudicating rights and legitimacy of children, resolving disputes in family law like divorce, maintenance, guardianship, and altering ante-nuptial agreements.

Furthermore, the Court has jurisdiction over matters concerning minors, parental power, and the management of minors' properties. It handles cases of incompetence, oversees property matters, and appoints custodians for deposited items. The Court is involved in decisions concerning the sale and division of co-owned property and disputes related to mortgaged properties. It enforces obligatory actions by debtors, including managing assets under bankruptcy law, and resolves conflicts in estate and will management, particularly in cases involving duress or fraud.

Moreover, the Court holds specialized roles such as authorizing marriages in exceptional circumstances, issuing certificates, and managing cases linked to betrothal agreements. It ensures the enforcement or dissolution of legal agreements, thus facilitating numerous civil disputes.

Overall, the Court maintains a multifaceted judicial role that spans estate administration, property transactions, and enforcement of legal agreements, thereby providing essential oversight and resolution in diverse legal proceedings.</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-4b333b466a8e220c02cd14e77e8fb935&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6674ed785a247829af22e22520fa7260&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-140da0bea780fb9ec8b35168f6556b93&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6e4efb3313af866dc7bcaba7c4daff62&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9926eb44610bf5182e4fad6451742c28&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9acfb88a2614f5c4b2f078b95a067e71&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bb67153d31d305a18c3208696a748f1b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-34e7b7cbd3efe1f3b5bdd00742010ed6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8898310f532e327f554bd8980c0ecbb2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-28aaa22d510e3f49e80675454af7f8a3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c35036965b446b68b1f64bc55f989965&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8ddccbf45ec50ee6c41104c7f6c4c61b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9fb8ecc1d3b7f08bd11bfbe372805373&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d45ed62b6b0bfc44f2c1ae4fe430c9c0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e417732f0f4e36ea8784fa2cc5dd8a85&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-42fad725aa98ee40547f7a36e0de09d6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d82b5d0a885fc8b96ea11f873f6f0c0a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e8a12bcf29dd0e194c7a3e4a71523199&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9a509ac47b9337aeb655dc7474ade913&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f3a1cd577a93157d9b1c759e9c604a8c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-691e23128e3c79c43c11b76dcdb0c630&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-99e04c388a7385a4978847a999d423f1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e7fb2f4e3c8f089ed58aad2cf781f6f9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e3fe26f521adf40f2978335cdbc054b9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ac44eff8208c6427b97025d89925979e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-89b8c822a665cc12b23359be3cc927d4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cced3c5fac31674d85b89a0610b1ee09&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6f29560483a94cdf780f52af44990dd1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3d46b5b738f6e0830f256b8e2ed69058&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-78127285a70d48835c00c4ab2953f9f8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-32f0865d6629c46fe99f13ae20d441f7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a3d4a61fa1cf40d9a40ee60bcdbb217e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-03ac67cce0a415062b1435a1e40830bb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a51405b734dd6683f138a8765370d40b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e0099557ffbf92309faf8ac19f118ba2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e319f375a4d832025273d5a023fbe5e9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e1e198b1f8b66564b0fae2fbe893a4c6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9eea79da373e97e5b9f92916632488ba&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6158dfc7a7c5c354484d988186bd2709&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6fd5b0ac67c6f4aafc6e1ef0e7ce2a77&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-94b10cff96051