    <node id="&quot;ELECTRONIC DATA&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Electronic Data refers to information stored or transmitted in electronic form, such as data, ciphers, account numbers, and electronic figures used to demonstrate relationships or identities."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-06264e1a1856b06042c54819d14b26b6</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;ELECTRONIC CARD FORGERY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Electronic Card Forgery refers to the unlawful creation of a counterfeit electronic card to deceive others, punishable by law under sections described."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-226c50ebda82206e6ae01871ad28a3a3</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 178&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 178 covers penalties for rendering incorrect translations in legal proceedings."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-e417732f0f4e36ea8784fa2cc5dd8a85</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 110&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 110 outlines legal consequences for acts of violence or threats against the monarchy and key state figures."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-5206f82195413280707c7f3a4938d1ba</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 307&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 307 describes the punishment for abandoning a person in a helpless condition, potentially endangering their life."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-79d122542ad136d4651dd10f0c3f5ced</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;OFFENCES RELATING TO THE SECURITY OF THE KINGDOM&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Offences Relating to the Security of the Kingdom are crimes that threaten the nation's security and are covered under sections 107 to 129 of the law."&lt;SEP&gt;"These are specific legal offences that threaten national security as defined in Sections 107 to 135."&lt;SEP&gt;"This category includes offences as provided in Sections 107 to 135, concerning acts that threaten the security and integrity of the kingdom."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-06264e1a1856b06042c54819d14b26b6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a3d4a61fa1cf40d9a40ee60bcdbb217e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bd062f5650ed30bf931f3a519e8693ce</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;ACT AMENDING THE CRIMINAL CODE (NO. 17), B.E. 2547&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"This event refers to the legislative amendment made to the Criminal Code, which prescribed and added sections related to electronic card offenses."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-226c50ebda82206e6ae01871ad28a3a3</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 111&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 111 describes the punishment for supporting offences related to sections concerning state and monarchy security."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-5206f82195413280707c7f3a4938d1ba</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 308&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 308 details the consequences and punishments if the abandonment described in Sections 306 or 307 results in death or serious harm."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-79d122542ad136d4651dd10f0c3f5ced</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;OFFENCES IN RESPECT OF TERRORIZATION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Offences in Respect of Terrorization involve acts of violence or intimidation defined under sections 135/1 to 135/4."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-06264e1a1856b06042c54819d14b26b6</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;TRADE OFFENSE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Trade Offense encompasses illegal activities related to the misconduct in trade, such as fraud and forgery, as defined under specific sections."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-226c50ebda82206e6ae01871ad28a3a3</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 112&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 112 outlines penalties for defaming, insulting, or threatening the monarchy."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-5206f82195413280707c7f3a4938d1ba</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 309&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 309 defines the offence of compelling a person to do or not do something under threat or violence, detailing associated punishments."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-79d122542ad136d4651dd10f0c3f5ced</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;OFFENCES RELATING TO COUNTERFEITING AND ALTERATION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Offences Relating to Counterfeiting and Alteration pertain to the illegal creation or modification of official documents or currency, specified in sections 240 to 266."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-06264e1a1856b06042c54819d14b26b6</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 269/2&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 269/2 discusses the creation of instruments or materials for counterfeiting or altering electronic cards, including the penalties for such actions."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-226c50ebda82206e6ae01871ad28a3a3</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 113&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 113 describes acts considered insurrection, with severe penalties for threatening state powers."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-5206f82195413280707c7f3a4938d1ba</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 310&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 310 outlines the punishment for detaining or confining a person against their will."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-79d122542ad136d4651dd10f0c3f5ced</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;OFFENCE RELATING TO ROBBERY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Offence Relating to Robbery includes crimes involving theft with violence or intimidation, covered under sections 339 and 340."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-06264e1a1856b06042c54819d14b26b6</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 269/3&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 269/3 refers to the act of bringing into or sending out items as per the forgery offenses in Section 269/1 or Section 269/2, detailing the legal repercussions."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-226c50ebda82206e6ae01871ad28a3a3</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;PUBLIC PEACE OFFENSE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Public Peace Offense includes acts that disrupt public peace, such as secret societies, criminal associations, or violent assemblies within Thailand."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-1429bffff14b8577c8748fc8f14a6678</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 114&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 114 covers acts of conspiracy or preparation for insurrection against the state."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-5206f82195413280707c7f3a4938d1ba</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 310 BIS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 310 bis extends Section 310 by adding circumstances where the detainee is forced to perform acts benefiting the offender."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-79d122542ad136d4651dd10f0c3f5ced</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;MALFEASANCE IN OFFICE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Malfeasance in Office refers to illegal or dishonest actions performed by public officials while in office."&lt;SEP&gt;"Referring to Sections 147 to 166, this category addresses misconduct or illegal acts committed by individuals in positions of public trust or authority."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-37adf4ae405c50d2a9e02b9fbd91341e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a3d4a61fa1cf40d9a40ee60bcdbb217e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 269/4&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 269/4 describes the penalties for using or possessing counterfeit electronic cards, as well as selling such items."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-226c50ebda82206e6ae01871ad28a3a3</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 311&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 311 prescribes the punishment for negligently causing someone to be detained or confined."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-79d122542ad136d4651dd10f0c3f5ced</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;STATE LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The State Legislative Assembly is a governmental body in Thailand with members involved in legislative activities and subjected to legal regulations and penalties under the Criminal Code."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-37adf4ae405c50d2a9e02b9fbd91341e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 269/5&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 269/5 specifies the punishment for wrongful use of another person's electronic card, in a manner that could cause harm."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-226c50ebda82206e6ae01871ad28a3a3</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 116&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 116 describes punishments for public acts aimed at unrest or legal transgression."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-5206f82195413280707c7f3a4938d1ba</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 312&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 312 defines acts related to slavery, including transporting, selling, or restraining persons, and their respective penalties."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-79d122542ad136d4651dd10f0c3f5ced</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;PROVINCIAL ASSEMBLY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Provincial Assembly is a regional governing body in Thailand with members responsible for legislative matters at the provincial level and subject to legal standards."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-37adf4ae405c50d2a9e02b9fbd91341e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 269/6&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 269/6 expands on Section 269/5, detailing additional penalties for wrongful use of electronic cards to cause detriment."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-226c50ebda82206e6ae01871ad28a3a3</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 117&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 117 governs legal consequences for strikes, lockouts, or business interruptions with political aims."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-5206f82195413280707c7f3a4938d1ba</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 312 BIS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A section added to the criminal code outlining penalties for causing grievous bodily harm, including life imprisonment or a set term of years."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 312 bis adds additional punishments for offences involved in the trafficking of children under 15, addressing degrees of harm caused."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-79d122542ad136d4651dd10f0c3f5ced&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d23931e05623c30bf7072dff6eb48dd5</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;MUNICIPAL ASSEMBLY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Municipal Assembly is a local governmental institution in Thailand, managing municipal legislative functions and regulations as outlined in the Criminal Code."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-37adf4ae405c50d2a9e02b9fbd91341e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 269/7&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 269/7 mentions penalties for offenses related to electronic cards used as payment instruments, with increased penalties."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-226c50ebda82206e6ae01871ad28a3a3</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 118&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 118 details legal penalties for acts against symbols of the state that are intended to deride the nation."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-5206f82195413280707c7f3a4938d1ba</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THAI CRIMINAL CODE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Thai Criminal Code is the set of laws in Thailand that defines criminal offenses and their corresponding penalties."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-79d122542ad136d4651dd10f0c3f5ced</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;CHANGWAT ASSEMBLY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Changwat Assembly is a local governmental entity in Thailand, participating in legislative processes at the changwat (provincial) level and falling within the jurisdiction of legal provisions."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-37adf4ae405c50d2a9e02b9fbd91341e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 270&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 270 addresses the use or possession of non-standard measuring instruments for trade advantages and the associated penalties."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-226c50ebda82206e6ae01871ad28a3a3</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 119&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 119 focuses on acts intended to compromise the sovereignty of the state."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-5206f82195413280707c7f3a4938d1ba</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;FOREIGN GOVERNMENT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Foreign Government refers to governmental bodies of countries other than Thailand."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-526a0b152c10330561e4c72c14e89416</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE MUNICIPALITY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Municipality is a local government entity in Thailand mentioned in the context of being potentially harmed by malfeasance of officials under the Thai Criminal Code."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Municipality refers to a local government organization or administrative division that can suffer damage due to wrongful actions by officials."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-37adf4ae405c50d2a9e02b9fbd91341e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-de71dcf326342843893937651bd927f6</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 271&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 271 involves selling goods through deceitful means to deceive buyers about the goods' origin, quality, or quantity."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-226c50ebda82206e6ae01871ad28a3a3</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;CRIMINAL CODE, B.E. 2499 (1956)&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Criminal Code, B.E. 2499 (1956), is a legal document outlining the statutory framework for criminal law in Thailand. It has been amended up to No. 17, B.E. 2547 (2003)."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-5b0b36a0f64bbdfdfd692bde041dc3f5</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 120&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 120 describes conspiracy with foreign states to act against the nation."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-5206f82195413280707c7f3a4938d1ba</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECURITY COUNCIL OF THE UNITED NATIONS ORGANIZATION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Security Council of the United Nations Organization is responsible for maintaining international peace and security, capable of designating terror groups."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-526a0b152c10330561e4c72c14e89416</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE SANITATION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Sanitation is presumably a government-related entity involved in public health and sanitation, referenced in the document concerning legal impacts from wrongful acts by officials."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-37adf4ae405c50d2a9e02b9fbd91341e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;A CHILD NOT YET OVER SEVEN YEARS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"This refers to children under the age of seven who are exempt from punishment for committing offences, as outlined in Section 73."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-52f915665c66fcbe0e7563608cbf7287</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;BHUMIBOL ADULYADEJ&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Bhumibol Adulyadej was the King of Thailand who reigned during the enactment of the Criminal Code, B.E. 2499, and proclaimed its promulgation."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-5b0b36a0f64bbdfdfd692bde041dc3f5</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 121&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 121 outlines penalties for Thai nationals who bear arms against their own country."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-5206f82195413280707c7f3a4938d1ba</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;NATIONAL ADMINISTRATIVE REFORM COUNCIL IN B.E. 2519&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The National Administrative Reform Council in B.E. 2519 was a body involved in reforming administration in Thailand."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-526a0b152c10330561e4c72c14e89416</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 86&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 86 refers to specific legal provisions related to the liability of supporters, instigators, and publishers in the commission of offences."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-bd062f5650ed30bf931f3a519e8693ce</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;A CHILD OVER SEVEN YEARS BUT NOT YET OVER FOURTEEN YEARS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"This category includes children between the ages of seven and fourteen, who may not be punished for offences but are subject to Court intervention as described in Section 74."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-52f915665c66fcbe0e7563608cbf7287</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;CRIMINAL ASSOCIATION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A criminal association consists of individuals who conspire to commit offenses punishable by laws in Thailand."&lt;SEP&gt;"Criminal Association refers to a group engaged in illegal activities, sometimes mentioned in laws regarding public safety."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-1429bffff14b8577c8748fc8f14a6678&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-526a0b152c10330561e4c72c14e89416</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE ASSEMBLY OF THE PEOPLE'S REPRESENTATIVES&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Assembly of the People's Representatives is the legislative body in Thailand that provided advice and consent for enacting the Criminal Code, B.E. 2499."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-5b0b36a0f64bbdfdfd692bde041dc3f5</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 122&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 122 includes legal repercussions for assisting enemies in battle against the country."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-5206f82195413280707c7f3a4938d1ba</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;NATIONAL EXECUTIVE COUNCIL IN B.E. 2514&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The National Executive Council in B.E. 2514 was a governing body responsible for legislative decrees in Thailand."&lt;SEP&gt;"The National Executive Council is a governing body responsible for issuing decrees, such as those that amend the Criminal Code in Thailand."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-526a0b152c10330561e4c72c14e89416&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4d20d8c7e43c4c0033ebd04d8b30c380</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 88&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 88 outlines the legal conditions under which a supporter or instigator is liable for punishment if an offence is not completed."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-bd062f5650ed30bf931f3a519e8693ce</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;PERSON OVER FOURTEEN YEARS BUT NOT YET OVER SEVENTEEN YEARS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"This refers to individuals aged between fourteen and seventeen, whose sense of responsibility is considered when deciding enforcement of punishment, as mentioned in Section 75."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-52f915665c66fcbe0e7563608cbf7287</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 273&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 273 addresses the forging of a registered trademark of another person, stating that the punishment involves imprisonment for up to three years or a fine not exceeding six thousand Baht, or both."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 273 outlines the offense of forging another's registered trademark, detailing its legal consequences."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-226c50ebda82206e6ae01871ad28a3a3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bf2e9ba1c433d67ab7eef97426e05cd4</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;STATE'S PROPERTY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"State's Property refers to assets or resources owned by any government entity that could be target of injurious acts."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-526a0b152c10330561e4c72c14e89416</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 89&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 89 focuses on the application of personal circumstances that can alter punishments in legal offences."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-bd062f5650ed30bf931f3a519e8693ce</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;PERSON OUT OF SEVENTEEN YEARS BUT NOT OUT OF TWENTY YEARS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"This category involves individuals aged seventeen to twenty, where the Court can reduce their punishment scale, according to Section 76."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-52f915665c66fcbe0e7563608cbf7287</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;PERSON'S PROPERTY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Person's Property involves assets owned by individuals that can be harmed under legal definitions."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-526a0b152c10330561e4c72c14e89416</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SPECIFIC OFFENCES&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Specific Offences is a section in the Criminal Code detailing offences related to various aspects such as the security of the kingdom, public administration, and justice."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-5b0b36a0f64bbdfdfd692bde041dc3f5</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 274&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 274 describes imitating another's registered trademark to mislead the public, specifying the penalties involved."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 274 pertains to the imitation of a registered trademark with the intent to deceive the public, with penalties including imprisonment up to one year or a fine not exceeding two thousand Baht, or both."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-226c50ebda82206e6ae01871ad28a3a3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bf2e9ba1c433d67ab7eef97426e05cd4</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 90&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 90 addresses the application of the severest punishment for acts violating multiple legal provisions."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-bd062f5650ed30bf931f3a519e8693ce</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 275&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 275 deals with bringing, disposing, or exposing goods bearing forged or imitated trademarks into the Kingdom, punishable as prescribed in Sections 273 or 274."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-bf2e9ba1c433d67ab7eef97426e05cd4</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;ECONOMIC INJURY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Economic Injury refers to harm or damage that causes financial loss or affects the economic health of a state or person."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-526a0b152c10330561e4c72c14e89416</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 91&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 91 provides guidelines for imposing and limiting cumulative punishments for distinct offences."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-bd062f5650ed30bf931f3a519e8693ce</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;PROBATION OFFICER OR ANY OTHER OFFICIAL&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"These are officials appointed by the Court to control the behavior of a child, ensuring adherence to conditions set forth under Section 74."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-52f915665c66fcbe0e7563608cbf7287</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;LEGAL REFORMS OF B.E. 2451&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Legal Reforms of B.E. 2451 refer to the previous set of criminal laws in Thailand that the Criminal Code B.E. 2499 was intended to update."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-5b0b36a0f64bbdfdfd692bde041dc3f5</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 276&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 276 concerns sexual intercourse with a woman against her will, detailing severe penalties including imprisonment for four to twenty years and fines between eight thousand to forty thousand Baht, or life imprisonment in aggravated cases."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 276 of the Thai Criminal Code deals with offenses related to sexual violence or coercion."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-79d122542ad136d4651dd10f0c3f5ced&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bf2e9ba1c433d67ab7eef97426e05cd4</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;DISORDER&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Disorder refers to a state of confusion or disruption, often related to public peace and security."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-526a0b152c10330561e4c72c14e89416</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 92&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 92 deals with increasing punishments for repeat offenders during or shortly after completing a previous sentence."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-bd062f5650ed30bf931f3a519e8693ce</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;PERSON OR ORGANIZATION TAKING CARE OF CHILD&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
      <data key="d1">"This pertains to a person or organization appointed by the Court to take care of, train, and instruct a child when parents or guardians are unable or unwilling to do so, as described in Section 74 (4)."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-52f915665c66fcbe0e7563608cbf7287</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;PUNISHMENTS AND MEASURES OF SAFETY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Punishments and Measures of Safety is a category in the Criminal Code covering aspects such as punishment types, safety measures, and suspension of punishment."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-5b0b36a0f64bbdfdfd692bde041dc3f5</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 277&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 277 covers sexual intercourse with a girl under fifteen years old, imposing penalties from four to twenty years of imprisonment and fines. Aggravated cases, such as involving a girl under thirteen, result in harsher penalties."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 277 focuses on statutory rape and the legal repercussions associated with it."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-79d122542ad136d4651dd10f0c3f5ced&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bf2e9ba1c433d67ab7eef97426e05cd4</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;TERRORIZATION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Terrorization involves acts aimed to instill fear or coerce governments or organizations into action or inaction."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-526a0b152c10330561e4c72c14e89416</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 93&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 93 specifies increased punishments for repeat offences related to national security, given certain conditions are met."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-bd062f5650ed30bf931f3a519e8693ce</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SCHOOL OR PLACE OF TRAINING AND INSTRUCTION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
      <data key="d1">"This includes institutions where children may be sent by the Court for training and instruction under Section 74 (5)."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-52f915665c66fcbe0e7563608cbf7287</data>
    </node>
