    </node>
    <node id="&quot;CRIMINAL CODE AMENDMENT ACT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Criminal Code Amendment Act encompasses legislative changes to the criminal code, detailing various offences and their legal implications."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-78de612c5be2681a856b09899b977bd3</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;ACT AMENDING THE CRIMINAL CODE (NO. 16), B.E 2546&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"This is a legal amendment that alters sections of the existing legal code, such as the procedures for capital punishment and life imprisonment."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-e8a12bcf29dd0e194c7a3e4a71523199</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;COUNTERFEITING AND ALTERATION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Counterfeiting and Alteration refer to illegal activities involving the unauthorized fabrication or modification of items, as defined in specific sections of the criminal code."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-78de612c5be2681a856b09899b977bd3</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;MEASURES OF SAFETY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Measures of Safety are legal provisions applied to individuals to ensure public safety, potentially modifying or replacing punishments under certain legal conditions."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-e8a12bcf29dd0e194c7a3e4a71523199</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;OFFENCE RELATING TO ROBBERY AND GANG-ROBBERY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Robbery and Gang-Robbery involve the illegal taking of property from someone with intent to permanently deprive them, often with force or intimidation, as detailed in relevant sections."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-78de612c5be2681a856b09899b977bd3</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 266&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 266 lists specific documents, such as wills and share certificates, whose forgery incurs severe penalties."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-0821966abff87f794597de47538cc67e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;DEATH&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Death as a capital punishment is the most severe penalty within the legal system, typically administered by injection of toxin and outlined by regulations from the Ministry of Justice."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-e8a12bcf29dd0e194c7a3e4a71523199</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;OFFENCES RELATING TO CAUSE PUBLIC DANGERS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"These offences involve actions that cause danger to the public, encompassing a range of acts outlined in various sections of the criminal code."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-78de612c5be2681a856b09899b977bd3</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;CONFINEMENT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Confinement is a lesser form of imprisonment, typically involving restricted liberty without the length or severity of formal imprisonment."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-e8a12bcf29dd0e194c7a3e4a71523199</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;JUDICIAL OFFICIALS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Judicial Officials refer to public prosecutors, officials conducting cases, and inquiry officials involved in judicial processes."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-e1e198b1f8b66564b0fae2fbe893a4c6</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 267&quot;">
