      <data key="d1">"An authority involved in amending laws in Thailand, as seen in Section 218 of the Thai Penal Code related to public danger offenses."&lt;SEP&gt;"The National Executive Council is a governing body involved in enacting and amending legal decrees and articles in Thailand."&lt;SEP&gt;"The National Executive Council is an authoritative body responsible for decreeing amendments, impacting the legal provisions stated."&lt;SEP&gt;"The National Executive Council is involved in amending legal articles and decrees within the criminal code, as indicated by the amendments mentioned in the sections."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-1429bffff14b8577c8748fc8f14a6678&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8898310f532e327f554bd8980c0ecbb2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-268065f480c7c2e17bd0004a31f0f454&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b04ccf793557331808974ade6067d896</data>
