    <node id="&quot;ROYAL COURT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Royal Court is the official residence and administrative center of the Sovereign and royal government."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-4d74317714e19def34fd622d8bf7eee3</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 312 TER&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A section introduced to address offenses such as dishonestly taking away a person aged over fifteen but not yet eighteen, with specific imprisonments and fines as penalties."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-d23931e05623c30bf7072dff6eb48dd5</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 101&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 101 specifies conditions related to the execution of court orders and the timeframe restrictions for payment orders."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-6d1b2dd52957470e3d89b1c4d7b09769</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SEA-GOING VESSEL&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Sea-going vessel refers to large ships used for transport, subject to legal regulations for passenger and operator safety."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-3aa47916d44030b53f9aac3e17c9da38</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 304&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 304 describes that attempts at certain offences related to abortion may not be punishable."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-d0507d79984fa42096d2e2bed7526a91</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THAI CRIMINAL CODE SECTION 387&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 387 specifies fines for placing objects that might fall and cause harm in public areas, with penalties of up to five hundred Baht."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-d274c9e863fb793abab4dc5884e523b8</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;INTERNATIONAL ORGANIZATION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
      <data key="d1">"An International Organization is a group inclusive of multiple countries working together, often for diplomacy or global issues."&lt;SEP&gt;"International Organization refers to entities beyond individual governments involved in global governance or diplomacy."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-4d74317714e19def34fd622d8bf7eee3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-526a0b152c10330561e4c72c14e89416</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 313&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A criminal code section specifying penalties for offenses involving taking away a person for ransom using deceitful or coercive means."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-d23931e05623c30bf7072dff6eb48dd5</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 102&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 102 defines petty offences as minor legal infractions with specific penalties including limited imprisonment or fines."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-6d1b2dd52957470e3d89b1c4d7b09769</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;WELL&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Wells are sources of water that can be subject to poisoning, thus are included in legal regulations for public safety."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-3aa47916d44030b53f9aac3e17c9da38</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 305&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 305 of the Thai law outlines the conditions under which a medical practitioner may not be guilty of offences related to abortion if it is necessary for the health of the woman or if the pregnancy resulted from certain offences."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 305 provides circumstances under which medical practitioners can perform abortions legally."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-d0507d79984fa42096d2e2bed7526a91&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-79d122542ad136d4651dd10f0c3f5ced</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THAI CRIMINAL CODE SECTION 388&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 388 describes penalties for public indecency, with fines not exceeding five hundred Baht."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-d274c9e863fb793abab4dc5884e523b8</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;CRIMINAL CODE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Criminal Code is a legal document that outlines crimes and offenses along with their respective punishments, serving as a foundational legal framework in Thailand."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Criminal Code is a legal document that outlines the laws and regulations governing criminal liability and the conditions for offenders, as referenced in sections and amendments throughout the text."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Criminal Code is a legal framework outlining criminal offenses and their corresponding penalties, serving as a fundamental document in legal proceedings."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Criminal Code is a legal framework that outlines the laws and penalties related to various offenses, including those concerning acts of violence and sexual offenses."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Criminal Code is a legislative document that outlines general provisions, definitions, and applicable laws related to offenses."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-de71dcf326342843893937651bd927f6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ce00bf86a210ec770e6555803254e48b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cbd1a08621190b50907588a23e2a2a3d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b879f636061e8c548d80b7bcc128b902&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-172659577ca25912dfd293590d712aae</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 314&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A section detailing penalties for supporting the commission of offenses outlined in Section 313, equating supporters' liability to principals' penalties."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-d23931e05623c30bf7072dff6eb48dd5</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 103&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 103 sets out the applicability of Title I's provisions to petty offences, with certain exceptions."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-6d1b2dd52957470e3d89b1c4d7b09769</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;POND&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Ponds are natural or artificial water bodies that are protected by legal measures against contamination for public use."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-3aa47916d44030b53f9aac3e17c9da38</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;CRIMINAL CODE (NO. 2), B.E. 2512&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Criminal Code (No. 2), B.E. 2512 is a legislative act amending parts of the criminal code."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-a5d0229c550b9e954016797ed8a8ac12</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THAI CRIMINAL CODE SECTION 389&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 389 covers causing harm or nuisance with falling objects, imposing fines and/or imprisonment."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-d274c9e863fb793abab4dc5884e523b8</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;ACT AMENDING THE CRIMINAL CODE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Act Amending the Criminal Code is a legislative event that introduced several amendments to Thailand's Criminal Code, affecting various laws and legal procedures."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Act Amending the Criminal Code refers to legislative changes made to update and modify existing laws in Thailand."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-cbd1a08621190b50907588a23e2a2a3d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4d20d8c7e43c4c0033ebd04d8b30c380</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 315&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Describes the role and penalties for acting as an intermediary in demanding or accepting property related to offenses under Section 313."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-d23931e05623c30bf7072dff6eb48dd5</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 104&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 104 clarifies that petty offences are punishable regardless of intent, unless otherwise specified."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-6d1b2dd52957470e3d89b1c4d7b09769</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;RESERVOIR&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Reservoirs are large storage areas for water, protected under law from being contaminated by harmful substances."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-3aa47916d44030b53f9aac3e17c9da38</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 335&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 335 refers to provisions in the Thai Criminal Code related to theft and penalties associated with it."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 335 specifies additional circumstances and increased punishments for theft under particular conditions."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-a5d0229c550b9e954016797ed8a8ac12&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b3afe90ab72cbd500e64a92888a58319</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THAI CRIMINAL CODE SECTION 390&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 390 specifies penalties for causing bodily or mental harm through negligence, with imprisonment or fine limits."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-d274c9e863fb793abab4dc5884e523b8</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 278&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 278 describes punishments for indecent acts committed against persons over fifteen years old, including imprisonment up to ten years or fines."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 278 is a specific provision within the Criminal Code addressing offenses related to acts of violence against children."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-cbd1a08621190b50907588a23e2a2a3d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bf2e9ba1c433d67ab7eef97426e05cd4</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 316&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A section providing for reduced punishment if an offender restores the liberty of a person taken away, restrained, or confined, under certain conditions."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-d23931e05623c30bf7072dff6eb48dd5</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 105&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 105 states that attempts to commit petty offences are not punishable."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-6d1b2dd52957470e3d89b1c4d7b09769</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 233&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 233 specifies legal consequences for using conveyances under dangerous conditions for passenger transport."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-3aa47916d44030b53f9aac3e17c9da38</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 335 BIS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 335 bis addresses theft involving religious or national property and stipulates harsher penalties."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 335 bis refers to an additional provision in the Thai Criminal Code specifying stricter penalties for certain types of theft."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-a5d0229c550b9e954016797ed8a8ac12&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b3afe90ab72cbd500e64a92888a58319</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THAI CRIMINAL CODE SECTION 391&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 391 describes penalties for non-harmful violence, with imprisonment or fine limits."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-d274c9e863fb793abab4dc5884e523b8</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 279&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 279 is a provision in the Criminal Code outlining penalties for offenses involving the exploitation or harm of children."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 279 provides for punishment of indecent acts on a child under fifteen, regardless of consent, with penalties including up to ten years of imprisonment or fines, with additional penalties if violence or deception is involved."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-cbd1a08621190b50907588a23e2a2a3d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bf2e9ba1c433d67ab7eef97426e05cd4</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 317&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Defines penalties for taking away a child under the age of fifteen from a guardian, including enhancements if done with lucre or indecent intent."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-d23931e05623c30bf7072dff6eb48dd5</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 106&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 106 affirms that supporting a petty offence is not punishable."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-6d1b2dd52957470e3d89b1c4d7b09769</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 234&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 234 addresses penalties for actions affecting public utility systems like electricity or water supply."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-3aa47916d44030b53f9aac3e17c9da38</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THAI CRIMINAL CODE SECTION 392&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 392 outlines penalties for causing fear through threats, with imprisonment or fine limits."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-d274c9e863fb793abab4dc5884e523b8</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 280&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 280 specifies the penalties for offenses that result in grievous bodily harm or death to the victim."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-cbd1a08621190b50907588a23e2a2a3d</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 339 BIS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 339 bis details additional penalties for robbery causing bodily, mental harm, or death, including life imprisonment and the death penalty."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 339 bis outlines penalties related to robbery offenses under specific circumstances."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-b879f636061e8c548d80b7bcc128b902&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a5d0229c550b9e954016797ed8a8ac12</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 318&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Outlines the penalties for taking away a minor aged over fifteen but under eighteen against their will, including penalties for those who facilitate such actions."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-d23931e05623c30bf7072dff6eb48dd5</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;B.E. 2530&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"B.E. 2530 is an event related to the amendment of Section 318 and Section 319 of the Act Amending the Criminal Code."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-78127285a70d48835c00c4ab2953f9f8</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 235&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 235 describes the legal repercussions for obstructing public communication systems such as postal or telecom services."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-3aa47916d44030b53f9aac3e17c9da38</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 340 BIS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 340 bis imposes penalties for gang-robbery against specific properties and under certain conditions, such as involving weapons."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 340 bis specifies crimes and penalties associated with gang-robbery in Thai law."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-b879f636061e8c548d80b7bcc128b902&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a5d0229c550b9e954016797ed8a8ac12</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THAI CRIMINAL CODE SECTION 393&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 393 covers penalties for insults made in person or publication, with imprisonment or fine limits."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-d274c9e863fb793abab4dc5884e523b8</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 281&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 281 details the conditions under which offenses are compoundable and do not cause severe harm or involve the public."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-cbd1a08621190b50907588a23e2a2a3d</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 319&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"This section details penalties for offenses involving taking a consenting minor aged over fifteen but under eighteen away for lucre or indecent intentions."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-d23931e05623c30bf7072dff6eb48dd5</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;B.E. 2525&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"B.E. 2525 refers to an event where Section 320 was amended by Section 10 of the Act Amending the Criminal Code."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-78127285a70d48835c00c4ab2953f9f8</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 236&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 236 provides legal frameworks against adulterating food or drugs, emphasizing consumer health protection."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-3aa47916d44030b53f9aac3e17c9da38</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THAI CRIMINAL CODE SECTION 394&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 394 specifies penalties for allowing animals onto others' farmland, with imprisonment or fine limits."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-d274c9e863fb793abab4dc5884e523b8</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 282&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 282 focuses on the procurement or seduction of individuals for indecent acts with their consent, specifying varying penalties."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 282 involves the unlawful procurement of persons for purposes of prostitution or similar exploitation."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-cbd1a08621190b50907588a23e2a2a3d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-79d122542ad136d4651dd10f0c3f5ced</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;OFFENCES RELATING TO PUBLIC PEACE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Offences provided in Sections 209 to 216, aimed at actions that disrupt or harm public tranquility and order."&lt;SEP&gt;"These offences include acts outlined in Sections 209 to 216 and relate to maintaining public order and tranquility."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-a3d4a61fa1cf40d9a40ee60bcdbb217e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6e4efb3313af866dc7bcaba7c4daff62</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;B.E. 2535&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"B.E. 2535 indicates an event concerning amendments to sections of the Act Amending the Criminal Code, including Section 326 and Section 328."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-78127285a70d48835c00c4ab2953f9f8</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 237&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 237 covers legal penalties for introducing harmful substances into food or water intended for public consumption."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-3aa47916d44030b53f9aac3e17c9da38</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THAI CRIMINAL CODE SECTION 395&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 395 details fines for allowing animals onto others' prepared or cultivated land."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-d274c9e863fb793abab4dc5884e523b8</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 283&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 283 addresses coercive acts for indecent purposes, including deceitful means, and imposes heavier penalties for underage victims."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 283 outlines offenses related to causing, procuring, or serving a child for, prostitution or sexual exploitation."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-cbd1a08621190b50907588a23e2a2a3d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-79d122542ad136d4651dd10f0c3f5ced</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;OFFENCES RELATING TO CAUSING PUBLIC DANGERS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"These offences, covered in Sections 217 to 224, involve actions that pose risks to public safety."&lt;SEP&gt;"These offences, outlined in various sections particularly between 217 and 238, involve acts that pose risks or harm to public safety and well-being."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-a3d4a61fa1cf40d9a40ee60bcdbb217e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6e4efb3313af866dc7bcaba7c4daff62</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;CRIMINAL CODE SECTIONS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Various sections of the Criminal Code that outline offenses such as taking a minor, disclosure of private secrets, and defamation, along with their respective punishments."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-78127285a70d48835c00c4ab2953f9f8</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 238&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 238 details punishments for offenses leading to severe consequences, such as death or serious injury."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-3aa47916d44030b53f9aac3e17c9da38</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THAI CRIMINAL CODE SECTION 396&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 396 covers the penalties for leaving a carcass that causes a smell near public ways, with fines not exceeding five hundred Baht."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-d274c9e863fb793abab4dc5884e523b8</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 283 BIS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 283 bis adds provisions regarding taking individuals for indecent acts with their consent, especially focusing on age-related penalties."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-cbd1a08621190b50907588a23e2a2a3d</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;OFFENCES RELATING TO CURRENCIES&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"These offences, as specified in Sections 240 to 246, deal with crimes related to currency and financial regulations."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-6e4efb3313af866dc7bcaba7c4daff62</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 239&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 239 deals with penalties related to negligence causing danger to life, following the guidelines in prior sections."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-3aa47916d44030b53f9aac3e17c9da38</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THAI CRIMINAL CODE SECTION 397&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 397 describes penalties for public bullying or causing annoyance, with imprisonment or fine limits."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-d274c9e863fb793abab4dc5884e523b8</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SECTION 284&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Section 284 covers further offenses that pertain to the exploitation of children and the corresponding punishment."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 284 details the use of coercion or deceit in the context of indecent acts and the associated penalties."&lt;SEP&gt;"Section 284 outlines the punishment for taking another person for indecent acts through deceit or violence, with specified imprisonment and fines."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-cbd1a08621190b50907588a23e2a2a3d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-79d122542ad136d4651dd10f0c3f5ced&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4d20d8c7e43c4c0033ebd04d8b30c380</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;OFFENCES RELATING TO SEXUALITY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Offences Relating to Sexuality are crimes related to illegal sexual conduct, as addressed in sections 282 and 283."&lt;SEP&gt;"These are criminal acts related to sexual conduct, specified under particular sections of the criminal code."&lt;SEP&gt;"These offences, as provided in Sections 276 to 286, encompass crimes regarding sexual behavior and conduct."&lt;SEP&gt;"This category, provided in Sections 276 to 285, involves illegal and unethical acts related to sexual conduct."</data>
