    <node id="&quot;CAPITAL OF FRANCE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Refers to the leading city and administrative center of France; commonly known to be Paris, not Yangon."&lt;SEP&gt;"The term 'capital of France' is intended to refer to the city that is officially designated as the administrative center, which is Paris."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-6e459e292c09831cb5355afa423a1cad&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8527717aaf5c016fde3403d174020e30</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;CAPITAL OF SPAIN&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Refers to the leading city and administrative center of Spain, correctly identified as Madrid."&lt;SEP&gt;"The term 'capital of Spain' refers to the city serving as the political and cultural hub, identified as Madrid."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-6e459e292c09831cb5355afa423a1cad&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8527717aaf5c016fde3403d174020e30</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;MYANMAR&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Myanmar is a country in Southeast Asia, known for its diverse culture and history, although incorrectly labeled as the capital of France in this context."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-6e459e292c09831cb5355afa423a1cad</data>
    </node>
