    <edge source="&quot;PUBLIC PROSECUTOR&quot;" target="&quot;THE COURT&quot;">
      <data key="d3">36.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"The Court receives statements and evidence about offenders from the Public Prosecutor to decide on warnings or further actions."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Public Prosecutor can apply to The Court for the appointment of a guardian or custodian for interested persons."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Public Prosecutor can apply to The Court to void a marriage when no other eligible party can do so."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Public Prosecutor can submit changes in circumstances to the Court, which may lead to modifications in the Court’s orders regarding children's care."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Public Prosecutor is an entity under the power of The Court, involved in legal and confinement processes, demonstrating a working relationship in enforcing judgments."</data>
      <data key="d5">"legal application, judicial process"&lt;SEP&gt;"legal authority, law enforcement"&lt;SEP&gt;"legal procedure, oversight"&lt;SEP&gt;"legal proceedings, guardianship"&lt;SEP&gt;"legal process, collaboration"</data>
      <data key="d6">chunk-ce00bf86a210ec770e6555803254e48b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4e5197de768063837bf5a455698da0aa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2f3971fdef62800a7dabb59d8dfbd427&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-268065f480c7c2e17bd0004a31f0f454&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-52f915665c66fcbe0e7563608cbf7287</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;PUBLIC PROSECUTOR&quot;" target="&quot;THE GUARDIAN&quot;">
      <data key="d3">8.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"The Public Prosecutor can challenge The Guardian's role if deemed necessary, such as in cases of misconduct or failure to perform duties."</data>
      <data key="d5">"legal accountability, oversight"</data>
      <data key="d6">chunk-cb6f943ed567718e3b0963e9f80b3c0b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;PUBLIC PROSECUTOR&quot;" target="&quot;PERSON OF UNSOUND MIND&quot;">
      <data key="d3">7.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"The Public Prosecutor can apply for a person to be adjudged incompetent due to unsound mind."</data>
      <data key="d5">"legal application, mental health"</data>
      <data key="d6">chunk-99e04c388a7385a4978847a999d423f1</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;PUBLIC PROSECUTOR&quot;" target="&quot;COURT&quot;">
      <data key="d3">64.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"A Public Prosecutor is involved in court processes, responsible for prosecuting cases before the Court."&lt;SEP&gt;"Public Prosecutors present cases and evidence to the Court in judicial proceedings."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Court can send requests to the Public Prosecutor for consideration in proceeding with child legitimacy cases."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Public Prosecutor can apply to the Court for the revocation of an adjudication of disappearance or for the appointment of a temporary representative."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Public Prosecutor can initiate legal proceedings or applications to the Court concerning guardianship issues."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Court interacts with Public Prosecutors in legal proceedings where evidence and statements are required."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Public Prosecutor has the authority to initiate relegation prosecution, and such cases are adjudicated by the Court."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Public Prosecutor interacts with the Court by making requests related to the application or revision of legal measures and judgments."</data>
      <data key="d5">"judicial process, legal application"&lt;SEP&gt;"legal procedure, authority collaboration"&lt;SEP&gt;"legal proceedings, advocacy"&lt;SEP&gt;"legal proceedings, prosecution"&lt;SEP&gt;"legal process, collaboration"&lt;SEP&gt;"legal process, court activities"&lt;SEP&gt;"legal process, judicial authority"</data>
      <data key="d6">chunk-e1e198b1f8b66564b0fae2fbe893a4c6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9fb8ecc1d3b7f08bd11bfbe372805373&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e417732f0f4e36ea8784fa2cc5dd8a85&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6fd5b0ac67c6f4aafc6e1ef0e7ce2a77&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e8a12bcf29dd0e194c7a3e4a71523199&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d9947bc7fb3e59afe960708bcf533e3c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6e4efb3313af866dc7bcaba7c4daff62&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e0099557ffbf92309faf8ac19f118ba2</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;PUBLIC PROSECUTOR&quot;" target="&quot;GUARDIAN&quot;">
      <data key="d3">6.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"The Public Prosecutor can apply to the Court for intervention if there is misconduct by the guardian."</data>
      <data key="d5">"legal intervention, oversight"</data>
      <data key="d6">chunk-d10f80809fc56f611edbadcb4809bc4e</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;PUBLIC PROSECUTOR&quot;" target="&quot;JUDICIAL OFFICIALS&quot;">
      <data key="d3">9.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"Judicial Officials include roles like Public Prosecutors, who are part of the justice system described in the document."</data>
      <data key="d5">"legal roles, justice system"</data>
