      <data key="d3">18.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"The Court pronounces judgments that affect the actions of The Registrar in the registration of legitimation and parental power decisions."&lt;SEP&gt;"The court notifies the registrar of judgments or orders regarding the dissolution or bankruptcy of a foundation."</data>
      <data key="d5">"legal proceedings, decision enforcement"&lt;SEP&gt;"legal process, authority"</data>
      <data key="d6">chunk-86deb2357b8656ccf8680e27cbac71ec&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c8c3be6aeb4b1e7e1a17d53346a1d923</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;THE REGISTRAR&quot;" target="&quot;THE ASSOCIATION&quot;">
      <data key="d3">9.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"The Registrar monitors and enforces the legal status of associations, with the power to strike them off the register if they fail to comply with legal standards."</data>
      <data key="d5">"regulatory oversight, legal compliance"</data>
      <data key="d6">chunk-182a2b244fdc4ad235c762ab46288dca</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;THE REGISTRAR&quot;" target="&quot;THE MINISTER OF INTERIOR&quot;">
      <data key="d3">8.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"The Minister of Interior appoints the Registrar and oversees the execution of association-related laws and regulations."</data>
      <data key="d5">"government supervision, regulatory control"</data>
      <data key="d6">chunk-182a2b244fdc4ad235c762ab46288dca</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;THE REGISTRAR&quot;" target="&quot;THE COMMITTEE&quot;">
      <data key="d3">8.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"The committee is responsible for notifying the registrar within a specified timeframe after the dissolution of a foundation."</data>
      <data key="d5">"notification, compliance"</data>
      <data key="d6">chunk-86deb2357b8656ccf8680e27cbac71ec</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;THE REGISTRAR&quot;" target="&quot;GOVERNMENT GAZETTE&quot;">
      <data key="d3">7.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"The registrar is responsible for publishing notices of foundation dissolution in the Government Gazette."</data>
      <data key="d5">"publication, notification"</data>
      <data key="d6">chunk-86deb2357b8656ccf8680e27cbac71ec</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;THE COMMITTEE OF THE FOUNDATION&quot;" target="&quot;THE FOUNDATION&quot;">
      <data key="d3">9.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"The Committee manages and implements changes to the Foundation's regulations to align with its objectives and legal obligations."</data>
      <data key="d5">"management, governance"</data>
      <data key="d6">chunk-a8f2d8db15aae9334e2b0c36d4ea99c8</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;DIRECTORS OF THE FOUNDATION&quot;" target="&quot;THE FOUNDATION&quot;">
      <data key="d3">8.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"Directors are responsible for its day-to-day management and ensuring that the Foundation’s activities are lawful and effective."</data>
      <data key="d5">"operational management, compliance"</data>
      <data key="d6">chunk-a8f2d8db15aae9334e2b0c36d4ea99c8</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;CIVIL AND COMMERCIAL CODE B.E. 2535&quot;" target="&quot;KROMAKARN AMPHOE&quot;">
      <data key="d3">8.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"The Kromakarn Amphoe enforces the amended provisions of the Civil and Commercial Code concerning wills."</data>
      <data key="d5">"legal authority, regulatory enforcement"</data>
      <data key="d6">chunk-950a514fa4e2ba58663fe41bd3a39da9</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;CIVIL AND COMMERCIAL CODE B.E. 2535&quot;" target="&quot;MINISTER OF INTERIOR, DEFENSE AND FOREIGN AFFAIRS&quot;">
      <data key="d3">7.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"These ministers are responsible for issuing regulations necessary for the implementation of the provisions in the Civil and Commercial Code concerning wills."</data>
      <data key="d5">"government regulation, legal oversight"</data>
      <data key="d6">chunk-950a514fa4e2ba58663fe41bd3a39da9</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;THE MORTGAGEE&quot;" target="&quot;THE DEBTOR&quot;">
      <data key="d3">9.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"The Mortgagee expects the Debtor to fulfill their obligation, and failure to do so allows the Mortgagee to take legal action."</data>
      <data key="d5">"obligation, legal enforcement"</data>
      <data key="d6">chunk-03ac67cce0a415062b1435a1e40830bb</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;THE MORTGAGEE&quot;" target="&quot;THE MORTGAGOR&quot;">
      <data key="d3">8.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"The Mortgagee lends money to the Mortgagor and holds the mortgagor's property as security for performance."</data>
      <data key="d5">"lending relationship, secured loan"</data>
      <data key="d6">chunk-03ac67cce0a415062b1435a1e40830bb</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;THE MORTGAGEE&quot;" target="&quot;SERVITUDE&quot;">
      <data key="d3">7.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"A servitude cannot precede a mortgage without consent, and mortgages take priority over subsequent servitudes affecting the property."</data>
      <data key="d5">"property rights, priority"</data>
      <data key="d6">chunk-03ac67cce0a415062b1435a1e40830bb</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;MILITARY OFFICER OR OFFICIAL OF COMMISSIONED RANK&quot;" target="&quot;KROMAKARN AMPHOE&quot;">
      <data key="d3">7.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"The military officer or official of commissioned rank has similar duties as the Kromakarn Amphoe concerning the validation of wills during arms conflict or war."</data>
      <data key="d5">"authority extension, war-time protocol"</data>
      <data key="d6">chunk-950a514fa4e2ba58663fe41bd3a39da9</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;THE MORTGAGOR&quot;" target="&quot;THE DEBTOR&quot;">
      <data key="d3">7.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"The Mortgagor may be distinct from the Debtor when securing an obligation for another's debt, impacting recovery and enforcement rights."</data>
      <data key="d5">"third-party obligation, security"</data>
      <data key="d6">chunk-03ac67cce0a415062b1435a1e40830bb</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;THE DEBTOR&quot;" target="&quot;THE CREDITOR&quot;">
      <data key="d3">9.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"The Debtor must compensate The Creditor for damages or provide substitute compensation during default."</data>
      <data key="d5">"compensation, obligation"</data>
      <data key="d6">chunk-2c01a4f68c167448d4624c0e8d938db0</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;CONTROLLER OF PROPERTY&quot;" target="&quot;MINOR&quot;">
      <data key="d3">8.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"A Controller of Property may be appointed to manage the property on behalf of a Minor as dictated by a will."</data>
      <data key="d5">"guardian role, property oversight"</data>
      <data key="d6">chunk-553b3730ac4ba8b3212a7d230dbc31ad</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;CONTROLLER OF PROPERTY&quot;" target="&quot;INCOMPETENT PERSON&quot;">
      <data key="d3">8.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"A Controller of Property is appointed to manage property for an Incompetent Person as provided for by the will."</data>
      <data key="d5">"property management, legal guardianship"</data>
      <data key="d6">chunk-553b3730ac4ba8b3212a7d230dbc31ad</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;SERVITUDE&quot;" target="&quot;DOMINANT PROPERTY&quot;">
      <data key="d3">17.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"Servitude benefits the Dominant Property by imposing obligations on the Servient Property for its advantage."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Dominant Property gains utility and benefits from a Servitude imposed on the Servient Property."</data>
      <data key="d5">"legal obligation, benefit"&lt;SEP&gt;"property benefit, legal right"</data>
      <data key="d6">chunk-0e69519b80d6cad28fe98f2e9235bd60&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9f9bc4a4809d7c6d989c8e5d2ab6f09f</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;SERVITUDE&quot;" target="&quot;SERVIENT PROPERTY&quot;">
      <data key="d3">17.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"The Servient Property is burdened by the Servitude, which requires it to comply with specific conditions for the Dominant Property."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Servient Property is subject to Servitude, imposing legal restrictions and obligations for the benefit of another property."</data>
      <data key="d5">"burden, legal obligation"&lt;SEP&gt;"legal burden, property limitation"</data>
      <data key="d6">chunk-0e69519b80d6cad28fe98f2e9235bd60&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9f9bc4a4809d7c6d989c8e5d2ab6f09f</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;LEGITIMATION&quot;" target="&quot;FATHER&quot;">
      <data key="d3">8.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"The Father's recognition through legitimation affects the child's legal rights and status."</data>
      <data key="d5">"parental recognition, legal status"</data>
      <data key="d6">chunk-a0818329731c6e20f0c0c43a0133253c</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;LEGITIMATION&quot;" target="&quot;MOTHER&quot;">
      <data key="d3">7.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"The Mother's relationship with the Father, such as elopement or open cohabitation, can influence the legitimation process."</data>
      <data key="d5">"parental relationship, legal influence"</data>
      <data key="d6">chunk-a0818329731c6e20f0c0c43a0133253c</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;LEGITIMATION&quot;" target="&quot;THE COURT&quot;">
      <data key="d3">17.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"The Court handles cases of legitimation, determining whether a child is legally recognized as legitimate."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Court plays a key role in the legitimation process, making judgments that can affect a child's legitimacy and associated parental rights."</data>
      <data key="d5">"legal authority, child status"</data>
      <data key="d6">chunk-a0818329731c6e20f0c0c43a0133253c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c8c3be6aeb4b1e7e1a17d53346a1d923</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;LEGITIMATION&quot;" target="&quot;THE CHILD&quot;">
      <data key="d3">9.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"The Child's status as legitimate or illegitimate is determined through the process of legitimation, impacting their rights and parental relationships."</data>
      <data key="d5">"legal status, child rights"</data>
      <data key="d6">chunk-c8c3be6aeb4b1e7e1a17d53346a1d923</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;THE CHILD&quot;" target="&quot;THE FATHER&quot;">
      <data key="d3">8.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"The Father seeks to legitimize The Child and attain parental power, often needing The Child's consent in the legal process."</data>
      <data key="d5">"parental rights, legitimacy"</data>
      <data key="d6">chunk-c8c3be6aeb4b1e7e1a17d53346a1d923</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;THE CHILD&quot;" target="&quot;THE MOTHER&quot;">
      <data key="d3">7.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"The Mother holds legal parental rights and is involved in giving consent for the legitimation of The Child."</data>
      <data key="d5">"parental consent, legitimacy impact"</data>
      <data key="d6">chunk-c8c3be6aeb4b1e7e1a17d53346a1d923</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;THE CHILD&quot;" target="&quot;THE COURT&quot;">
      <data key="d3">9.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"The Court makes decisions impacting The Child's legitimization and the assignment of parental power through legal judgments."</data>
      <data key="d5">"legal decisions, child welfare"</data>
      <data key="d6">chunk-c8c3be6aeb4b1e7e1a17d53346a1d923</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;THE MOTHER&quot;" target="&quot;THE FATHER&quot;">
      <data key="d3">8.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"The Father's application for legitimation requires The Mother's consent or can be contested by her in legal proceedings."</data>
      <data key="d5">"consent, legal rights"</data>
      <data key="d6">chunk-c8c3be6aeb4b1e7e1a17d53346a1d923</data>
    </edge>
